title: southern gal biscuits
directions: Sift all dry ingredients in bowl.
Add shortening and blend until size of cornmeal.
Pour milk into flour mixture slowly.
Add the egg.
Stir to a stiff dough.
Knead on floured surface 5 times.
Roll or pat to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Put in greased 9-inch round cake pan.
Cover tops with 1 tablespoon bacon grease.
Bake in 450° oven for 15 minutes. Makes 9 or 10.

title: cheesy spinach soup
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan.
Add onions and garlic.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add chicken broth.
Heat to boil.
Add noodles and salt. Cook 6 minutes.
Stir in milk, spinach and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Do not boil.
Sprinkle with croutons and paprika. (Can substitute broccoli or/add American, Cheddar cheeses.)

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix first three ingredients in a microwave safe bowl. Microwave on low, stirring constantly, until morsels are melted. Add chopped nuts if desired.
Pour into
greased
square baking dish.
Cool.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: "purple cow"
directions: A child's treat, summertime special.
Ideal party favorite! Not just for children, "Mom."

title: white fruit cake
directions: Make cake batter as usual.
Sprinkle candied fruit, raisins and nuts with 1 cup flour and add to batter.
Bake in tube pan, loaf pans or other size pans.
Line pan with 2 thicknesses of brown paper; grease each thickness.
Bake at 300° for approximately 2 hours in tube pan.
Other time vary depending on depth of pan.
Cake is best made 2 or 3 weeks before using.
After cool, wrap in cheese cloth soaked in pineapple juice and store in refrigerator or freezer until ready to use.

title: dudley's stew
directions: Add stew meat to about 2 quarts of water.
Boil until brown and tender.
(Extra water can be added when, and if, needed.)
Add tomato sauce, cubed potatoes and sliced carrot.
Cook until potatoes and carrot are done.
Add spices.
Bring to a vigorous boil and add macaroni.
Cook until tender about 10 minutes.
Goes good with cornbread.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Microwave until heated through.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 3 cups dip.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix together and chill 1 hour and serve.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Add any spices you like (hot pepper and salt).
Cook until thick.
Put in jars and seal.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and bake in a 350° preheated oven for 45 minutes.
Drain off grease and pour an 8 ounce can tomato sauce on top.
Bake for 15 minutes more.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread undiluted soup over bottom of a 4 to 5-quart Dutch oven.
Add chicken and turn to coat.

Sprinkle with thyme. Add sweet potato chunks. Cover and bake 50 minutes. Add peas. Cover and bake 10 minutes longer or until chicken is no longer pink near the bone and vegetables are tender. Serves 4.

title: easy pizza pie
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and spices until browned.
Drain; set aside.
Spread 1 can crescent rolls on bottom of loaf pan.
Spread tomato soup on top of rolls.
Next, spread beef mixture over tomato soup.
Top with cheese.
Lastly top with second can of crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until browned on top.

title: red beans and rice(8 servings)
directions: Place the smoked hock, water and kidney beans in Dutch oven. Bring the water to a boil and add the hot pepper sauce, Worcestershire sauce, celery, onion, green pepper, garlic and mixed pickling spices (tied in cheesecloth).
When boiling, stir well, then cover pot and reduce heat to simmering.
Cook until the beans are very well done, at least 2 hours, but no more than 3 hours.
Uncover and stir the beans occasionally and add a little more water.
Add no salt to these beans.
Near end of cooking time, remove pork hock and cool.
Continue simmering the beans, mashing a cupful or so, to get the creamy texture.
Strip off the meat from the hock and return to pot, along with the sliced sausage.
Continue to cook approximately 15 minutes.
Remove spice bag.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: ham noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Cream the cheese; add milk and soup.
Mix well with mixer.
Add other ingredients.
Place in a 3-quart Pyrex casserole dish or 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix together margarine, flour and pecans and spread in bottom of an 11 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Let cool. Blend together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread this mixture over crust.
Mix pudding with milk.
Let this begin to set up and pour over cream cheese layer.
Top with whipped topping. Refrigerate.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Chill dough for 3 hours on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake until edges are slightly brown (approximately 8 minutes) at 375°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla. Add eggs and beat. Add peanut butter. Mix together dry ingredients. Add flour mixture to peanut butter mixture. Beat well. Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto ungreased, shiny cookie sheet. Press with floured fork to make crisscross. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Wait 5 minutes. Move cookies, with a flexible spatula, to a wire rack to cool. Makes 5 dozen.

title: lime cream cheese salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with the 2 cups hot water. Set aside until slightly congealed. Beat cream cheese until soft. Add mayonnaise to cheese and also juice from crushed pineapple. Mix until well blended. Make Dream Whip according to directions. Fold all the ingredients into the slightly congealed Jell-O. Let set for 2 hours or overnight in the refrigerator.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix 1 pound powdered sugar, coconut, pecans and milk.
Add more sugar as needed to maintain consistency to shape into balls with hands.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Mix Veg-All, soup and chicken; pour into 1 pie crust.
Put other pie crust over mixture.
Crimp edges with fork; trim sides. DO NOT VENT.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until brown.

title: spanish coffee cake
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients well with a mixer.
Remove 1/2 cup of mixture and save for topping.
Add remaining ingredients to mixture and pour into greased cake pan.
Sprinkle topping on cake and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned cookies
directions: In a small bowl, mix the flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar; beat in eggs. Gradually stir in the flour mixture.
Using 1 level tablespoon of the dough for each, roll into balls.
Dip in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Place a few inches apart on greased cookie sheets. Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Do not overbake.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: spinach cheese casserole(serves 8)
directions: Chop spinach.
Heat all ingredients in a saucepan.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake one half hour at 350°.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Put cooked noodles in greased casserole dish.
Mix remainder of ingredients and pour over noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fanny mae chocolate fudge
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add sugars and milk; stir until sugar melts (medium heat).
Cover; boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows until melted.
Add chocolates, one at a time.
Stir each until melted.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a very large, flat jelly roll pan (11 x 15-inch).
Cool in fridge for 30 minutes.
Makes about 10 pounds.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place in baking dish.
Bake in oven at 350° (glass dish) for 1 hour or at 400° (metal dish) for 45 minutes. Ten minutes before done, pour 1/4 cup tomato sauce over top of meat and finish baking.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Add enough boiling water to dissolve the sugar and cocoa.
Add almost 1 cup milk or cream.

title: shrimp okra gumbo
directions: Into a heavy gumbo pot, pour oil; add onions and fry for 5 minutes.
Add okra; smother for 45 minutes or until cooked.
Add salted shrimp, water and garlic.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 40 minutes.
(Okra seeds will look brown.)
Before serving, mash whole cooked garlic pods that float on the top.
Season to taste with salt, pepper, and hot sauce.
Serve over rice.
For a variation, add 1 can whole tomatoes, smothered with okra.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.
The flavor is even better the next day.

title: moon in june salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine lettuce, watercress, spinach leaves, chives, oil and lemon juice.
Season with salt and pepper. Put mixture on shell-shaped cabbage leaves.
Garnish with artichoke bottoms, onion and garlic.
Arrange grated carrots in a circle around the cabbage leaves.

title: crunchy fried tomatoes
directions: Slice the tomatoes.
Dip slices into the egg; then into the bread crumbs.
Melt butter in a large skillet.
Drop the tomatoes into the butter, turning only once, until golden brown.
Season to taste.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple slices
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Roll out 1/2 dough; place on cookie sheet.
Place sliced apples on dough.
Add seasoning. Sprinkle on apples.
Roll out other half of dough to cover apples. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and cool.
Frost with powdered sugar, butter and hot water frosting.
Cut in slices.

title: golden fudge
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, butter, salt, evaporated milk and water.
Heat, stirring constantly, to boiling; then cook rapidly, stirring several times.
Remove from heat at once, when a soft ball forms (when dropped in a cup of cold water).
Cool mixture in pan or until lukewarm; heat 2 or 3 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix shortening and sugar, add eggs and mix well.
Add pumpkin and then the flour a little at a time, alternating with the water a little at a time.
Add salt, soda, baking soda, baking powder and spices and mix well.
Fold in the nuts and raisins.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes in loaf pans until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix together the wine, rice and chicken broth; place in greased baking dish.
Place chicken over rice mixture.
Add about 1/2 cup milk and undrained mushrooms to soup.
Mix well and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with thyme and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cover with aluminum foil; cook another 20 minutes.
Remove cover and allow crumbs to lightly brown.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix flour and cake mix in extra large bowl with lid.

Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add softened yeast to flour and cake mixture. Mix well. Seal lid and place in warm water to help mix rise. Roll dough on very lightly floured surface. Spread with soft butter, sugar and cinnamon. Roll to form rolls and cut in 1 1/4-inch sections.
Place on cookie sheet.
Let rise again.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 24 to 36 rolls.

title: granola
directions: Mix in large bowl the oatmeal, wheat germ, nuts, coconut, cereal, sunflower and sesame seeds and milk.
Mix well.
In another bowl, mix honey, oil, vanilla and cinnamon (optional). Mix into cereal mixture.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Stir and bake 15 minutes more.
Add 1 cup raisins.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix together the cherry jello, blueberry pie filling, crushed pineapple, hot and cold water.
Put in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix well in blender.
May be used in any recipe.
Use same amount as sweetened milk.

title: pineapple shake cake
directions: Beat the eggs and add the pineapple.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Bake in a 325° to 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken in wine
directions: Skin chicken.
Mix flour with Bells seasoning until flour is tinted.
Dip chicken in tinted flour and quick fry just enough to seal.
Butter casserole dish and sprinkle with favorite herbs. Place chicken in dish, dark meat first, then white.
Cover with can of mushroom soup.
Pour 3/4 cup of sherry wine over all. Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: scratch italian sauce
directions: Peel and seed tomatoes. Chop up and set aside.
Saute green onions, green peppers and garlic.
Pour in tomatoes and spices. Simmer on low for at least 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Serve on pasta or grilled chicken.

title: salmon and eggs
directions: Melt margarine in frypan.
Add salmon (mashed with fork), eggs, water, salt, black pepper and onion.
Cook on medium-low for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve over white rice.

title: slushy strawberry punch
directions: Cook sugar and 2 cups water in a Dutch oven over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Stir in remaining 4 cups water, orange juice and next 3 ingredients.
Pour mixture into large plastic container and freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 1 hour before serving.
Place in large punch bowl and break into chunks.
Add soft drink and stir until slushy.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels with oleo and sugar.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Bake 7 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.
Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over crust. Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Add strawberries and pineapple with juice.
Chill until almost thick; pour over cheese mixture. Chill 1 hour.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour; mix well.
Add egg yolks, slightly beaten, to mixture along with milk slowly.
Add margarine and cook on low temperature until thickened.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and cover with meringue and brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Pour combined barbecue sauce and dressing over chicken. Cover.
Marinate 1 hour.
Drain; reserve marinade.
Place chicken on greased rack of broiler pan or greased grill.
Broil or grill, uncovered, over low coals 10 minutes on each side or until tender, brushing occasionally with reserved marinade.

title: curried pumpkin soup
directions: Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan over moderate heat.
Add onion and leek; saute, stirring often, until soft, about 8 minutes.
Stir in pumpkin, chicken broth and spices.
Bring to a boil, stirring; reduce the heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Process in blender or food processor in batches.
(May be refrigerated for 2 days or frozen, puree only.)

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Let cool 15 minutes.
Add cranberry sauce, stirring to mix.
Add nuts, apple and pineapple to gelatin mixture.
Pour into oiled mold or 9 x 13-inch rectangle dish.
Chill until firm.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Let vegetables sit out and thaw at least part way.
Put into large casserole. Add 2 cans cream of mushroom or celery soup and mix.
Bake in 350° oven 1/2 hour, then add grated Cheddar cheese. Bake another 15 minutes. Sprinkle on onion rings and bake a final 15 minutes.

title: marinated pork chops
directions: Put 1 1/2-inch butterfly pork chops, cut in half (works with other chops too) in a large Ziploc bag.
Pour 1/2 of large bottle of Wish-Bone salad dressing over pork chops.
Marinate several hours.
(If pork chops are frozen, let thaw in marinade for 8 hours.)

title: plum pastry
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour and combine until dough is formed.
Sprinkle with flour as needed to prevent sticking to fingers and pat dough into greased and floured 11 x 14-inch jelly roll pan or large pizza pan.
Bake dough only for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: brown rice
directions: Brown rice and onion in margarine.
Pour in casserole.
Add soup, cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: e z wet chocolate cake
directions: In a large bowl combine sugar and flour.

title: curry pickles
directions: Wash and drain cucumbers.
Combine salt and water.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand 5 hours.
Drain; rinse thoroughly.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add cucumbers.
Heat until boiling.
Pack in sterilized pint jars.
Water bath jars in boiling water for 20 minutes.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: In Dutch oven, fry bacon until crisp.
Remove and drain pan. In same pan saute ground beef, onion and celery until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, crumbling bacon on top of beans.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 375°.
This serves quite a few people.
Can be reduced in quantity if too much.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt, shortening, eggs and mashed potatoes.
Mix flour in by hand until dough is easy to handle.
Turn onto floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place greased side up in greased bowl.
Cover with damp cloth and place in refrigerator.
Let set about 2 hours.
Shape dough into desired shapes.
Cover and let rise until double in size.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Makes 4 dozen rolls.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix together onions and cucumbers, finely chopped.
Mix all ingredients (cream cheese should be at room temperature).
Yields 12 sandwiches.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Fry or microwave bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Set aside.
In bowl, mix eggs, whipping cream, 3/4 cup Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Whip well and set aside.
Cook pasta until firm but not over cooked, drained.

title: quick lemon pepper pork chops
directions: Heat 1/2 teaspoon vegetable oil in a nonstick skillet.
Brown 4 boneless pork loin chops.
Turn and sprinkle with lemon pepper or your favorite seasoning.
Brown other side and serve with potatoes and your favorite vegetable.
Takes 15 minutes cooking time.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer lettuce on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Put pepper, celery, corn, peas, carrots, apples, nuts, shallots and beans layered on top.
Spread mayo and sugar on top.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon bits.
Cover with Saran Wrap and put in refrigerator overnight.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix uncooked meat with seasonings (salt and pepper) and crumble over bottom of lightly greased casserole.
Drain vegetables and put on top of meat.
Pour the soup over vegetables. Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peaches-n-cream pie
directions: Beat cheese until smooth; blend in sugar and milk.
Fold in 2 cups of the whipped topping and spread in crust.
Top with diced peaches, pressing down lightly.
Chill.
Prepare pie filling mix with 1 cup of milk as directed on package for pie.
Add extract and let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in remaining whipped topping and spoon over cheese mixture.
Freeze 1 hour or chill in refrigerator 3 hours before serving.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping and peach slices, if desired.

title: belgian chicken normandy
directions: Melt butter in a large baking pan. Add chicken. Add apples to the pan with the chicken.
Pour the apple brandy and cream over the chicken and apples.
Put in a 350° oven and bake for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and cube chicken.
Spread chicken in bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Mix soup with sour cream and pour over chicken. Prepare stuffing mix according to package and put on top of casserole.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes. Uncover and let brown for 10 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash and onion in saucepan with enough water to cover; cook until tender.
Combine soup, salt and eggs in mixing bowl, mixing well.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Rinse dried beef in cold water.
Spread on the bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Debone chicken breasts and place on dried beef.
Cover with strips of bacon.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Drain off juice.
Add sour cream to cream of mushroom soup. Spread over bacon and bake for 30 more minutes at 350°.

title: libby's cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in square pan.
Freeze and serve.

title: swiss chocolate fondue
directions: Melt chocolate in fondue pot or saucepan.
Add other ingredients; cook 5 minutes.

title: champagne punch
directions: Mix together in large punch bowl.
Do not let powdered sugar settle in bottom.
Float slices of orange, lime and lemon on top; add strawberries.
Freeze strawberries and rose buds in ice ring. Float ice ring on top.
Keep well mixed.
Serve in punch cups.

title: microwave peanut-butter brownie pie
directions: Grease a 9-inch pie plate. Cut peanut butter cups in quarters.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients with finger tips, adding just enough milk to make dough stiff enough to be rolled out thin.
Then sprinkle with sugar.
Cut out with knife into squares or with a glass to make rounds.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° about 10 minutes, or until brown.

title: brown rice
directions: Brown rice in margarine in skillet.
Add soup, water and mushrooms.
Bring to slow boil for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: milk sherbet
directions: Mix sugar, juice and salt.
Add gradually to milk.
(Curdled appearance will disappear in freezing.)
Freeze.

title: onion bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Soak instant onions in water 5 minutes. Combine biscuit mix, egg, milk and Tabasco sauce in large bowl; stir until blended. Stir in onion. Turn into greased 8-inch pie plate. Brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with seed. Bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine sugar, flour, egg and pineapple juice.
Bring to a boil; stir.
Let cool.
Whip in cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip. Serve with fruit.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat egg, milk, Worcestershire sauce, catsup, salt, celery salt and onions together.
Add corn flakes and mix well.
Add meat, mixing thoroughly.
Pack lightly into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake in moderate oven (350°) about 1 hour or until done.
Slice and serve hot.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Add applesauce. Stir in flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and allspice and mix with water.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat; drain and rinse. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Cover and simmer for 1 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Serve with chips or cornbread. Top with cheese and sour cream, if desired.

title: chocolate peanut butter brownies
directions: Stir until it holds together the cake mix, peanut butter, margarine and eggs.
Press 2/3 of batter into the bottom of an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cranberry apple casserole
directions: Combine apples, cranberries and 2 tablespoons flour. Toss to coat fruit. Add sugar; mix well.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish. Combine oatmeal, pecans, brown sugar and 1/2 cup flour.
Add melted butter and stir well. Spoon over mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Garnish with pecans and cranberries. Serves 6 to 8.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate at least two hours before serving.

title: mint fudge
directions: In 3-quart casserole, combine sugar, evaporated milk and butter.
Microwave at 70% power for 12 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add marshmallow cream and peppermint extract, beating until blended. Pour into buttered 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Chill until set.
Cut into squares.

title: hearty beef 'n cheese crescent pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large skillet, brown ground beef with onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Stir cumin seed, garlic salt, salt, tomato sauce, and green beans.
Simmer uncovered while preparing crust.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place in ungreased 9 inch pie pan.
Press firmly over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Seal perforations.
In small bowl, combine egg and cheese.
Spread over bottom of crust.
Spoon hot meat mixture over cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 20-25 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: pineapple carrot jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix Jell-O, hot water and pineapple juice. Set until chilled.
Add carrots, pineapple and olives.
Serve with thin layer of Miracle Whip.

title: fruit salad
directions: Boil water and sugar for 3 minutes; cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Freeze.
Thaw 2 to 2 1/2 hours before serving.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cut chicken into cubes and cook until done.
Combine chicken with soups and Rotel tomatoes and bring to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes and then remove from heat.
Cover the bottom of a 13 X 9 inch pan with crushed tortilla chips.
Spread 1/2 of cheese over chips and pour chicken mixture over cheese and chips.
Top chicken mixture with more crushed tortilla chips and remainder of cheese. Bake at 350 degrees until cheese on top of casserole melts.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar together; spread in a glass dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes - no longer!

title: rhubarb delight
directions: Blend flour, oleo and powdered sugar.
Pack in bottom of an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Beat eggs; add sugar, flour and rhubarb.
Pour over warm crust.
Bake 35 more minutes at 350°.

title: southern pralines
directions: Combine milks and sugar in a large heavy saucepan.
Stir until melted.
Add pecans and let the mixture come to a boil.
Boil for 20 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add salt, butter and vanilla. Remove from heat and beat a few more strokes.
Spoon onto waxed paper and let cool.
This recipe can be halved.
(Make on a day when the humidity is high.)

title: pear salad
directions: Put cream cheese and boiling water in blender, add 1 package jello (any flavor). Blend and dump in bowl.
Put 1 large can fruit in blender.
Add to mixture in bowl and stir.
Stir in 1 container Cool Whip, thawed.
Stir while cooling in refrigerator.
Top with walnuts.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter and mix with corn.
Beat eggs and fold into corn. Add milk.
Mix sugar and flour.
Add to other ingredients.
Mix well and bake at 350° for 35 minutes (longer if needed).

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine pineapple and apple juices in a punch bowl.
Pour undrained strawberries into blender.
Whip until smooth.
Stir into pineapple juice mixture, pour in ginger ale.
Garnish with strawberry slices, lime slices and fresh mint, if desired.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: polynesian meatballs
directions: Combine beef, soy sauce, ginger, salt and pepper.
Drain pineapple (reserve liquid).
Mix 1/2 cup pineapple into meat; form into 1/2 inch balls.
Brown thoroughly in hot skillet.
Lower heat.
Add remaining pineapple and syrup, onion and pepper. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix flour and salt together.
Cut in shortening using a pastry blender; sprinkle with water.
Mix with fork until dough can be gathered together with hand.
Press into a ball; divide into 2 parts; roll out on floured board.
Line pie pan with one crust and add filling, covering with remaining crust.

title: chocolate pretzels
directions: Dip pretzels into chocolate.
The chocolate clears holes best if fork is under the pretzel rather than going through the pretzel holes.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Dip onion rings in this mixture and fry in deep, hot fat until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with additional salt if desired.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cream the shortening, sugars and vanilla. Beat in eggs until mixture is fluffy.
Blend in flour, coconut, oats and orange bits.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet about 1 inch apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit well.
Mix all ingredients.
Prepare the night before.
Cover and refrigerate in serving bowl for at least 12 hours.

title: corn muffins
directions: Mix together.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Makes 15.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Melt chocolate chips in a double boiler.
When melted, add 1 egg yolk at time, beating after each yolk is added.
Cool.
Add 4 or 5 tablespoons of water.
Mix whipped cream.
Beat 4 egg whites together.
Add vanilla and powdered sugar.
Fold in chocolate and egg mixture and pecans.
Break angel food cake into chunks about the size of eggs.
Pour chocolate mixture over cake and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Serve with whipped cream and cherries.

title: cheese eggs
directions: In a medium bowl, beat the eggs and milk together.
In a greased pan, scramble the eggs over low heat.
As they begin to cook, add the cheese and stir constantly until the cheese is melted throughout the eggs.
Set the stove setting to low and add the bacon bits.
Serve with toast and jelly or fresh fruit.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugars, eggs, flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Chill dough a few minutes for easier handling.
Take ball of dough, roll in granulated sugar and put on cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 8 minutes.
Put chocolate stars on and bake 2 more minutes, or until done.

title: creole cabbage
directions: Saute until cabbage is tender and all ingredients combine.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Make brownies according to package directions and cool. Poke holes
in
top and pour Kahlua over it.
Crumble brownies with a fork.
Put
half into a large, pretty bowl.
Layer over brownies half
the
mousse, half the Cool Whip, half the Heath bars and half
the pecans.
Repeat the layers.
Chill.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.
My family likes this dessert frozen.

title: goulash
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain and set aside.

title: chicken tetrazzini 2
directions: Mix all while noodles are boiling.
Add cooked noodles (I cook my noodles in the chicken broth).
Put the mixture into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 40 minutes, then take out of oven and cover with grated sharp Cheddar cheese.
Place back in oven until cheese melts.

title: garlic bologna(almost like a summer sausage)
directions: *Morton Tender Quick salt may be purchased in canning section of grocery store.

title: pace six layer dip
directions: Mash avocados in a bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper. Then combine sour cream and mayonnaise in another bowl.
To assemble:
Spread bean dip in an oblong dish; top with avocado mixture and layer with sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle with onions, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with cheese.
Top with Pace picante sauce.
Serve with chips.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: *For variety, I sometimes use approximately 1/3 cup peanut butter instead of nuts.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix first
ingredients together and pour into casserole dish.
Bake in
a
425° oven until brown or bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° until brown.
Top with grated cheese.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Beat brown sugar and Karo syrup together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add butter, vanilla and salt.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: whole wheat cranberry bran bread
directions: Combine flours, bran cereal, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda and nuts; mix well.
Combine cranberries and granulated sugar.
Stir sugared cranberries, egg, milk, orange juice and margarine into flour mixture all at once, but only until mixed.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake in oven for 60 to 70 minutes, or until firm in center.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove to rack and cool on long side before slicing.
Freezes well.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat well the eggs and sugar; set aside.
Beat well whipping cream and add salt.
Combine egg mixture with cream.
If too thick, add some milk.
Add rum flavoring.
Chill.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix butter, sugar and cinnamon with fork until blended. Add flour and oatmeal. Place apples in buttered 8 x 8 pan. Sprinkle topping over apples. Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour or until apples bubble. Allow to cool or serve warm with ice cream.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend eggs, buttermilk, sugar and shortening together. Blend dry ingredients together.
Mix all together and blend well.
Add raisins and caraway seed.
Put in greased floured loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.

title: creamed sweet potatoes
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Add milk and cook until smooth and thick, stirring constantly.
Add seasoning. Add cubed sweet potatoes and reheat.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, condensed milk, lemon juice and vanilla until smooth.
Pour into pie crust and chill 3 hours.
Top with cherries and serve.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream oil, oleo, powdered sugar and granulated sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt, soda, cream of tartar. Mix and put in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Make into small balls. Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: italian beef
directions: Baked rolled roast.
Slice thin.
Add bouillon cubes and water to roast drippings. Add remaining ingredients.
Add sliced beef and simmer.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Combine rice, mushroom soup, celery soup, water and milk. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with chicken pieces. Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Dot with butter.
Cover with foil and cook at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes, until chicken is done.

title: lois' bean relish
directions: Rinse and drain beans for at least 2 hours.
Mix relish, horseradish and garlic in a large bowl, after pressing garlic; add the pieces that are left in the press.
Add beans and mayonnaise to mix.
Mix all and refrigerate in small containers.
Take them out as you need them as the longer it is out of the fridge the colder the horseradish gets.
Serve with saltines.
Enjoy!!!

title: cholesterol free hot rolls
directions: Heat milk until warm enough to add yeast.
Combine all other ingredients except flour.
Then start adding flour a little at a time until it is desired consistency, which is not sticky.
Cover and let rise until double.
Punch down and make into rolls.
Let this double and bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until hollow when tapped one time.
Sometimes I mix the yeast with rather warm water and then add to milk mixture.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Chop onion and green pepper by hand.
Combine everything and chill in refrigerator.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Preheat skillet to 325°.
Add butter and melt.
Stir in flour very slowly to combine.
Add stock slowly and bring to boiling point.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Add cream, chicken, mushrooms and pimento and stir until hot.

title: sugar cream cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 2 eggs; pat into bottom of a 9 x 13 inch greased pan. Mix remaining ingredients and put on top of first mixture. Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes. Cool at room temperature, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except candy.
Mix well.
Shape into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and while hot, top each with a candy Kiss pressed down firmly.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream butter and cheese together.
Add sugar in small amounts. Blend until smooth.
Add juice and mix well.
Makes a lot!

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix well first 4 ingredients.
Add whipped topping.
Pour in graham cracker pie crust.
Chill.
Top with chocolate curls.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add taco seasoning and beans. Heat thoroughly.
Chop lettuce, onion and cheese.
Pour cooled meat mixture into lettuce and toss.
Serve with tortilla chips, dressing of your choice, picante sauce and sour cream.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into 2-quart casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: mushroom-bacon burgers
directions: Combine ground beef, mushrooms, bacon, onions, Worcestershire and salt; mix thoroughly.
Shape into 4 patties.
Broil for 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn; broil 8 to 10 minutes more, or to desired doneness.
Serve on split, toasted buns with additional green onions, if desired.
Makes 4 large servings.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine sea legs, crumbs, onions and parsley in bowl.
Stir in milk and egg, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
Mix well. Shape into about 8 patties.
Add more bread crumbs if it is too moist.
Fry in oleo in large skillet.
Cook 2 minutes on each side, until brown.

title: fruit-nut whiz
directions: Pour orange or apple juice into blender, then add remaining ingredients.
Yield: Serves 6.

title: old fashioned meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Tear bread into crumbs.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add chuck and mix lightly.
Add crumbs, onion and pepper.
Mix lightly to keep juicy.
Add milk, salt, mustard, pepper, 1/4 cup catsup and Worcestershire.
Mix lightly.
Put into shallow baking pan.
Make 2 grooves on top of loaf and fill with remaining catsup.
Bake 50 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix cake mix, apricot juice and oil. Add eggs and sugar.
Mix well. Bake in tube or Bundt pan for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: russian corn bread
directions: In 14 x 10 x 2-inch baking pan, melt margarine.
Combine all of the other ingredients except eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Pour in melted margarine.
Stir well and pour mixture into baking pan.
Bake at 400° for approximately 35 minutes.
Serve.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Beat eggs and gradually add dry ingredients until thick.
Add milk, half and half and vanilla. Chill in gallon freezer container until ready to churn.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in water until tender.
Drain; cook remaining ingredients until well blended.
Stir in cooked carrots and cover with lid and cook 7 to 8 minutes.
Stir once.
Let stand 3 minutes before serving.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: In a large heavy pan, brown beef and cook sausage and onion with garlic and Italian seasoning until done.
Stir to separate meat.
Stir in soup, water, vinegar and salt.
Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add spaghetti.
Transfer to two 2 1/2-quart shallow baking dishes (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Stir.
Top with cheese.
Makes about 15 cups.

title: ice box cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out 1/4 inch thick.
Cover with oleo, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll and cut 1 inch thick. Let rise.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.
Dribble powdered sugar icing over when cool.

title: cherry and pineapple jello
directions: Mix all together.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate a few hours.

title: veggie bites
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in soup mix, broccoli and cheese until well blended.
Refrigerate 20 minutes.

title: chicken patties
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill well.
Shape into patties and dip in flour.
Then into milk, seasoned with a little lemon juice and then into cracker crumbs.
Deep-fry and drain well.
May be made ahead and frozen.

title: pie crust
directions: Make a ball when you mix.
Put in pie pan and shape with fingers.
Cook until lightly brown.

title: chicken souffle
directions: Cut crust from all of bread. Save 8 slices for top.
Crumble other 2 slices and crust as for dressing.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix other ingredients, except soup and cheese, and spread on top of crumbs. Cover with 8 bread slices.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, put soup and cheese over top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chimpanzee stew(from liberia, west africa)
directions: Burn hair off chimpanzee, slit stomach and remove heart, liver, kidneys and intestines.
Save.
Save hands and feet for garnish, lightly roasted.
Cut up chimpanzee, place in pot after palm oil is very hot and brown meat well.
Add tomato sauce, hot peppers, salt and pepper.
After sauteing well, add enough water to cover ingredients and add bitter balls and okra, chopped up. Let come to a boil and simmer 4 hours.

title: new peanut butter crispy treats
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a large saucepan, over low heat, stir together first 3 ingredients.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add cereal; toss to coat well.
Press into pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Yields 32 (2-inch) squares.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Chop cabbage as desired.
Cut onions into thin rings.
Toss together and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients and boil for 1 minute.
Pour dressing over cabbage and onion.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 12 hours, stirring 2 or 3 times.
This will keep 3 weeks in glass container in refrigerator.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: gnocci
directions: Squeeze spinach dry.
Mix all ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Roll balls in flour.
Drop into boiling water.
Cook until they surface.
Serve with spaghetti sauce.
Serves 6.

title: cheddar-onion bundt
directions: Thaw dough according to directions.
Slice each loaf into 12 equal pieces.
Punch hole in each piece of dough and fill with cheese.
Close hole.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon; drain and put aside.
Fry hamburger; drain.
Put all ingredients together; mix well.
Pour into casserole or ovenproof bowl.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: microwave pecan pralines
directions: Mix sugar and milk well with wooden spoon in 2-quart microwave bowl.
Microwave for 6 minutes; stir well.
Microwave another 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from microwave, add butter and beat with spoon for 3 minutes.
Add vanilla and pecans.
When candy loses gloss, drop by spoonfuls onto foil.
Wrap in plastic wrap when cool.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream oleo and vanilla; add sugar gradually.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to mixture gradually.
Can be doubled.
Chill overnight for best results. Roll out 1/4 to 1/3-inch thick.
Use cookie cutters.
May sprinkle with colored sugar for holidays.
Bake at 350° (electric oven) 6 to 8 minutes; 375° (gas oven) 6 to 8 minutes.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Mix applesauce, sugar, oil, eggs and milk. Add the rest of the ingredients (flour, soda, baking powder, salt, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and 1/2 cup nuts). Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. On top, sprinkle 1/4 cup chopped nuts, brown sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: waffles
directions: This recipe makes four and a half full sections.
And it's a good basic recipe to keep on hand.
Just keep dry ingredients ready-mixed and add eggs, milk and oil when you're ready to prepare waffles.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Cook head of cauliflower in salted water until tender (20 minutes).
Reserve 6 to 8 flowerets.
Mash the rest and add to hot stock.
Thicken with flour and butter.
Simmer a few minutes.
Beat egg yolks with cream.
Add a little at a time, stirring constantly. Season to taste.
Add whole flowerets and mushrooms.

title: special "k" bars
directions: Cook sugar and syrup until clear, then add peanut butter and cereal.
Spread mixture in buttered pan, then melt together chocolate and butterscotch chips.
Spread melted chips on top. Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: golden apricot pie
directions: Cook apricots in water; drain and reserve juice.
Dissolve Jell-O in warm apricot juice and water.
Add salt and pour over apricots; chill.
When slightly thickened, turn into cold pie shell.
Chill until firm.
Top with whipped cream.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook the peas and lima beans separately and drain.
Mix these with the remaining ingredients and put in an 8 x 8-inch casserole. Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion in oil until soft.
Add sausage and cut in small pieces.
When done, add chopped beef and brown.
Put in a pot and add all other ingredients.
Simmer about 1 hour, stirring several times to break up tomatoes and to keep from sticking.
More tomato sauce can be added or water.
Freeze unused sauce for future use.

title: brother's jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all but last 2 ingredients.
Add corn bread mix and milk or buttermilk.
Bake at 400°.

title: mincemeat
directions: Mix and seal in jars.
Keeps in refrigerator a couple months.

title: egg nog
directions: Separate the egg. Beat the yolk. Add sugar as you mix. Add flavoring. Beat in egg white.
Whip the cream and top mixture. Dust with nutmeg.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots and chop in food processor.
Combine with other ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart greased casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken breast
directions: Place 1 slice of cheese over each chicken breast.
Cover with sliced mushrooms (can use canned mushrooms).
Spread soup over all and cover with crushed stuffing mix.
Drizzle butter over all. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pretzels
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a bowl.
Put pretzels in a large roaster.
Pour mixture over pretzels.
Stir gently until pretzels are all coated.
Bake at 200° for 2 hours.
Stir gently every 20 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Fry the hamburger and season with the onion, salt and pepper. Soak the bread crumbs in the milk.
Combine all ingredients and simmer about 1/2 hour or so.

title: cheese pecan crisps
directions: Grate the cheese.
Cream butter and cheese and add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until able to roll into round rolls the size of fifty-cent piece.
Put rolls in freezer.
May freeze indefinitely.
Take out of freezer and wait 10 minutes before slicing into thin rounds.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: crescents
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add flour, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Roll in crescent shapes. Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: great-grandma's banana bread
directions: Cream shortening
and add sugar.
Beat eggs until light and add.
Press bananas or
mash
and add.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together
and
mix
quickly into mixture.
Add lemon juice and nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan on 425° for 45 minutes to 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: cornflake baked chicken
directions: Dip chicken into melted butter. Roll in mixture of cornflakes, black pepper and garlic salt. Place pieces in 13 x 9 glass pan. Sprinkle with remaining butter and crumbs. Bake at 375° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: killer dip
directions: Cube cheese in 1-inch cubes.
Strain juice from Ro-Tel. Combine cheese and Ro-Tel.
Microwave to melt cheese (90% to 95%). Stir with a fork.
Serve with chips, hot or cold.

title: springerle cookies
directions: Beat egg yolks until light.
Mix in 1 cup sugar.
Beat egg whites stiff and add cup of sugar.
Put together and beat in rest of sugar.
Beat 15 to 30 minutes or longer until bubbles rise (or triple volume) and mixture is creamy and thick.
Add sifted flour, salt and baking powder.
Dough will be stiff.
Let dough rest or chill (about 45 minutes to 1 hour).
Divide dough in fourths. Knead into ball, roll and print (about 1/4-inch thick).
Place on greased cookie sheet, sprinkled with anise seed, 1 inch apart.
Let stand overnight.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: hello dolly's
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 12-inch jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over melted butter, covering entire bottom.
Add Angel Flake coconut over crumbs.
Add butterscotch bits over the coconut.
Add 1 cup fine chopped nuts over the bits.
Dribble condensed milk over the entire mixture until completely covered. Bake in a 350° oven 20 minutes to 1/2 hour.
When done, sprinkle top with 1/2 cup of nuts.
Cut while warm in squares or diamond shape.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake white cake according to directions on package.
Mix and soften 1/2 cup milk and cream cheese.
Mix instant pudding and 1 1/2 cups milk.
Combine.
Spread on cake.
Sprinkle on nuts.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in bottom of pan that has been sprayed with Pam. Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour in bowl on top of butter.
Don't stir.
Put peaches in and then pour juice on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ranch potato salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, thoroughly combine all ingredients except potatoes.
Toss with warm potatoes, cover and chill. Makes about 10 side dish servings.

title: cream cheese fruit squares
directions: Melt margarine and mix first four ingredients.
Press mixture evenly over the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In a large bowl beat cream cheese with electric mixer until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until well blended. Spoon cherry filling over crust.
Carefully pour cream cheese mixture over cherries.
Bake at 325° just until set, 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
Chill until cold.
Cut into 24 squares.

title: rocky road
directions: Partially melt chocolate bars over hot water; remove from heat and beat smooth.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Spread in buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill; cut when firm.

title: apple muffins
directions: In a large bowl combine the flours, sugar, baking power and cinnamon.
In a medium bowl, beat together egg, milk and oil. Pour the liquid ingredients into the dry ingredients and combine until just mixed.
Fold in apples.
Spoon into greased muffin tins and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen (1 1/2-inch) muffins or twelve (2 1/2-inch) muffins.

title: shrimp sauce
directions: Put 1 bottle of chilli sauce in the blender. Sprinkle shallots and parsley over top and blend until they are minced. Add the two remaining bottles of chilli sauce, lemon juice, horseradish and garlic salt to taste.
Yields approximately 1 quart.

title: blackberry delight
directions: Mix all fruit in bowl.
Chill for 2 hours.
Sprinkle with sugar over fruit before serving.

title: meat dip
directions: Brown ground meat and onion together.
Drain fat, then add Ro-Tel tomatoes, soup and refried beans.
Put in a casserole dish and bake at 200° for 2 hours.
Top with green onions, olives and cheese.
Serve in a chafing dish with dip size corn chips or favorite kind of chip.
This is also a good main dish.

title: welcome punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, combine concentrates and apple juice. Add ginger ale.
Spoon in 1 pint sherbet.
Keep adding sherbet as it melts.
Makes 14 cups.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients together in mixing bowl and put in microwave to blend together for 1 1/2 minutes. Pour mixture over chicken wings and bake at 350° for 2 hours or until wings are very brown.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add shortening, eggs and milk. Mix well.
Add chopped rhubarb and mix slightly.
Dough will be fairly stiff.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lee's hard candy
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients together over medium heat until sugar dissolves and it begins boiling. Leave on stove eye and don't stir anymore. Cook until mixture reaches 310° on candy thermometer (about 45 minutes). Remove from heat and let it settle. Stir in choice of food color; mix well to avoid streaks. Stir in flavoring (Lee uses about half the bottle, probably about 2 tablespoons). Mix well under a vent or fan. Fumes are very strong. Sift powdered sugar onto a 4-sided cookie sheet. Pour mixture over it and let cool completely. Use handle of knife to break it up.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in boiling water per directions on grit package. Add butter and cheese. Stir until
melted. Add eggs, beaten with milk. Stir until blended.
Pour into greased casserole. Bake 40 to 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: cheese and cherry dessert
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Spoon pie filling over top. Chill.
(Better made the day before serving.)

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix together Jell-O, pudding mixes and hot water and cook until mixture thickens.
Cool 30 to 40 minutes.
Add Cool Whip and blend well.
Fold in oranges.
Chill overnight.
(Can substitute Jell-O flavors and fruits:
peach Jell-O/peaches or strawberry Jell-O/strawberries.)

title: helen's cookies
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Combine ingredients.
Pour into a 9-inch well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 45 minutes before cutting.
Do not overbake.

title: bread dip
directions: Use a round loaf of bread, Hawaiian, rye or pumpernickel.
Take out middle of bread.
Chunk and use for dipping.
Mix dip; put in hollowed out bread.

title: german chocolate brownies
directions: Grease	9
x
13-inch
baking dish.
Spread coconut and pecans in
bottom
of
dish.
Mix
German
chocolate cake mix according to directions on box.
Spread over nuts and coconut. Mix cream cheese, butter and confectioners sugar.
Spread over cake mix. Let stand 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and dried beef
directions: Line casserole dish with dried beef.
Roll bacon around each piece of chicken.
Secure with toothpick.
Do not season.
Combine mushroom soup with sour cream.
Place chicken in casserole dish and pour the mixture over it.
Let stand overnight.
Bake at 250° for 2
1/2 hours.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Pour blackberries into pot with 1/2 cup of sugar.
Heat over medium heat until boiling.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
If necessary to thicken, cook with a little more sugar. Do not make it too sweet.

title: apple-cinnamon crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread pie filling across rectangular pan.
Squeeze the juice of 1 lemon over pie filling.
Sprinkle muffin mix on top and dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 to 45 minutes until golden on top.
Great served with ice cream.

title: easy stir and roll pie crust
directions: Stir until mixed.
Roll between waxed paper.
Place in 8-inch pie pan after removing paper.
Flute edges.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: apple squares
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and shortening as for pie crust.
Add water and egg.
Chill.
While dough is chilling, peel and slice 2 pounds of apples.
Roll out 2/3 of dough to fit a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Add apples, along with the sugar, cinnamon and tapioca.
Roll out remaining dough to fit pan.
Cover filling with top crust, but do not seal edges.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Ice with powdered sugar icing while still warm.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Prepare brownie mix and bake according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Punch holes in top of warm brownies and drizzle with Kahlua.
Let cool and crumble.
Prepare pudding according to directions, omitting chilling.
Place 1/3 of the crumbled brownies in bottom of 3-quart trifle dish. Top with 1/3 each of pudding, Cool Whip and crushed candy.
Repeat layers twice, ending with crushed candy.
Chill 8 hours.
Makes 16 to 18 servings.

title: noodle broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add chicken broth, noodles and pepper to onion.
Bring to boil and boil for three minutes.
Add broccoli and garlic powder.
Cook for 4 minutes.
Add milk and soup. Stir.
Sprinkle cheese on top and let melt.

title: tang salad
directions: To pineapple juice, add pudding and drink mix. Mix all ingredients together.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine jello with boiling water.
Add bananas, strawberries, juice, pineapple and nuts.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix lemon cake mix with the lemon Jell-O.
Make a hole in the middle and add salad oil, cold water and eggs.
Beat 5 to 10 minutes.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Take out of oven and while hot, pierce with meat fork all over.
Spoon on sauce.

title: sugar-free fudge
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add chocolate and stir just until melted.
Remove from heat; stir in sweetener and vanilla. Combine chocolate mixture and cream cheese; beat until smooth. Stir in nuts and spread mixture in lightly greased 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 64 squares of fudge.

title: steak and vegetable salad
directions: Grill steak over medium heat to desired degree of doneness. Slice steak diagonally across grain into scant 1/4-inch slices. Combine veggies and meat.
Pour dressing over and toss.

title: roquefort dressing(blue cheese)
directions: Crumble cheese; mix all ingredients.
Stores well.

title: orange spice cake(special at christmastime)
directions: Chop nuts, fruits and orange slices.
Cream butter and sugar well.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk. Add to creamed mixture.
Mix flour and chopped ingredients.
Add to batter.
Mix with hands.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in 250° oven for 2 or 3 hours.

title: new year's day soup
directions: Mash peas from one can.
Combine all ingredients in large stew pot and cook on low heat for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot with sour dough bread anytime, but for "good luck" on New Year's Day. Makes 6 servings.

title: corn chowder
directions: Melt butter in a pot; add onion and scallions.
Saute over medium heat for about 2 minutes.
Add the milk, salt and pepper and bring to a boil.
When soup reaches boiling point, add corn and stir.
Remove from heat and cover to steep 2 to 3 minutes.

title: the ultimate cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease inside of 9-inch spring-form pan. Remove side.
Make crust:
In medium bowl combine flour, sugar, lemon peel and vanilla.
Make well in center; with fork blend in yolk and butter.
Mix with fingertips until smooth.
On bottom of pan, form half of dough into ball.
Roll pastry to edge of pan. Bake 6 to 8 minutes, or until golden brown.
Meanwhile, roll rest of dough into 3 strips 2 1/4-inches wide and 9-inches long. Assemble spring-form pan.
Line inside of pan with pastry strips, overlapping ends.
Preheat oven to 450°.

title: mints
directions: Stir about 1/2 sifted powdered (confectioners) sugar into a bowl.
Combine hot water with corn syrup and mix well.
Add egg white and flavoring.
Knead in sufficient sugar to make fondant type nature that won't stick to your hands while you are kneading it.
Will use most of sugar (but depends on egg size used).
Divide fondant and knead in food coloring.
Roll about 1/4-inch thick. Cut into small circles and dust with more powdered sugar.
Press into molds or shape but remove from molds immediately.
Pack in containers, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Close tightly and let ripen about 10 days.
This also makes delicious bonbons.
Use vanilla instead of mint flavors.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix together sugar, oil and eggs.
Dissolve in separate bowl: cocoa in hot water, then add cold water and set aside.
Mix flour, salt, soda and powder with sugar mixture.
Add cocoa mixture, then slowly add vanilla.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Rip apart cake or slice cake and cover 9 x 13-inch pan with pieces.
Mix together pudding and milk.
Add ice cream and mix. Pour over cake.
Mix jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add strawberries, juice and all.
(If using whole, frozen berries, slice in half.)
Pour over pudding mixture.
Set in refrigerator until jello mixture jells.
Before serving, top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Top with fresh strawberries.
Serves 12.
Very pretty, very good!

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Spread pecans on bottom of pie shell.
Combine all remaining ingredients; pour over pecans and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until firm.

title: delicious crab meat dip
directions: Melt cream cheese in top of double boiler.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour into chafing dish and serve warm with assorted crackers or chips.

title: laura's chicken
directions: Flour chicken and fry in olive oil until brown.
Add garlic, vinegar, broth, thyme and bay leaf.
Cook over moderate heat for 15 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Add butter and saute mushrooms for 5 minutes.
Pour over chicken and serve.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix all ingredients; bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: velveeta cheese spread vegetable bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook broccoli as directed on package except just until heated through.
Drain.
Mix broccoli and Velveeta process cheese spread.
Spoon into greased 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Dot with margarine.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cranberry crumb cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine brown sugar, flour and cinnamon in small bowl.
Combine cake mix, pudding mix, sour cream, oil and eggs in large bowl.
Blend for 4 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Dice cranberry sauce and sprinkle evenly on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Carefully remove partially baked cake from oven and sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Remove from pan and turn crumb side up.

title: praline biscuits
directions: Preheat
oven to 450°.	Place butter, sugar and nuts in each of 12 muffin cups (2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch).
Sprinkle cinnamon	in each
cup.	Heat in oven until melted.
Mix Bisquick, applesauce and milk until dough forms.
Spoon onto mixture in muffin
tin. Bake
minutes
Invert on heatproof serving plate.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix pudding with pineapple.
Fold in nuts and Cool Whip.

title: herb dip
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth. Serve over cooked vegetables or as dip.

title: banana bran muffins
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until fluffy. Add bananas, milk, vanilla and eggs; blend well. Stir in flour, bran, baking powder and salt. Blend until moistened. Stir in walnuts.
Stir into 12 greased muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from cups.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, onion, celery, pepper, mayonnaise, broth and seasonings.
Place 5 slices of cubed bread in bottom of 3-quart casserole; spread chicken mixture over.

title: oven baked chicken fingers(low-fat)
directions: Mix milk and egg whites.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Dip chicken in milk-egg mixture, then in the crumb mixture.
Line baking sheet with foil; coat foil with cooking spray.
Place chicken tenders on baking sheet and bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Serve with honey or hot mustard.

title: baby back ribs with mustard sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on the ribs, then place them in a large baking pan and bake in the oven until tender, about 1 hour.
Drizzle with the Mustard Sauce.

title: potato chip munchies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat butter with electric mixer on medium speed until softened (30 seconds).
Add 1/2 sugar and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Mix on low speed, gradually adding flour and potato chips.
Beat until well mixed.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with a fork that is dipped in sugar.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until golden.
Lift onto cooling rack.
Yields 36 cookies.

title: buttermilk white cake
directions: Mix soda and cream of tartar with flour.
Add egg whites last. Bake in 350° oven.

title: russian raised pancakes(blini)
directions: Heat 1 cup milk to 105 to 115 degrees fahrenheit.
Pour heated milk into large bowl and stir in yeast and 2 cups of flour. Mix until smooth.
Cover the bowl and sit in a warm place for 1 hour or until the batter has doubled in size.
Stir down with a wooden spoon.
Stir in egg yolks, butter, sugar, salt and remaining flour, alternating with remaining milk.
Stir until mixture is almost smooth.
Cover bowl and set aside for 45 minutes to an hour or until batter has doubled in size again.
Stir down batter.
Beat egg whites to stiff peaks and gently fold into the batter.
For each pancake, pour 1/3 cup of the mixture onto a lightly greased griddle for frying pan.
Fry over medium heat for about 4 minutes, turning once, or until pancake is golden brown. You can garnish with sour cream by putting 1 Tbsp. sour cream on the pancake and rolling it up.
Yields 24.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients.
Form into ball and chill.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight in 1 quart cold water. Do not drain. Next day add celery, onion, potatoes, parsley and garlic. Simmer for one hour or until beans are tender. Cut meat from bones and add to soup. Season to taste. For potatoes, frozen hash browns work.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Shape dough into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix into soft dough.
Roll into teaspoon size balls.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Add a small amount of milk, if needed to make mixture of consistency to fry.
Fry on medium heat in small amount of oil until brown on both sides.
Serve hot as a vegetable.

title: beatnick cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well. Add remaining ingredients alternately with beets.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: P
ut hamburger, chopped onion and chopped pepper in pan and cook until done.
Add spaghetti sauce and tomato sauce.
Simmer about 30 minutes.

title: coconut and pineapple pie
directions: Put mixture in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground round; add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low to medium heat 30 minutes or so.
Serves 8.
Can be frozen.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Mix all ingredients except the butter.
Place bread slices on rimmed baking sheet. Pour batter slowly over bread slices.
Turn to coat both sides.
Cover with waxed paper or Saran Wrap and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: cinnamon ring pickle
directions: Mix the lime and 2 gallons of water. Add cucumbers. Let stand 24 hours. Drain and wash. Soak 3 hours in ice water. Drain. Simmer 2 hours in the vinegar, alum, red coloring and enough water to cover pickles. Drain. Make syrup.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cover bottom of pot with cooking oil.
Brown (fry until golden) rice.
Add other ingredients and simmer until done.

title: judy's pie crust
directions: Mix well first three ingredients. Beat well the egg, water and vinegar. Add to dry ingredients. Makes 5 balls of dough. Store in refrigerator for up to 5 days. Also freezes well.

title: italian green bean bake
directions: Combine all ingredients except half the Mozzarella cheese. Place in a baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: eleanor's bread and butter pickles
directions: Put salt over cucumbers.
Cover with ice and mix.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain and rinse.
Sliced onion may also be added.
Combine sugar, vinegar, celery seed, mustard seed and turmeric.
Bring to boil and add the well drained cucumbers (and onions if desired). Bring to a boil.
Place pickles in sterilized jar and cover with hot liquid.
Makes about 5 pints.

title: beef pot pie
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Drain vegetables.
Mix all ingredients with 1 can water.
Place ingredients in casserole dish (round).
Put pie crust shell on top.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes until crust is brown.

title: aunt callie's chocolate cake
directions: Cream
together
sugar,
shortening and eggs.
Dissolve cocoa in	hot
water
and
add to creamed mixture.
Mix baking soda and flour together.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk to cream mixture,
a
little at a time.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Add marshmallows to hot mixture.
Stir until softened and partially dissolved.
Add 7-Up. Add pineapple and bananas.
Chill until firm, then spread Cool Whip on top.

title: seven minute icing
directions: Put egg whites, water, sugar and corn syrup in upper part of double boiler.
Beat with electric mixer until thoroughly mixed. Place over rapidly boiling water.
Beat constantly and cook 7 minutes or until frosting stands in peaks.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat until thick enough to spread.
Good on chocolate or white cake.

title: buttered barbecued shrimp
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, melt butter. Stir in onion, catsup, water, Worcestershire sauce, lemon peel, lemon juice, sugar and mustard.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Thread shrimp on skewers.
Place shrimp in a shallow dish.
Pour marinade over shrimp.
Let stand at room temperature 1 hour or refrigerate overnight.
Broil 4 to 5-inches from source of heat about 5 minutes on each side, brushing occasionally with marinade. Serve with hot rice and remaining marinade.

title: tuna pate
directions: Line a 3-cup bowl with clear plastic wrap, set aside.
In medium mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except crackers. Transfer mixture to the prepared bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight ( or at least several hours).
To serve, let stand at room temperature 30 minutes.
Unmold pate onto serving plate. Remove plastic wrap.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: polish sausage & sauerkraut
directions: Brown sausage in skillet in small amount of oil.
Put sauerkraut in small roaster and add sausage & sugar.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1/2 hour.

title: mandarin chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, lemon juice, onion and salt.
Chill well.
Add mayonnaise, grapes, oranges and almonds to chicken mixture.
Toss until well mixed.
Place on lettuce leaves to serve.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook soup macaroni according to directions.
Heat frozen peas and drain off butter.
Dice all vegetables very small and add shrimp and cooked peas.
Mix mayonnaise, sandwich spread and salt together.
Add this to the shrimp/vegetable mixture.
Toss good. This makes a lot!
Fills a 4-quart bowl.
May cut recipe in half. Chill and serve.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place chops in casserole.
Top with soup mix and pour in the salad dressing and water.
Cover and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Boil chicken and onions until tender meat can be removed from bones.
While chicken cools, add beans, potatoes and okra to broth and cook for 45 minutes.
Remove chicken from bones; remove skin and chop chicken into small pieces.
Add to beans along with corn and tomato juice.
(Amount of juice depends upon the amount of chicken broth you have.)
Season and simmer for at least another hour, adding the soup during the last 15 or 20 minutes of cooking time.
Freezes well.

title: spiced date-e-roos
directions: Spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
Pour onto waxed paper.
Add soda, salt and nutmeg to flour.
Stir well to blend. Cream sugar, oleo and eggs thoroughly.
Stir in milk.
Add blended dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Stir in chips, dates and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by slightly rounded tablespoonfuls, about 2-inches apart, onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from baking sheet immediately.
Cool on rack.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.
If using self-rising flour, omit soda and salt.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Place butter, chocolate and milk in top of double boiler over hot water.
Cook until melted.
Add vanilla.
Beat in sugar gradually adding just enough to make mixture smooth and creamy, not crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Press in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and let cool.
Enjoy!
Makes 36.

title: melting moment cookies
directions: In bowl, stir together first three ingredients.
In large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine until smooth.
Beat in flour mixture and vanilla until well blended.
Refrigerate one hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place about 1 1/2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with lightly floured fork.
Bake in 350° oven 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are lightly browned. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.
If desired, place a nut on top of each cookie before baking.

title: fuzzy navel punch
directions: In large punch bowl, combine Peach Schnapps liqueur and orange juice; blend well.
Add ice.
Garnish with peach slices and orange slices.
If desired, make an ice ring using the peach slices and orange slices.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix jellos as directed.
When dissolved, then add other ingredients.
Then pour in a large bowl and chill.
Serve with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: church chili(served at church bazaar for many years.)
directions: Preheat pan.
Add oil.
Lightly brown ground meat.
Add onions, celery, garlic and green pepper.
Continue frying and stirring until onions are golden (about 15 minutes).
Add tomatoes, chili powder, which has been mixed with cold water, salt, sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
When boiling, cover and simmer about 1 hour.
Add beans drained of excess liquid.
Cook, uncovered, until well heated and chili is desired thickness.

title: seven layers salad
directions: Spread on top and serve.

title: hot fudge topping
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, combine sugar, margarine, water and corn syrup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a full boil (5 to 8 minutes).
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Immediately add chocolate chips and beat until smooth. Stir in vanilla. Serve warm over ice cream or cake. Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: corn cakes
directions: Grill corn, turning frequently until marked lightly (about 8 minutes).
When corn is cool, cut kernels from the cob.
In a food processor, combine eggs, 1/2 of the corn, scallions, basil, rosemary, cilantro and red peppers.
Pour into a bowl and add the rest of the grilled corn, cornmeal, salt and pepper.
Fold in the egg whites.
In a large non-stick frying pan heat 1 Tbsp of canola oil over medium heat.
Spoon in corn batter for size of corn cakes desired.

title: easy chow mein
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: chili
directions: Heat oil in large pot.
Add meat; cook until almost brown. Add water.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Add remaining ingredients, except thickening; simmer for 30 minutes.
Mix thickening ingredients; add to chili mixture.
Cook 5 minutes while stirring.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Remove chicken from bones.
Cut meat into small pieces.
Place in the bottom of casserole dish.

title: geronimo's fried squash blossoms
directions: Gather about 1 dozen ears of corn from the garden.
Shuck and silk the corn as soon as possible (corn should be cooked soon after leaving the garden).
Take a sharp knife and cut about halfway down on the kernels of corn.
Then scrape the rest of the corn to get the milk out of it.
Place a skillet on top of the stove and add about 3 tablespoons of bacon grease.
Place the corn in the bacon grease.
Add a small amount of water to cook the corn in.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Stir often so it will not stick to the skillet. Fry for about 20 minutes or until done.

title: apple bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter until crumbs are size of peas.
Stir in egg yolks.
Divide mixture in half.
Press half over bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine apples and remaining sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Arrange over crust.
Crumble remaining dough over apples and brush egg whites over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hozel dressing
directions: Put ingredients in blender or processor.
Mix well and add oil slowly.
Chill and serve over garden salad.

title: harless recipe
directions: Make a small batch of biscuits or use canned biscuits.
Do not bake.
In a baking pan, add soups and cooked ground beef.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 450° or until biscuits are done.

title: spicy sausage and potatoes in a skillet
directions: In 10-inch skillet combine sausage, potatoes, pepper and thyme. Cook over medium to high heat, stirring occasionally until potatoes are browned (10 to 12 minutes).
Reduce heat to low to medium, cover and cook until potatoes are tender (8 to 10 minutes).
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Continue cooking, uncovered, until vegetables are tender (4 to 5 minutes).

title: mammaw's jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs 10 minutes.
Add sugar and water.
Combine baking powder with sifted flour and add.
Bake in greased jelly pan (10 x 14-inch).
When done, cut crust from the edges.
Spread with jelly.
Roll gently from long end.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Put into a dish towel.
Serve anytime.

title: cranberry-sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water and chill until slightly thickened.
Break up cranberry sauce and add to gelatin. Add celery and nuts.
Fold in sour cream.
Chill until firm.

title: orange slush
directions: Heat water and sugar to boil; cool. Mash bananas and add rest of ingredients. Freeze in 1-quart container. Thaw until slush and add ginger ale.

title: wassail
directions: Mix together and warm until orange juice is dissolved and then serve.
Keep warm in slow cooker to serve.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix, 1 egg and oil until crumbly; reserve 1 cup. Pat remaining mixture lightly in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Beat cheese, sugar, lemon juice and 1 egg until light and smooth.
Spread over baked layer cake.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: freezer corn
directions: Put all ingredients in heavy weight pan.
Bring to a boil. Watch carefully to prevent sticking to bottom of pan.
Cool.
Put in freezer containers and freeze.

title: rum bundt cake
directions: Mix well.
Beat 2 minutes.
Put in prepared Bundt cake pan and bake in 325° oven for 60 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
When done, remove from oven and let cool for 30 minutes.
Remove from pan and pour glaze over partially cooled cake.

title: delicious dump cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Use a 9 x 10-inch well buttered cooking dish.

title: chicken divan
directions: Combine the soup, mayo, sour cream and lemon juice.
Mix until smooth.
Place broccoli on the bottom of a buttered casserole dish.
Cover with chicken, then with the sauce.
Sprinkle the top with cheese and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Enjoy.

title: chunky tomato soup
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and cook on High for 6 to 9 minutes, or until heated through.
Serve each 3/4 cup portion with 2 Melba toasts.

title: gingered carrots(low calorie)
directions: Rinse, trim and peel carrots.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices. Steam 15 to 20 minutes, or until barely tender.

title: fruited coleslaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: salsa
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
in a large cooking kettle.
Cook for
1 hour.
Pack
hot into clean jars.	Seal with hot lids. Hot water bath for 15 minutes.

title: babka
directions: Sprinkle yeast and 2 teaspoons of sugar into 1/4 cup warm water; stir.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Combine sugar, flour, salt and lemon rind in a large bowl.
Make well in middle.
Pour eggs, yeast mixture, cream and vanilla into well.
Stir until mixture is well blended.
Gradually beat in softened butter.
Turn dough onto floured surface.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes, adding up to 1 1/2 cups of flour as needed until smooth and elastic.
(Dough will be very soft.) Place in greased bowl, turning once to coat.
Cover with cloth; let rise in war place until doubled.

title: green beans with ketchup and bacon dressing
directions: Mix together onions, ketchup, sugar and water; simmer 5 minutes.
