Add beans and crumbled bacon.
Finish on top of stove or oven.

title: potato-bean soup(lo-fat)
directions: In a large saucepan, mix and cook the celery, carrots and garlic in hot oleo over medium heat for 4 minutes or until tender. Carefully stir in broth, potatoes and dill.
Heat to boiling and reduce heat. Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes until potatoes are tender. With the back of a spoon, lightly mash 1/2 of the potatoes in the broth and add the drained beans.
In a small bowl, mix the yogurt or sour cream, flour, salt and pepper and stir into the potato mixture. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly. Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Freezes well.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, sour cream and oil and pour 1/2 mixture into greased pan.
Sprinkle mixture of brown sugar and cinnamon over the cake mix, then add remaining cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
While cake is baking, mix frosting.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Spray and flour tube pan.
Heat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients and pour into greased pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Take cake out of pan and punch holes in cake.

title: my favorite chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine first 3 ingredients in a small bowl.
Combine the next 4 ingredients in a big bowl; beat until creamy.
Beat in the eggs.
Gradually add the dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups hot water, until dissolved.
Add the cranberry sauce and mash.
Then add the grapes, celery and pineapple.
Refrigerate to make firm and then serve.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and extract.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add alternately with strawberries, then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Line loaf pan with greased wax paper.
Pour in batter and bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 1/4 cup sugar and butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Do not overbake.
Chill.

title: country style pot roast
directions: Coat sides of meat with flour.
Place in Dutch oven and brown with butter or fat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water and pour over meat.
Cover and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables and cook 40 minutes longer.
Remove meat and vegetables to warm platter.
Add water, if necessary, to juice in pan.
Thicken for gravy.

title: spaghetti ryan
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Add all ingredients to hot spaghetti; stir vigorously over low heat until egg is cooked and butter is melted.
For garnish, may add chopped parsley, sliced pimentos and sliced ripe olives.

title: rosy peaches
directions: Drain peaches and put the syrupy liquid into a saucepan.
Add the small, hard, red candies.
Heat and stir until candies have dissolved.
Add the peaches and heat through.
Serve warm or cold. Also good made with pears.

title: bourbon steak
directions: Combine all liquid ingredients.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Marinate steak overnight or longer.
Cook on grill until desired preference (rare, medium or well done).

title: louisiana gumbo
directions: Chop the vegetables.
In a large heavy pot, brown the flour in oil until VERY dark, stirring constantly and watching carefully so it does not burn.
(For a fat-free gumbo, you may brown the flour without the oil.)

title: three-milk cake(queque de tres leches)
directions: Mix sweetened condensed milk, whipped cream and evaporated milk together; set aside.
Beat until fluffy 7 egg whites and 3/4 cup sugar.
Add 7 egg yolks and beat.
Add 1 cup sugar, baking powder and cream of tartar.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Immediately when cake is taken from the oven, pour milk mixture slowly and lightly over cake, a little at a time, until all the milk is absorbed.
Ice with seven minute frosting and refrigerate until serving.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in flour and cornmeal.
Add eggs, milk, vanilla, and lemon juice.
Pour into crust with high edges.
Bake at 350° for 55-60 minutes.

title: aunt eva's and aunt irma's shepherds pie
directions: Prepare potatoes as directed. Set aside. Spray rectangular casserole dish with Pam and spread 1 package of dough on bottom and sides of dish. Bake in oven for 25% of baking time listed on tube. Set aside. Brown hamburger; drain grease. Add 3/4 jar of salsa and all of broccoli. Simmer on low for 5 minutes or until broccoli is no longer firm. Layer potatoes on dough in casserole dish; top with 1 1/2 cups of cheese. Add hamburger mixture. Spread second pizza dough over hamburger mixture pressing sides of dish. Bake per dough instructions until light golden brown. Remove from oven; top with remaining cheese and parsley. Return to oven for 2 minutes. Remove and let stand 2 minutes before serving. Serves 6.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Simmer chicken bouillon in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Add seasoning package in Stove Top stuffing. Gently beat egg and add to meat in large bowl. Add stuffing and bouillon mixture.
Mix well and form into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: golden fruit punch
directions: Combine juices and sugar in a punch bowl. Stir until sugar dissolves. Chill.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Mix half the strawberries, water and cornstarch.
Crush all together.
Add lemon juice, sugar, salt and coloring.
Cook, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes.
Cool.
Put rest of berries in pie crust.
Cover with glaze mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: easy sweet rolls
directions: Prepare biscuit dough rolling dough into rectangle, about 1/4 inch thick.
Brush with melted butter.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over dough. Roll dough up (jelly roll fashion) beginning with long side.
Slice dough into 1/2 inch slices. Place rolls into lightly greased 9 inch round cake pan.
Bake 18-20 minutes in preheated 425 degree oven. Drizzle with confectioners sugar icing. Makes 16-18 rolls.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Pour 1/2 of batter in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Melt caramels and milk over low heat to make a sauce.
Pour sauce over cake which has been baked for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour the rest of the batter over this.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients and put in loaf pans.

title: pretzel strawberry dessert
directions: Pack out and press down in a baking dish: crushed pretzels, melted butter and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Bake in oven for 15 minutes at 350°.
Take out and let cool.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown beef and garlic.
Add paste, tomatoes and seasonings. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
In oblong baking dish (11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch) alternate layers of cooked noodles, Swiss cheese, cottage cheese and meat sauce.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together.
Use on steak or chicken, anything you want a barbecue sauce for.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: brunch stuffed french toast
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex.
Place half the cubed, crustless bread in pan.
Place the cubed Philadelphia cream cheese on top. Place remaining bread over cheese.
Beat eggs with syrup, milk and salt.
Pour over all and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.
Serve with sausage, ham or bacon and fresh fruit cup.

title: coke cake with coca-cola frosting
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour and sugar together.
Stir in marshmallows and set aside.
In saucepan, bring to a boil, margarine, cocoa and cola.
Remove from heat and pour over dry mixture.
Stir in buttermilk, baking soda and eggs.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350° for 45
minutes or until done. Frost with Coca-Cola Frosting.

title: mom's tea cakes
directions: Mix. Drop or roll about the size of a walnut and put on cookie sheet lined with foil.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: papa vitos basic red sauce
directions: *Muir Glen organic tomato products are better (if available).

title: chinese spareribs
directions: You may need to double or triple ingredients, depending on amount of spareribs used.
Marinate all ingredients all day.
Bake in a 350° oven open pan for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: broiled dijon grouper
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a small bowl.
Place fillets on rack of a broiler pan coated with cooking spray; brush with margarine.
Broil 5 1/2 inches from heat 8 minutes.
Turn fish; spread mustard mixture evenly over fillets.
Broil an additional 3 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Yield:
6 servings (127 calories and 21% fat per serving).

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Oil and flour 4 small loaf pans.

Cream together oil and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time; mix well. Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with water to creamed mixture. Blend in pumpkin, nuts and raisins. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. You can freeze these; keeps very well.

title: perfect rhubarb pie
directions: Place rhubarb in a colander and pour water over it; set aside.
In a bowl, combine sugar, flour and tapioca; mix well. Drain rhubarb; add to sugar mixture and toss to coat.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Beat egg and water; add to rhubarb mixture and mix well.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with bottom pastry.
Add filling.
Dot with butter.
Cover with remaining pastry; flute edges.
Cut slits in top crust.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 to 50 minutes longer or until crust is golden brown and filling is bubbly.

title: herbed chicken
directions: Mix dressing, wine, garlic, onions and seasonings.
Pour salad dressing mixture over chicken; cover.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Drain.
Place chicken on grill over medium hot coals or on rack of broiler pan.
Grill or broil for 8 to 10 minutes on each side or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked chicken for four
directions: Mix seasoning together and rub chicken with mixture.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.
Remove foil and broil chicken about 2 inches from heat until browned.
Test for doneness.

title: cheerios squares
directions: In 5-quart microwave bowl put butter (margarine), peanut butter and marshmallows.
Cook for 3 1/2 minutes or until melted. Mix in Cheerios.
Spread into pan (buttered); wait for 10 minutes and cut into squares.

title: granola cereal
directions: Mix all ingredients except raisins.
Add 1 cup melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Stir.
Bake 12 more minutes.
Add raisins after baking.

title: breakfast or brunch
directions: Beat eggs; mix with milk.
Add rest of ingredients.
Let set overnight.
Put in a 9 x 13 inch buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let set for a few minutes after taking out of oven before serving.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients into a loaf.
Boil sugar, mustard and vinegar together 5 minutes.
Pour over loaf and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Blend butter and brown sugar; add egg.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder together and add to sugar mixture, then add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lemon pistachio pound cake
directions: Blend first five ingredients in bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in a greased 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until center springs back when touched lightly.
Cool right side up for 20 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: hamburger (turkey) stroganoff
directions: Saute onion, garlic and butter over medium heat.
Add turkey. Brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook with meat for 5 minutes.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Simmer, uncovered 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and parsley.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: quiche
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Crumble well.
Place sausage in bottom of pie shell.
Sprinkle cheese and onion over this.
Beat eggs with soup and pour over mixture in shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: jelly bismarks
directions: Heat milk in a small saucepan, until bubbles form around edge of pan.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, salt and butter, stir to melt.
Cool to lukewarm.
In a large bowl, sprinkle yeast over warm water.
Stir yeast until dissolved.
Add milk mixture, egg yolks and 2 cups flour with electric mixer at medium speed.
Beat until smooth, approximately 2 minutes with a spoon, stir in remaining flour, beating again until smooth.
Dough will be very soft.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 1 hour.

title: turtles
directions: Arrange pecans in clusters on wax paper. Cook 1 can Eagle Brand milk and 1 cup Karo syrup over low heat. Stir and cook until caramel color and thick, 20 to 30 minutes. Drop a spoonful on nuts and place a Hershey square on top mixture. Spread around as it melts, then chill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix with 1/2 of stuffing mix.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Mix stuffing mix with melted butter and the other ingredients together.
Put into greased casserole dish.
Put remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: english orange rounds
directions: Mix and shape into balls about 1/2-inch in diameter.
May be served fresh, chilled or frozen and served later.

title: creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large bowl combine pumpkin, sweetened condensed milk, eggs and spices; mix well and turn into shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and continue baking 35 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean.

title: italian rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add in cooked rice.
Bake in a deep greased pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate clair cake
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk, mixing well. Fold in frozen whipped topping and beat 2 minutes at medium speed with electric mixer. Butter 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Place layer of whole graham crackers in dish. Spread 1/2 of pudding mixture over crackers. Top with second layer of graham crackers. Spread remaining half of pudding mixture over crackers. Top with third layer of graham crackers. Spread with chocolate icing. Refrigerate until ready to serve, overnight or at least 12 hours. Yield: 12 to 15 servings.

title: hot crab cocktail spread
directions: Combine softened cream cheese with milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Drain and flake crabmeat.
Add to creamed mixture.	Add the green onion.
Turn into greased 8-inch pie plate or shallow baking dish.
Top with slivered almonds.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until heated through.
Keep cocktail spread warm and serve with assorted crackers.

title: vegetable strudel
directions: Cut carrot and red pepper into matchstick strips.
Dice onion and mushrooms; coarsely slice escarole.

title: forget-me-nots
directions: Brown beef and pork.
Drain.
Add cheese and seasonings.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Spread on bread and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until bubbles.
May be prepared ahead and frozen before baking.
Great to keep on hand for unexpected company.
Serves 16.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Add boiling water to jello and mix.
Stir until dissolved. Then stir in orange sherbet.
Put in refrigerator until almost set up.
Add Cool Whip and mandarin oranges.
Stir easily until blended.
Sprinkle walnuts over top and put back in refrigerator until set.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Add sugar, egg and margarine.
Blend with wooden spoon.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Fold in nuts and mix again.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: edna clark's cake frosting
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients in saucepan at 240°.
Beat egg whites very stiff.
Pour syrup very slowly into egg whites.
Beat constantly; add vanilla.
Frost cake.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: low carb vegetable soup
directions: Put ham bones with meat in stockpot.

Add tomatoes, water, celery, onion and parsley. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer until ham comes off bone. Remove ham and bone and take ham off bone. Cut up. Put ham in pot. Add mushrooms, cabbage, beans, seasoned salt and pepper to taste. Cook until vegetables are done. Add lemon juice and serve.

title: cabbage goulash
directions: Brown sausage, ground chuck and onion-drain well. Add 5 next ingredients and simmer 5-10 minutes. Add cabbage.
Cover and simmer till cabbage is tender. Serve with pinto beans and corn bread.

title: chinese noodle candy
directions: Melt the butterscotch and chocolate chips in double boiler. Stir in noodles and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper. Let set 1 hour.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Chop onion and mushrooms and brown in small amount of margarine.
Add ground chuck and brown.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt while browning.
Stir in flour after meat is brown. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, liquid from mushrooms, 1/2 cup water, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce and simmer for at least 30 minutes.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine egg and milk. Sift together dry ingredients and add to egg and milk mixture. Fry in hot oil at 375° using a funnel with 5/8-inch opening. Holding finger over funnel bottom, measure 1/4 cup batter at a time. Swirl in a circle as batter runs from funnel into hot oil. When golden brown, remove from oil and drain on paper towels. Sprinkle with a good dusting of powdered sugar.

title: low-fat blueberry-pear dessert
directions: Cut up pears.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, pear juice in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cook 1 minute, stirring while cooking. Add the cut-up pears and 2 cup blueberries.
Pour mixture into an 8 x 8-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Make 6 dollops of batter on top of fruit in pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm or cold. Add a dab of Cool Whip on top of each serving.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta and rinse in cold water.
Add all other ingredients.
Toss and let stand in fridge for awhile.

title: tanuki artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, heat either on stove top or microwave.	Serve with crackers.
Plenty for 6-8 people.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Saute chicken, onion and garlic in margarine until chicken is lightly browned, about five minutes.
Stir in cornstarch and cook 1 minute longer.
Add broth, carrot, lemon juice, peas and salt. Boil 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Serve with lemon wedges. Serves 4.

title: pecan sandies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
Add water and vanilla; mix well.
Gradually add flour.
Fold in pecans.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and flatten with fingers.
Bake at 300° for 10 to 25 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
When cool, dust with confectioners sugar.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and peanut butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add noodles and peanuts to the mixture until well coated.
Form into little clusters on foil or waxed paper and allow to harden.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Combine cake mix, melted margarine and egg, patting into pan as you would a pie crust. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Remove from oven.

title: sugar nuts
directions: Heat nuts on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Cool. Combine sugar, water, cinnamon and salt and cook to soft ball (236°) with stirring. Remove from heat. Add vanilla and nuts. Mix well. Turn out on waxed paper or foil. Separate while cooling.

title: stuffed bread
directions: Roll out bread dough and spread lightly with dressing. Sprinkle each ingredient evenly over dough (use you choice of ingredients).
Roll up dough and fold under 2 ends.
Make sure seam is face down on lightly oiled pan.
Brush bread dough with butter. Score bread at an angle 3 times.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 375°.

title: yum-yums
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls, then roll in coconut.
Makes about 50 to 60.
Keep in covered dish in refrigerator.
Best after 2 days old.

title: tropical trifle
directions: Slice pound cake in 10 slices.
Cut each slice into 6 cubes. Place 1/2 of the pound cake cubes in a deep glass bowl.
Sprinkle with orange juice.
Spoon 1/2 of the strawberries over the cubes. Next, layer 1/2 of the pudding, 1/2 of the pineapple, 1/2 of the bananas and 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Repeat layers.
Refrigerate at least a few hours (can be overnight) before serving to let flavors blend.

title: heavenly hash
directions: To the beaten eggs, add all other ingredients except marshmallows; mix well.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Remove from oven and immediately cover with marshmallows.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Frost.

title: lemonade pie #2
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill in a graham cracker crust. Delicious.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, syrup, margarine, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: easy oven stew
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika in bag.
Drop beef portions in a few at a time.
Shake until coated.
Mix with Wesson oil in 3-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 30 minutes.
Stir once; add vegetables, tomato paste and water.
Bake at 350° for 1 3/4 hours.

title: perfect microwave fudge
directions: Blend powdered sugar and cocoa.
Add milk, butter and marshmallows, but do not stir.
Cook 3 minutes on High in microwave; then stir and add vanilla and nuts.
Stir to blend. Pour into a greased pan or line pan with foil.
Place in freezer 20 minutes or refrigerator 1 hour.

title: sausage and cheese dip
directions: Heat together until well blended.
Serve with tostados or can be used as a meat dish.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Grease a baking pan and cover bottom with cup of uncooked rice. Season chicken breast with salt and place on top of rice.
Mix mushroom soup with 1 can of water and pour over the chicken, making sure it goes into the rice to moisten it, spread onion soup over top.
Sprinkle a few drops of water over soup mix.
Cover pan tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake for 2 hours at 325° or bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate maple nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Stir in 1 beaten egg. Press evenly into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 25 minutes. Meanwhile, in medium bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk, remaining 1 egg and flavoring.
Stir in nuts and sprinkle chips evenly over prepared crust.
Top with nut mixture.
Bake 25 minutes longer or until golden.
Let cool before you cut to serve.

title: martha washingtons
directions: Mix together first 4 items.
Roll in 1 inch balls; chill or freeze.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls and set on waxed paper.

title: steak and potatoes casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cut meat into 6 to 8 serving pieces, trimming fat and bone.
On a wooden board or waxed paper, using a meat mallet or edge of a heavy saucer, pound mixture of flour, salt and pepper into meat.
In a heavy skillet over medium heat, brown meat well on both sides in hot oil.
Don't crowd pieces. Arrange browned meat in a 3-quart casserole.
Place carrots and potato slices on top.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix and pour 3 1/2 cups water over top.
Bake, covered, 2 hours or until tender. Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: tex mex soup
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Saute onion and peppers in butter until soft.
Add ham, chiles, white pepper and cayenne.
Cook 1 more minute.
Set aside.

title: mrs. higgin's lace cookies
directions: Have butter hot but not bubbly.
Pour over oats and brown sugar.
Add flour, egg and vanilla.
Place on cookie sheet, 1 teaspoon each.
Spread apart.
Bake at 350° for about 5 minutes or until they have spread out.
Let cool in pan before removing.
(It works best to spray your cookie sheet with Pam so the cookies come up easier.
They are very fragile and breakable.)

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt Milky Way bars and 1/2 cup butter together.
Cream together 1/2 cup butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs singly.
Stir in alternately with buttermilk, flour and soda.
Beat in melted candy mixture, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool and dust with sifted powdered sugar.

title: citrus pie
directions: Beat frozen lemonade concentrate for 30 seconds.
Gradually spoon in ice cream and blend.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze until mixture mounds.
Spoon into the graham pie crust.
Freeze pie for at least four hours.
Take out 5 minutes before serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in hot water; set aside.
Cream together the sugars, eggs, shortening and peanut butter.
Add flour and water mixture.
Bake in a 37° oven.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix well and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon and remove any skin; put in a mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients (except oil).
Mix well and make into patties, just like hamburgers.
Heat oil in skillet, then fry patties, turning several times until golden brown.
These can have cheese melted on top, if desired.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Sift into mixing bowl flour, sugar, salt and baking powder. Add oil, eggs, orange juice and vanilla.
Beat until smooth, about 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour half the cake mixture into pan, then the berries which have been tossed with the sugar and cinnamon.
Then the rest of the cake mixture again.
Top with any blueberries that are left.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool in pan.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients and pour into a greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fettuccine with scallops and lemon chive cream
directions: Combine half and half, 3 tablespoons lemon juice, chicken bouillon and lemon rind in small heavy saucepan.
Simmer until reduced to 3/4 cup, about 20 minutes. Reduce heat to very low. Whisk in butter, one tablespoon at a time, until incorporated into mixture. Season with salt and pepper. Add chives.
Set aside and keep warm.

title: perfect pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Put in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; toss well.

title: lasagna
directions: Let cheeses come to room temperature.
In a bowl, beat eggs; add cheeses and Italian seasoning.
Mix well.
Cook noodles until soft.
Layer noodles in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add sauce and cheese.
Continue to layer until the pan is almost full.
Top with 1 pound Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: linguine salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Toss with linguine and mushrooms.
Chill.

title: half hour ham pie
directions: Cut ham, pepperoni and Mozzarella cheese into cubes.
Mix all the ingredients into bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased pan, 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes or until done.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: fresh lemonade
directions: Combine sugar and 2 cups of water in saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add to remaining water and lemon juice.
Chill and serve over ice.
Garnish, if desired. Yields 2 1/2 quarts.

title: peanut surprise
directions: Mix sugar and syrup and heat in large boiler just until sugar melts (do not cook).
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add corn flakes.
Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.
Let cool before wrapping up, that is if you have any left to wrap up.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Mix well all ingredients together.

title: mint chocolate cocoa mix
directions: Put mints and 1 cup malted milk in blender to crush mints. Add rest of ingredients and mix well.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush whole package of cookies.
Pack the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with half the cookies; press firmly.

title: bisquick cornbread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, add milk, eggs and melted oleo.
Mix well.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch lightly greased pan.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix altogether and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix flour and sugar. Then add milk.
Mix until all lumps are gone.
Pour in pan with butter.
Add peaches.
Spread around.
Add cinnamon (sprinkled) on top.
Bake at 350° for an hour or until crust has risen and is brown.

title: ranch-style peach pie
directions: Beat egg whites until peaks form.
Add sugar very gradually, beating until stiff.
Fold in crackers, pecans, vanilla and peaches.
Spread over bottom and sides of greased 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Reserve several peach slices for garnish.
Alternate layers of whipped topping and peaches on cooled crust, ending with topping.
Chill until serving time.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together sugar, salt, cornstarch and water.
Cook until thick; add food coloring, lemon juice and strawberries.
Put in baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake Jiffy cake mix as directed.
Bake 10 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Mix 1 box vanilla instant pudding with 2 cups milk and 8 ounces cream cheese.
Let set.
Layer on cake.
Top with cut strawberries mixed with glaze.
Top with 9 ounce Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: mama's sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix together well.
After sprinkling sugar/nut mix over top of potato mix, bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: barbecue bean soup
directions: In a stock pot, cook the onion and garlic in oil over a moderate heat, stirring until soft.
Stir in the chili powder, cumin, allspice and cloves; simmer for a minute.
Add the tomatoes with their juice and everything else, except the vinegar.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer, partially covered, stirring occasionally for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in the vinegar and simmer until heated through.

title: muscadine bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beating in one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk and Muscadine sauce.
Stir in chopped pecans. Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes, until a toothpick inserted in the center tests clean.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients in Ziploc bag. Add chicken wings. Place in icebox 8 hours. Turn occasionally. Drain and broil 10 minutes on each side about 7-inches from broiler or bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into hot oil.
Brown and drain.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and cocoa with a little of the milk. Add yolks of eggs that are well beaten.
Scald remainder of diluted milk.
Pour slowly into egg mixture; cook in double boiler until it thickens.
Cool; add vanilla.
Pour into cooked pie shells.
Cover with stiffly beaten egg whites with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Brown in oven and serve hot.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken and put in large pan.
Drain fruit. Save syrup and refrigerate fruit.
Mix fruit syrup, soy sauce and garlic.
Pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°. Pour liquid from cooked chicken into pan along with sweet and sour sauce.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Simmer about 30 minutes until sauce thickens.
Add fruit.
Pour over chicken.
Bake for another 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Yields 12 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In medium bowl, mix together catsup, bread crumbs and water. Mix with all other ingredients and shape into a loaf. Place into a shallow baking pan. Bake one hour.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix.
Form into balls and brown in 2 tablespoons butter. Remove from heat and keep hot.

title: pecan pie
directions: Whip eggs and melt butter.
Mix all ingredients together, adding nuts last.
Pour into unbaked deep-dish pie crust. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Grease a 1-quart baking dish.
Break bread into cubes.
Toss with cheese in baking dish.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper and pour over bread and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake, covered at 350°
for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: greek pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare the crust.
Let the cheeses come to room temperature while you cook the bacon.
Cream the Feta and Ricotta cheeses together and spread evenly over the crust.
Cover with the sliced onions and tomatoes.
Drizzle the olive oil over the top and bake for about 20 minutes.
Top with freshly ground pepper.
Yields one 12-inch pizza.

title: skillet corn
directions: Melt butter in large skillet. Drain whole kernel corn and add to skillet along with creamed corn. Allow to come to a boil, then turn down and simmer. Cook down to desired consistency. It's good if you let the bottom brown some and scrape it up and stir it.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill before serving.

title: pigs in the blanket casserole
directions: Grease the bottom of a casserole dish.
Cut cabbage.
Brown meat with onion; drain excess fat.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add rice.
Layer 1/2 cabbage, 1/2 meat mixture, 1/2 cabbage and 1/2 meat mixture in dish.
Mix tomato soup with water in separate bowl.
Pour over top of casserole.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and cool; mix with all but 1 cup of crumbs. Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: english picnic pie
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, eggs, Worcestershire sauce, milk and salt in a large bowl.
Set aside.
Line a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan with a pie crust, overlap the rim.
Spoon half of the meat mixture. Top with hard-cooked eggs.
Cover with the remaining meat mixture and pat smooth.
Place pie crust on top of meat, flute (pinch together) top and bottom crust.
Cut out a small circle in the center of the pastry.
Brush with egg yolk mixed with water. Bake at 350°
for 2 hours.
Chill.
Unmold and slice.

title: cherry cobbler bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 11 x 7-inch baking pan.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine squash, onion, salt, pepper, sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add egg and fat or oil.
Drop by spoonful into hot grease. Fry until brown.

title: super salad
directions: Layer lettuce, beans, carrots, pineapple and onion in a flat dish or pan.
Spread mayonnaise over the top and sprinkle with sugar.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Just before serving, sprinkle with bacon on top and toss.
(Bacon bits may be used.)

title: chocolate potato cake
directions: Stir together flour, cocoa, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
In large bowl of mixer, cream shortening and sugar until light.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add potatoes and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in flour.
Mix alternately with milk.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until tests done.
Cool in pan on rack.
Cut in bars, serve with ice cream or whipped cream.
Makes 18 bars.

title: chocolate cookie ice cream pie
directions: Mix crushed cookies with melted butter.
Press into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread ice cream over top of cookies.
Pour fudge topping in even layer over ice cream. Spread Cool Whip over the fudge. Garnish with crushed cookies or chocolate curls.
Put in freezer for 2 hours before serving.

title: cherry chocolate kisses
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine margarine, powdered sugar, cherry juice, almond extract and food coloring; blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off. Stir in flour and salt. Add cherries.
Mix well. Form dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned around edges.
Immediately top each cookie with chocolate kiss. Remove from cookie sheets.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: chicken swiss
directions: Gently flatten chicken breasts between pieces of wax paper with rolling pin or flat side of meat mallet.
Combine egg, water and 1 tablespoon mustard in bowl.
Combine bread crumbs, thyme, salt and pepper on piece of wax paper.
Coat chicken evenly with flour.
Dip chicken in egg mixture; roll in bread crumbs.

title: kraut and wieners
directions: Melt butter or bacon grease in skillet.
Mix potato and kraut well and add to skillet.
Cut wieners in 1-inch pieces and put on top of kraut.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops off peppers; chop and saute with onion and butter. Add ground beef; cook and drain.
Stir in rice and tomato sauce. (Cook whole peppers in boiling water.)
Set cooked peppers in a shallow baking dish with 1/2 cup water.
Fill peppers and bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Add cheese on top and bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.

title: lucille wood's cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve jello and cool a bit.
Mix mayonnaise and cottage cheese. Add to jello. Dice or shred the cucumber and chop the onion fine.
Slice or chop the black olives. Add to mixture.
Let set until firm.

title: spareribs
directions: Mix all (except ribs) and pour over ribs in pan.
Place in oven over
low
heat at 300° to bake 1 hour and 15 minutes. Baste occasionally and turn.
Then broil to brown, turning and basting, for about 10 minutes each side.

title: cucumber dill pasta salad
directions: Slice or cube cucumbers, celery, tomatoes and onions in a bowl. Season with yogurt, sour cream and mayonnaise, according to taste. Salt, pepper and other seasonings to taste.

title: cranberry quick bread
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Combine dry ingredients and add, alternating with the juice, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan.
Serve with Sweet Orange Spread.

title: carrot and vegetable salad
directions: Cover and let set overnight.

title: brunch goodie
directions: On bottom of greased 10 x 6-inch dish, combine croutons and sprinkle cheese on top.
Combine eggs, milk, salt, pepper and diced green pepper.
Pour over croutons.
Fry bacon until crisp and crumble over top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Combine oleo, cream cheese, sugar, milk, pudding and Cool Whip.
Crush Oreo cookies (4 to 10) depending on size of container.
Layer mixture and crushed cookies.
Put a flower in the top or gummy worms.

title: blushed gerardo
directions: Saute rosemary and garlic in oil for 5 minutes.
Add cream and brandy and heat for 10 minutes.
Add cheese.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for 10 minutes.
Serve over penne, ziti or shells.

title: rocky road fudge bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine butter and chocolate in saucepan.
Heat on low until melted.

title: ann landers meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon and tomato sauce.
Place in baking pan with strips of bacon and tomato sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Place all ingredients, except 2/3 cup salad oil, in blender container. Cover and blend at medium speed for 5 seconds. Remove cover insert. Quickly pour 2/3 cup oil in center of egg mixture in a steady stream while blending at medium speed.
Blend until mixture is thick and smooth.
Yields approximately 1 1/4 cups.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Ground hamburger and drain. Add minced onions, ketchup and chili mix. Cook for 5 minutes or until blended. Serve on your favorite brand of hot dog.

title: syrup for pecan rolls
directions: This is Lester's favorite.

title: freezer sweet pickles(very good)
directions: Wash and slice pickles.
Combine with sliced onions.
Add salt and mix well.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Drain water off pickles and onions.
Mix sugar, vinegar and celery seeds.
Pour over pickles and mix.
Put into freezer containers and put into freezer.
Will keep for 4 to 6 months.

title: gingerbread upside-down cake
directions: Melt margarine in 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Stir in brown sugar until dissolved.
Arrange pineapple and cherries in brown sugar mixture.
Prepare gingerbread mix, using package directions.
Pour over pineapple and cherries.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Puree peaches in blender.
Combine with other ingredients. Pour into an ice cream freezer container and freeze until hard.

title: microwave fantasy fudge
directions: Microwave margarine in 4 quart bowl on High until melted.
Add sugar and milk; mix well.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes or until mixture starts boiling.
(Stir after 3 minutes and again after 2 minutes.)
Microwave 5 1/2 minutes (after it starts boiling).
Stir after 3 minutes.
Gradually stir in chocolate until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour into a buttered pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: betty strong's chicken diable
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.	Saute onion, mushrooms and garlic until tender.
Add tomato, salt, pepper, sugar and cayenne.
Heat to boiling.
Add chicken and spaghetti.
Put in 9 x 13 casserole and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/4 cup of the sugar to egg whites.
Cream Crisco plus remaining sugar.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients with milk.
Fold beaten egg whites; add berries.
Sprinkle top with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: creamy ranch pork chops and rice
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add chops and cook until browned.
Add soup, milk and 1/2 package salad dressing mix.
Heat to a boil. Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with Ranch-Style Rice.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix and pat into 9x13 inch pan. Bake at 325 degrees for 30 minutes*.

title: yams and apples
directions: Boil yams until barely tender (whole or cut widthwise in big pieces).
Peel.
Cool.
Slice and alternate yams and peeled apple rings in margarined casserole dish.
Boil together:
sugar, water, margarine, cornstarch and salt until it begins to thicken.
Pour over yams and apples and bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: holiday cherry squares
directions: Gradually add sugar to butter in large mixer bowl, creaming at medium speed of mixer until light and fluffy.
At medium speed, add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
At low speed, add flour and lemon extract.
Pour batter into well-greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Mark off into 20 squares.
Place 1 heaping tablespoon of pie filling in center of each square.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
While warm, sift powdered sugar over cake.
Cut into squares, when cool, with cherry filling in center of each square (marking disappears during baking).

title: salisbury steak
directions: In a bowl, combine beef, egg, onion, cracker crumbs, milk, horseradish, salt and pepper; shape into patties.
Fry in skillet over medium heat for 10 to 12 minutes, or until cooked through, turning once.
Remove patties and keep warm.
Add gravy, mushrooms and water to skillet; heat 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve over mashed potatoes, noodles or rice.

title: crescent chicken chunk roll-ups
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 8 triangles; press each to flatten slightly.
Put about 2 tsp. cheese on shortest side of triangle; top with 1 tsp. barbecue sauce and chicken chunk.
Roll to opposite point, punch edges and seal.
Combine egg and water beating slightly.
Dip edges and sides of crescents in egg mixture; roll in sesame seeds.
Place point side down on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 18 minutes.
Serve with additional barbecue sauce.
Garnish as desired.

title: grilled fish and shrimp
directions: Melt butter; add lemon juice and garlic and simmer 1 minute. Season fish and shrimp lightly with Greek seasoning.
Place fish and shrimp in a large sheet of heavy foil with top loosely opened. Baste heavily with lemon butter and garlic sauce.
Add chopped tomato, onion and green pepper.
Place on an outdoor grill and cook about 5 minutes.
This may be baked in oven with foil closed.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Heat all ingredients in double boiler until melted.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Pour in jars and refrigerate.
Makes 1 quart.

title: microwave quiche
directions: Grease 9-inch pie pan or quiche dish.
Layer meat, cheese and vegetables.
Beat milk, mayonnaise, Bisquick and eggs for 1 minute. Pour into pan. Microwave on inverted plate on Medium-high for 18 to 20 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: pecan butter balls
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Chop pecans in blender.
Combine pecans with flour, butter, granulated sugar, vanilla and salt.
Mix until well blended, then gather in a ball.
With lightly floured hands, shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets for 20 minutes or until browned on bottom.
Cool slightly, then remove from cookie sheets.
Shake a few cookies at a time in a bag with confectioners sugar.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: chicken mandarin
directions: Coat chicken with flour, fry on both sides until brown. Transfer to 9 x 13-inch shallow casserole.
Add chopped onion.
Mix chicken bouillon with apricot; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with parsley and almonds.
Cook, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes, uncover and cook 20 minutes more.
Serve over rice.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook stew beef with a small onion and 1 tablespoon oil; brown and let cool.

title: pizza casserole(triple batch)
directions: Brown and season hamburger; add noodles.
Add cheese soup, pizza sauce and mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and bake another 10 minutes.

title: zero salad dressing
directions: Combine in a jar with lid and shake well.
Good for those on a diet.

title: peachy crumbly cake
directions: Whiz peaches, 2 bananas, orange juice, almond and vanilla in blender.
Layer, using liquid first, then crumbs.
Blend in liquid.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Grind peppers.
Mix with sugar and vinegar.
Cook and bring to a boil.
Cook 2 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes.
Add Certo and green food coloring.
Mix and let stand 10 minutes.
Pour into jars. Seal with wax.

title: delicious peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and shape into balls.
Melt the chocolate chips and paraffin in top of double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate and set on wax paper.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Layer on largest platter possible:

title: carrot and cracker casserole
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water in saucepan until tender. Drain, reserving 2/3 cup cooking liquid.
Mash carrots with reserved liquid.
Add butter, onion and cracker crumbs; stir well. Spoon into 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening, all sugar and egg.
Add well mashed bananas. Mix and pour into a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake 35 minutes or until done when tested.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix and press into pan.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, mix peanut butter, chocolate chips, eggs, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Add flour last.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes and then cool.

title: scotch pie
directions: Mix all ingredients as you would for pie crust.
Divide dough in half; roll out dough and place in cookie sheet.
Put pie filling on top of dough, then cover with remaining pie crust. Poke with fork.
For best results, use smaller size cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: company salad
directions: Cook together until it boils and becomes thick.
Set aside to cool.
When cool, spread pudding mix over jello mixture. Refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute onions and garlic in a little oil.
Add ground beef and pork sausage.
Cook until all red color is gone.
Drain off excess fat.
Mash tomatoes with a spoon or your hands.
Add to meat.
Add salt, pepper, sugar, oregano, Italian seasoning, French's spaghetti sauce mix.
Simmer gently, uncovered, until sauce cooks down to about 1-inch (approximately 2 hours).
In a baking pan, just cover the bottom with sauce, then layer lasagna noodles, sauce, Ricotta or cottage cheese and lots of Mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers as before.
End with sauce, Mozzarella and a little Parmesan.
Bake at 350° about 40 to 50 minutes, until bubbly and slightly brown.
Remove from oven 15 to 25 minutes before serving so it will set before cutting.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add sugar and continue beating until well mixed.
Fold in rest of ingredients.
Bake in well-greased deep pie plate for 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool thoroughly.
This can be made the day before.
If made the same day, ample time must be allowed for proper cooling.

title: shortcut brunswick stew
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over low heat, cook bacon until crisp. Transfer to paper towel to drain, reserving 1 tablespoon drippings in pan.
Crumble bacon and set aside.

title: ribbon salad(dietetic recipe)
directions: Choose 2 colors of sugar-free gelatin (for example, red and green for Christmas).
Dissolve large box of gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Add cold water.
Pour half of this into each of two molds or all in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Let stand until firm. Spread on Pineapple Cheat Cake Layer (recipe follows) and top with layer of second color gelatin (mixed as previously stated).
Serves 15.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except margarine and stuffing mix.
Melt margarine and pour over stuffing mix.

title: the best banana bread
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and margarine.
Blend in banana and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix just until moist.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes one loaf.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Soak limas overnight. Cook, uncovered, until soft. Add salt to taste.
Save 1/2 juice and put in casserole.
Add light brown sugar and ketchup. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add 1 teaspoon liquid smoke.
Add bacon and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: crispy oat cookies
directions: Cream Parkay; gradually add sugar.
Beat well.
Add egg; beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats and remaining ingredients.
Shape dough in 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with fingers.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Serve with assortment of crackers, raw vegetables or pumpernickel bread loaf.

title: curried egg salad
directions: Cover eggs in pan with cold water by 1 inch.
Bring to a boil; turn off heat.
Let sit covered for 15 minutes.
Drain. Rinse under cold water.
Mix eggs, onion, mayonnaise, curry, carrot, salt and pepper.
Divide lettuce, tomato and egg mixture into pitas.

title: old-fashioned baked beans(microwave)
directions: Place beans and water in 3-quart casserole.
Cook, covered, on full power for 10 to 13 minutes or until boiling.
Let stand, covered, for 1 hour.
Add salt, soda and oil to beans.
Cook, covered, on full power for 9 to 12 minutes or until boiling. Continue cooking on Cook Level 3 for 30 to 35 minutes or until tender.
Stir occasionally, during cooking time.
Drain liquid from beans, reserving 1 1/4 cups liquid.

title: celery water chestnut casserole
directions: Cook celery in small amount of water for 8 minutes; drain. Mix celery, water chestnuts, soup and pimento; turn into buttered casserole.
Mix bread crumbs with almonds and melted butter. Sprinkle evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peach praline pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Stir in slowly the peach juice.
Cook until thick.
Add peaches.
Combine flour, brown sugar and nuts and cut in oleo.
Spread 1/3 of mixture in unbaked shell; add peach mixture and cover with remaining pecan mixture. Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Then 20 minutes at 350°.

title: syrup cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat.
Add dry ingredients along with milk.
Add syrup last.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while hot.

title: ratatouille
directions: Coarsely chop tomatoes (about 4 cups).
Set aside.
Heat oil in large saucepan.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes. Add zucchini, eggplant and green pepper.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes. Add 1/2 cup water, seasonings and tomatoes.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, until vegetables are tender, about 15 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine and sugar in large bowl of mixer.
Add eggs.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add and mix well.
Blend in mashed bananas.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 1 large or 2 small loaves.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine ingredients except soda in large skillet.
Bring to boil and cook 10 minutes on medium heat.
Remove from heat and beat in soda.
Pour into buttered pan while still foaming.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: creamy taco dip
directions: Microwave all ingredients in 2-quart microwavable bowl on High 5 minutes or until Velveeta is melted, stirring after 3 minutes. Serve hot or cold with corn chips or tortilla chips. Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all above ingredients.
Top with crumbled crackers.
Dot with margarine. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender.
Pour cold water over spaghetti and drain well.
Add salad dressing, chopped celery, green pepper, onion and cut up tomatoes.
Mix well and let set for a while.

title: hobo sacks
directions: On foil packages, press out 4 hamburger patties.
Add sliced potatoes, onions, carrots, salt and pepper.
Fold up foil and seal.
Cook on grill until tender (about 25 minutes); turn once.

title: almond crescents
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat margarine, sugar and almond extract and vanilla until fluffy.
Add flour and salt; mix until blended. Stir in oats and almonds.
Shape tablespoonfuls into crescents. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 14 to 17 minutes.
Remove to wire rack and dust with powdered sugar.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add the remaining ingredients, beating thoroughly after each ingredient.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: gingered peach sauce
directions: Put peaches in food processor.
Cover and process until smooth, scrape down sides.
Add ginger and liqueur, process until smooth.
Serve over fruit.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix with mixer until creamy; bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Heat pineapple juice and let come to a boil.
Add Jell-O mix and stir until dissolved.
Put this in refrigerator to cool.

title: cheese bread
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl. Stir in water. Add Bisquick mix and beat.
Add mustard and 1 cup cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Turn batter into greased loaf pan. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and dot with butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove and cool on rack before slicing.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pineapple-cheese casserole
directions: Mix together pineapple, sugar and cheese.
Place into casserole dish
Put crushed Ritz crackers on top of pineapple mixture.
Drizzle butter (melted) on top of crackers. Bake in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add zucchini and next 6 ingredients; bring to a boil; reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Spoon soup into bowls.
Garnish with chips and cheese.
Makes 2 1/4 quarts.

title: easy potato bake
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes, then add potatoes and mix. Bake at 350° in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour or until top is brown.
Remove and sprinkle a little cheese on top.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Add flour, salt and spices together.
Cream shortening; add sugar.
Beat until light.
Stir soda in applesauce; add egg. Combine with creamed mixture.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop 2 or 3 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
You can add 1 cup nuts and raisins and/or 1 cup quick cooking rolled oats.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: potato skin appetizers
directions: Cut baked potatoes in half.
Scoop out insides leaving 1/8-inch in shell.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with grated cheese and bacon.
Place in 500° oven until cheese is melted and potato skins are crisp (about 10 to 12 minutes). Combine sour cream with chives and salt and pepper to taste. Serve with potato skins.
Serves 8.

title: garden vegetable pizza(no cook)
directions: Spread dill dip over bread shell about 1/2 inch from edge. Sprinkle with vegetables and cheese.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pastry
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Pour oil and milk into one measuring cup (don't stir).
Add, all at once, to flour; mix well.
Roll between two pieces of waxed paper (will be greasy).
Peel off top sheet of waxed paper.

title: little red chicken
directions: Place chicken on open baking dish.
Combine other ingredients and mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: lemon whippersnappers
directions: Mix together cake mix, egg and Cool Whip.
Form balls and drop into powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes or until light brown.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix all together.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch dish and bake at 325° until light brown.
Let this layer cool completely.

title: charlotte's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, salt, soda and vanilla. Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Roll balls in sugar.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar on ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Makes 8 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: cream cheese peanut butter pie
directions: In large bowl, with an electric mixer, combine cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar and milk; beat until smooth.
Gently fold in whipped topping.
Pour into pie shell.
Freeze 4 to 6 hours.
Thaw 10 minutes before serving.

title: four-bean salad
directions: Place all beans, green pepper and onions in a large bowl.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Stir until dissolved. Pour over beans.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour and soda.
Blend in oil, eggs and fruit cocktail.
Mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle on top the brown sugar and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs #1
directions: Mix together and form into meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: tarts
directions: Mix condensed milk, Cool Whip and lemon juice.	Fold in oranges, cherries and nuts.
Put in tart shells and top with a cherry.

title: debbie keys pound cake
directions: Combine the cake flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to first mixture, alternating with the milk.
Pour into a greased and floured angel food cake pan.
Put in a cold oven in center.
Turn oven on and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: applesauce raisin bread
directions: In a large bowl, beat egg lightly; stir in applesauce, butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar, mixing until well combined. Blend in flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Turn batter into a well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or a plain or fluted 1-quart ring mold.

Bake in a preheated 350° oven (325° for a glass pan) for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Let cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn out onto a rack to cool completely.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: shipwreck
directions: Grease bottom of 1 1/2 qt. dish/pan.
Put potatoes, celery, kidney beans & onion.
Next put in hamburger.
Pour soup over the top & bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until tender.
We like it just fine without the celery.

title: mexicali pasta salad
directions: Cook fettuccine; drain and set aside.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bell pepper may be substituted for chili peppers. Toss with fettuccine and vinaigrette dressing.

title: strawberry romaine salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss the Romaine lettuce, strawberries and onion.

title: ranch dressing
directions: Whisk all ingredients together and chill.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add eggs, coffee, oil and vanilla, beating well.
Add soda to buttermilk; stir well and add to the batter.
For a layer cake, bake in two round pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash and dry strawberries before slicing, set aside.
Mix together the milk and lemon juice,
fold in the cool whip and strawberries.
Pour into cooked and cooled pie crust.
Refrigerate 2 - 3 hours before eating.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together hamburger, soup mix, bread crumbs, egg, water and garlic powder.
Shape into balls.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Mix together hot ketchup and apple jelly in large saucepan.
Add meatballs. Simmer.

title: poppy seed dinner rolls
directions: Mix lightly.
Roll out and cut in wedges (pie shape).
Roll toward point to make crescent shaped rolls.
Let rise.
Bake in a 375° oven until lightly browned.
Brush with beaten egg white and sprinkle with poppy seed or sesame seed before baking.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Boil sweet potatoes and then mash.
Combine all ingredients except marshmallows; beat until fluffy.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Then add marshmallows to top and return to oven until golden brown.
For a variation pumpkin or squash can be substituted for the sweet potatoes.

title: baked ham with peaches
directions: Score fat in diamond pattern and stud with cloves.
If there is a skin or rind, roll it back for scoring and then back for roasting.
It will be removed later.
Roast 1 hour on a rack in preheated oven.
Remove ham from oven.
Remove rind.
Pour orange juice in baking pan and sprinkle grated orange zest over ham. Return to oven for another hour, basting every 15 minutes.
Mix the brandy and spices into peach juice.
Pour entire mixture over ham and continue basting during the remaining cooking time of total 15 minutes per pound cooking time.

title: knock your eyes out brownies
directions: Mix the caramels with 1/3 cup milk in saucepan over medium heat until melted.
Combine the cake mix, 1/3 cup milk and butter. Mix by hand; then add nuts.
Press half cake mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle morsels over baked cake.
Pour melted caramels over morsels.
Put the remainder of cake mixture in globs over the rest of ingredients. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fannie's rhubarb custard pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, nutmeg, butter and eggs.
Beat until well mixed and smooth.
Pour over rhubarb in unbaked pie shell.
Top with full crust or lattice crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: low fat mocha ice cream cookies
directions: Remove yogurt from freezer about 10 minutes before using. Mix Grape-Nuts, brown sugar and coffee granules.
Scoop 2 Tbsp. yogurt onto a chocolate wafer, cover with another wafer, compress slightly and roll edge in crumb mixture.
Freeze on cookie sheet until hard and then wrap individually in plastic wrap and put in a heavy duty plastic bag.

title: pecan patties
directions: Mix all ingredients; let stand 10 minutes.
Form into patties. Bake in the oven at 350° for 20 minutes on each side.

title: hot turkey salad(chicken)
directions: Mix together.
Put into a large casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese, then chips.
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: domingo chocolate cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, whisk together the cocoa, sour cream, eggs and vanilla until smooth.

title: carrot coins
directions: Cook the carrots in salted water. Add the onion, celery and green pepper. Bring to a boil the soup, oil, dry mustard, vinegar, apple cider vinegar and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over vegetables.

title: cream of onion soup
directions: Melt butter in large, heavy saucepan or Dutch oven. When foam subsides, add onions and reduce heat to low.
Cook, stirring frequently, until onions are golden brown, about 20 to 25 minutes. Stir in flour and salt.
Stir in milk until mixture is smooth. Heat to simmering.
Simmer, covered, until onions are tender, 7 to 8 minutes.
Beat egg yolks lightly in bowl.
Stir small amount of soup into beaten egg yolks.
Stir this mixture back into the soup. Cook until just heated through (a minute or two).
Do not allow to boil.
Season with nutmeg, and/or Worcestershire sauce and white pepper to taste.
Ladle into warmed soup bowls and, if desired, garnish with croutons, bacon and parsley.

title: thai beef salad
directions: Prepare a charcoal fire.
Combine the lime juice, fish sauce, sugar and chili in a large glass or ceramic bowl.
Add the tomatoes and cucumbers.
Toss.
Refrigerate.
Grill the steaks over hot coals until medium rare, about 3 to 5 minutes per side. Let stand for 5 minutes.
Slice the meat across the grain into thin slices.
Add to the salad.
Add mint leaves and toss well. Serve at room temperature.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: chicken and vegetable casserole
directions: Cut peeled potatoes and carrots into small, mouth-sized pieces.
Cook in boiling water with salt for 5 minutes.
Prepare spinach according to package instructions.
Cut chicken breasts in pieces and fry in pan with salt and pepper.
Mix all ingredients in an 8 x 12-inch (approximately) glass casserole dish.
Melt cheese in hot milk and season with pepper.
Pour on top of casserole.
Place in oven preheated to 400° and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring milk, sugar, salt and peel to a boil; be sure container is large enough so ingredients do not spill over (about a 2-quart pan).
Put in rice and cook over low heat.
Stir so it doesn't stick.
Cook about 45 to 50 minutes.
Take out the lemon peel; add 2 beaten egg yolks to the rice mixture.
Pour into a shallow dish (casserole).
Sprinkle cinnamon on top, then cool.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer vinegar, brown sugar, mustard, lemon slices, margarine, salt and pepper for 20 minutes.
Add catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to boiling point.
Brown meat and combine all ingredients.
Bake or grill.
Can be used for chicken, beef, pork and hot dogs.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Roll into balls.
Set in refrigerator to cool.
Put a toothpick in each.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin together in top of double boiler.
When balls are cool, dip in chocolate coating.
Place on waxed paper and let cool.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add broccoli and chicken broth; simmer until tender.
Mash.
Add milk and heat 5 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into fourths.
Boil in water until tender.
While that cooks, fry hamburger meat and onion.
When brown, drain off grease.
Add mushroom soup and can of water. Place potatoes in casserole dish.
Pour hamburger mixture over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with shredded cheese, if desired.

title: daisy fish fillets
directions: Place almonds and butter in skillet and brown, stirring occasionally.
Remove almonds and add fish.
Cook on medium heat 12 to 15 minutes, turning once.
Replace almonds and add remaining ingredients (except whole lemon) and cook 2 to 5 minutes.
Slice lemon into circles and place separately on serving platter. Arrange fillets around circles for "petals."

title: banana nugget drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together all dry ingredients.
Add bananas, vanilla, oats and chips.
Drop by spoonfuls.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Break bread into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients and bake in a 9-inch square pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Really good served with ham.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream sugars, eggs, vanilla and oil in large bowl.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Add oats and corn flakes.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Mix first six ingredients together in large bowl.
Shape into a ball.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour, then roll in chopped pecans. Cover and refrigerate.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except for tomato, bread crumbs and butter.
Season to taste with pepper, basil, garlic powder and oregano.
Place in a greased large pie pan.
Top with thinly sliced tomato, bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: marie's surprise meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5-inch pan.
Combine meat mixture ingredients together.
Press half of mixture in pan.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Combine flour, salt and lard, cutting until well mixed.
Beat egg until light.
Add to water and vinegar.
Add this mixture to flour and shortening and roll out as needed.
Will keep in refrigerator, wrapped in paper 3 to 4 days or may be rolled out in pie pans and frozen.

title: soup cracker snacks
directions: Place crackers in a 2 pound coffee can.
Pour salad dressing on crackers, then oil and other ingredients.
Shake and turn container upside down. Let set 3 days.

title: no cook mint patties
directions: Blend corn syrup, butter, extract and salt.
Add sugar.
Mix with spoon and hands until smooth.
Divide into how many colors you want.
Knead in a drop of coloring.
Shape into small balls. Flatten with a fork on waxed paper.
Let dry for several hours.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Blend cheese and butter together.
Slowly mix in flour and Rice Krispies.
(You can use a hand mixer, but when the flour and Krispies are added, the batter gets thick.
I use the mixer until I have the flour mixed in and then I use my hands to mix in the Rice Krispies.)
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets; press with fork to flatten.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mom's pennsylvania dutch oyster pie
directions: Clean and chop celery and onion.
Wash, pare and dice potatoes.
Simmer celery, onion and potatoes together in skillet in enough water to cover and cook just until tender.
Add oysters and a little of the oyster liquor, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup milk; gently heat through.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and spices.
Add raisins and coat.
Cream sugar, butter and molasses.
Add milk, eggs and pumpkin and blend well.
Stir in dry ingredients, blending only until flour disappears.

title: peppers, chuck and rice
directions: Remove seeds from green peppers and parboil in salted water to cover for 3 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Brown ground chuck sprinkled with onion salt; then add celery seed, rice, corn, chili powder and tomato soup.
Cook slowly until the seasonings are blended, about 30 minutes.
Put pepper shells into casserole and pile in the meat mixture until heaping.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 325° about 40 minutes.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Heat oil in skillet and fry ham and onion until onion is soft. Transfer contents to a large pan.
Add carrot, celery, tomato, kidney beans and meat broth.
Simmer, covered for 30 minutes.
Add potato, basil, garlic and salt.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add cabbage, green beans and macaroni.
Simmer until soup is thickened and all ingredients are tender.

title: cinnamon flop
directions: Sift sugar, flour and baking powder together.
Add melted butter and milk; stir until well blended.
Divide mixture between 2 (9-inch) pie or cake pans, well-greased.
Sprinkle tops with flour, then brown sugar, then cinnamon.
Push chunks of butter into the dough.
This makes holes and later gets gooey as it bakes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: recipe for a wonderful day
directions: Measure words carefully.
Add cups of understanding to human kindness.
Sift together 3 times to make smooth paste.
Cook with gas on front burner.
Keep temperature low to make both even. Season with gentle humor, warm personality and spice of life. Serve in individual molds.
Works best with a good mixer.

title: creamy mushrooms
directions: Wash and slice mushrooms; set aside.
Melt butter over low heat, then add mushrooms, sauteing them until they are slightly brown.
Add flour; stir as you add, then slowly pour in canned milk.
Stir until you get the consistency you like.
Add garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Makes a great sauce over veggies, pasta, chicken or fish.

title: broccoli potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes and broccoli in 2 cups water with salt added over medium heat until vegetables are tender.
Add remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.

title: chicken meatballs
directions: Combine chicken, egg, stuffing mix, parsley and 1/4 teaspoon each salt and pepper in large bowl until well blended.
Shape into 16 equal-size meatballs.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Wash broccoli and cut up.
Put in boiling salt water.
Cook stems 5 minutes first.
Add rest of broccoli and cook, covered, for 8 to 10 minutes.
Blend together soup, mayonnaise and curry powder.
Put into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and squeeze lemon juice over top.
Cover the mixture and top with crumbs.
Cook for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves about 6.

title: cheese log
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Save 1/2 package beef for outside of log.
Mix all ingredients together, chill and form into a log.
Cover with remaining beef.

title: frozen puddin-wiches(kids)
directions: Add milk gradually to peanut butter in a bowl; blend until smooth.
Add pudding mix.
Beat slowly until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spread filling about 1/2-inch thick on 1/2 the crackers.
Top with remaining crackers.
Press lightly and smooth edges with spatula.
Freeze until firm.

title: lemon sauce(especially good on gingerbread)
directions: Add all ingredients together and cook in double boiler until thick.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Put the sliced apples in a large bowl.
Break eggs over them and stir with fork.
Blend together the sugar, flour, soda, cinnamon, baking powder and salt.
Stir over apple mixture.
Stir well.
Add the oil, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Stir well and bake in an 8 x 12-inch pan at 325° for 1 hour.
This makes a nice moist cake and does not have to be frosted.

title: sherried beef
directions: Put beef in a 2-quart casserole dish with cover.
Mix and heat remaining ingredients; pour mixture over beef.
Cover dish; bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Serve over noodles, rice or potatoes.

title: pineapple icebox cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo together.
Add eggs; beat until fluffy. Spread crumbs into an 8-inch square dish.
Pour creamed mixture over crumbs.
Spread pineapple over creamed mixture; add the Cool Whip.
Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Chill overnight, or at least 12 hours.

title: mardi gras rice salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in large bowl and set aside. Combine mayonnaise, creole seasoning and curry.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Scrape carrots and slice into 1/4-inch crosswise slices.
Put 1-inch water , with 1/2 teaspoon salt per cup of water, in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and add carrots.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Cook for 12 to 15 minutes or until carrots are tender.

title: bacon-topped cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream in a large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Add cheese, onion, relish, horseradish and seasoning.
Beat at low speed until well blended.
Cover and chill thoroughly.

title: creamy dill dip
directions: Thoroughly combine sour cream, mayonnaise or salad dressing, minced dried onion, dill weed and seasoned salt.
Cover and chill thoroughly to blend flavors.
Serve with fresh vegetable dippers or crackers.
Makes 2 cups dip.

title: christmas candy
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and cream to soft ball stage.
Beat until thick and add vanilla.
Continue beating as the remaining ingredients are added.
It will be thick and sticky.
Pour into greased pans and chill for 24 hours before cutting.
This candy can be stored for weeks and improves with age.

title: cheese ball
directions: Leave Velveeta cheese and cream cheese out of refrigerator to get to room temperature.
Mix with hands.
Then roll in chili powder.

title: monkey bread
directions: Let bread dough thaw and rise.
Pull off pieces.
Roll in butter, sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Put in a greased tube or Bundt pan.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tiny fruit cakes
directions: Cut up fruit and nuts.
Add milk, coconut, butter and vanilla. Grease tiny muffin tins well.
This will fill about 48.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Remove carefully when done and cool.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Before preparing the actual salad, mix the Mayonnaise, Sugar and Vinegar together and set aside.
Combine the remaining salad ingredients.
Do not add the dressing until salad is being served.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring water to boil; add rice.
Cook 7 minutes.
Add milk, and oleo.
Bring to boil, watch closely. Cook slowly on top of stove for 1 hour.
Beat eggs and sugar; add to rice mixture.
Turn off heat; add vanilla
and raisins.

title: vegetable oil pastry
directions: Roll between wax paper.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Mix ingredients together well.

title: soft sour cream date nut cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter, eggs and sour cream. Sift all dry ingredients together. Add to cream mixture with dates and nuts. Drop on cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: vegetarian golden fried scallops
directions: Drain scallops.
Beat eggs and milk together, forming batter. Dip scallops in batter, then in bread crumbs and sprinkle generously garlic powder on scallops.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco in large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add flavorings. Pour into well-greased and lightly floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add flour and mix well. Add egg, milk and vanilla, mixing well after each.
Bake on cookie sheet for 8 minutes at 375°.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Melt butter until caramel color.
Add milk until almost scalded.
Cool.
Beat eggs, add sugar and lemon juice.
Pour into pie shell, bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: 7-up pie crust
