directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening together. Combine egg, 7-Up and vinegar. Stir into flour mixture quickly so dough clings and cleans bowl. Work dough into smooth, flat round.
Divide in half (2 balls).
Makes enough for 2 crusts (9-inch).

title: leigh's peanut butter kisses
directions: Beat shortening, peanut butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar together in large bowl.
Beat eggs, milk and vanilla into mixture.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt in medium bowl.
Mix dry ingredients gradually into creamed mixture at low speed until just blended.
Form dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar and place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°
for 8 minutes.
Press chocolate Kiss, Hug or M&M peanut candy into center of each cookie and bake 3 more minutes for 7 dozen cookies.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: In a
medium
size bowl blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons of
butter
until
smooth.
Add next 5 ingredients; mix well. Separate
crescent
dough
into
rectangles.
Firmly press perforations
to
seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture onto center of rectangle.
Pull
the
four corners of the dough to the top center
of
the
chicken mixture.
Twist slightly and seal edges. Brush top with reserved 1 tablespoon butter.
Dip in crouton crumbs.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: cream pie
directions: Whip and put in graham cracker crust.
Top with cherries or pineapple, strawberry or blueberry pie filling.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans.
Mix well.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Chill well.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Makes 1 (5-inch) cheese ball.
Make several days in advance for full flavor.
Freezes well.

title: wanda's chicken casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Crush Ritz crackers and mix 1/2 stack into mixture.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch or 2 (8 -inch) square baking dishes.
Spread 1 stack crushed Ritz crackers over top and pour melted margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave on High for 15 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: english muffin pizza
directions: Pour 2 teaspoons of sauce on top of each muffin.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese generously.
Add meat or vegetables of choice. Bake in oven until cheese bubbles.

title: cinnamon twists(great for breakfast!)
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Roll biscuits, each to a 9-inch rope; bring ends together and seal.
Dip in melted margarine, then in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Twist.
Place on greased baking sheet. Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Bake at 425° for about 10 minutes.

title: fruit salad(original recipe)
directions: Put grapes and undrained pineapple in bowl.
Add sugar or Sugar Twin.
Stir.
Let stand in refrigerator.
Add bananas when serving. Fruits, I add any or all:
kiwi pieces, can of mandarin oranges (juice and all), apples (diced with skins on), 1 can undrained fruit cocktail (in winter when fresh fruits are scarce).
Lately have been using star slices, too.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook over low heat until sauce thickens.

title: gram's spaghetti carbonara
directions: While cooking spaghetti, heat ham cubes in small frying pan with olive oil.
Season with ginger and ground pepper, heating through.
Have cheese and beaten eggs set aside, ready to toss into spaghetti (in large mixing bowl) immediately after draining. Add ham to mixture. Serves 4 to 6.

title: caramel walnut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar and egg.
Cut in 1/2 cup butter until crumbly.
Stir in walnuts.
Reserve 2 cups crumb mixture; press remaining firmly on bottom of greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Melt caramels in heavy pan with condensed milk and 1/4 cup butter.
Pour over prepared crust soon as it comes out of oven (15 minutes).
Top with reserved crumbs. Bake 20 minutes more (until bubbly).
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Store at room temperature loosely covered.

title: cheese strata
directions: Remove bread crusts; butter and cube bread.
Beat eggs.
Add seasonings, then add milk.
Add cubed bread and cheese.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Refrigerate covered overnight. Do not stir before cooking.
Bake approximately 50 minutes at 350°.
Allow to set 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.
This holds heat and cuts into neat squares.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: crab apple chili
directions: In large saucepan brown beef, pork and add Worcestershire sauce.
Drain fat and simmer.
In separate pan combine all other ingredients, then add meat mixture and simmer for 1 hour.
One large can of kidney beans is optional.

title: taco salad
directions: Rinse beans; put in bowl.
Crush Fritos in package by hand. Mix all ingredients together, add dressing and serve immediately.

title: chocolate fudge balls(no bake)
directions: Leave cheese and butter out overnight to soften.
Place in mixer; cream with 4x sugar.
Add rest of ingredients; press flat in pan.
Chill.
Cut into squares.
Roll squares into balls.
Roll balls in coconut and 4x sugar.
Keep cold until ready to use.

title: great-grandma atkinson's corn pie
directions: Combine all dry ingredients and add milk.
Stir in beaten eggs and add butter and corn.
Bake in a buttered casserole until slightly browned, 30 to 40 minutes, at 350°.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat sweetened milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Add biscuit mix; mix well.
Chill at least an hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Flatten with fork.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Store, tightly covered, at room temperature.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake in tube pan or loaf pans (2) for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.
Turn oven on after cake is inside.

title: annie's e z fruit salad
directions: Cut up fruits to bite size pieces.
Use melon baller for nice round melon bits.
If you use watermelon, try not to let too much squishy liquid in the mixture.
Gently stir all fruits together, then throw in the walnuts. Top fruits with cherry pie filling. Voila!
It's beautiful as well as tasty.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together, then add eggs, butter, lemon juice and water.
Add a little grated lemon rind.

title: mounds
directions: Bring syrup to a boil.
Pour over coconut.
Mix well; let set overnight.
Melt chocolate.
Wet hands and roll coconut into balls.
Dip in chocolate and place on waxed paper.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add water, vinegar and salt and bring to boil, stirring.
Add beets and onion; cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in butter until melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: old-fashioned vermont beans
directions: Wash beans, cover with cold water.
Add soda and soak overnight.

title: scandinavian fish stew
directions: Rinse salt cod and place in bowl.
Cover with water and refrigerate 24 hours.
Remove salt cod from water.
Pat dry.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Place in slow cooker with remaining ingredients.
Cook on simmer setting for 6 hours.
Be sure to serve hot biscuits or crusty bread to dredge up the liquid and baked apples for dessert.

title: chinese cookies
directions: Melt chips in a pan or bowl over hot boiling water.
Mix in noodles and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and chill.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Set aside.
Add brown sugar to beaten egg and shortening.
Mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients, oats and buttermilk.
Bake in greased muffin pans at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: hamburger-vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburg in a large saucepan.
Put water and bouillon cubes in pan to dissolve over medium heat.
Add to browned hamburg.
Add rest of vegetables and spices.
Simmer until done. (Discard bay leaf.)

title: stuffed pasta shells
directions: Combine ham or turkey, Ricotta cheese, salad dressing and onion, mix.
Fill shells with mixture and place, filled side up, in shallow pan.

Add 2 Tbsp. cold water to dish, cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until heated. Combine Parmesan cheese, crumbs, parsley and margarine, melted. Sprinkle over shells. Continue to bake uncovered 5 minutes.

title: skillet chicken stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in shallow bowl; coat chicken. In a large skillet; melt butter; brown chicken. Add onion and celery; cook for 3 minutes. Stir in potatoes. Combine broth, thyme, ketchup, and cornstarch; stir into skillet. Bring to boil. reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: mock cranberry salad or applesauce deluxe
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Blend in applesauce and lemon juice.
Pour into mold or serving dish.
May be used as a dessert, salad or relish.
Serve with your favorite turkey dinner

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Save 1 slice chipped beef.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Shape into a ball and cover with the slice of chipped beef.
Serve with crackers.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix jello and cornstarch dry.
Bring water to boiling, then add all ingredients.
Cook until it starts to clear and thicken. Cool and let it partly set.
Pour over strawberries in prepared pie shell.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger meat.
Drain.
Mix with melted cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Heat until hot!
Serve with chips or on hamburger buns.

title: snowman sandwiches
directions: Spread a thin layer of cream cheese on 1 slice of bread. Cover the cream cheese with another slice of bread to make a cream cheese sandwich.
Cut the bread in the shape of a snowman.
Spread another thin layer of cream cheese over the top of your snowman. Decorate your snowman sandwich using the raisins and walnuts to make eyes, a nose, a mouth and buttons.
Makes one sandwich.

title: mystery salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges, reserving liquids.
Combine fruit and marshmallows.
Prepare the instant pudding mix using the reserved fruit juices; pour over fruit and stir.
Chill or serve immediately.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, orange peel and vanilla.
Add egg, beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in milk.
Sift together dry ingredients, blend in creamed mixture.

title: never fail graham cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well; add egg yolks and beat well until thoroughly blended.
Stir the baking powder into the cracker crumbs.
Add the milk and crackers crumbs alternately and blend thoroughly.
Stir in the chopped nut meats.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and fold these into the mixture last.
Bake in two 8-inch pans in moderate oven, 350°, about 45 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Pour pineapple juice in pitcher; set aside.
Bring water to boil; add sugar and dissolve.
Remove from heat.
Add frozen juices and stir until melted.
Pour into pitcher and refrigerate. Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Pour over ice in large punch bowl.
Serves 20 to 25.

title: pam's lemon bread
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to other mixture alternately with milk. Add
grated
lemon
rind.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°. In
the meantime,
mix
the
cup lemon juice and 1/3 cup sugar.
Ad soon as bread is taken from the oven, drizzle this mixture on
top of the hot bread.
Do not poke holes in bread to allow more to soak in!

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat well.
Alternately add flour and whipping cream.
Add flavoring last.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in cold oven at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave for 10 more minutes.

title: quick doughnuts
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out and cut doughnuts with doughnut cutter.
Let stand 15 minutes on board.
Have hot fat (370°) as you drop in doughnuts.
Fry about 1 minute on each side. Frost or roll in sugar or leave plain.

title: eggnog french toast
directions: Cut loaf of bread crosswise into eight 1-inch thick slices (use remaining bread another day).
Cut each slice diagonally in half.
Arrange bread slices in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan (greased)
In a large bowl with fork, beat eggs, milk, sugar, rum extract and nutmeg until blended. Pour mixture over bread in pan.
With fork, prick bread slices and turn occasionally to coat both sides of bread until all egg mixture is absorbed.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in butter until lightly browned, about 20 minutes. Add broth and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle toast with cheese; place under broiler until cheese is lightly browned.
Pour soup in bowls and float toast slices on top.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: appetizer ham logs
directions: Combine ham, egg and pepper in medium bowl; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch logs or balls.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Refrigerate, covered, for 1 hour.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Slice rolls in half.
Spread mixture on both sides of rolls.
Layer cheese and ham in one layer.
Spoon remaining mixture on top of rolls.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: john's chili
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat in saucepan on high.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer approximately 1 hour.

title: hot spiced cranberry punch
directions: Combine juices, water and sugar in a 30-cup percolator.
Place cinnamon pieces and cloves in basket.
Allow punch to perk entire cycle.
Percolator will keep punch piping hot.
Makes 30 cups.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all together and bake 45 minutes at 350°. Serve hot.

title: "dirt" dessert
directions: Combine butter, cream cheese and sugar; mix well.
Mix pudding and milk as directed on package and combine with cream cheese mixture.
Add Cool Whip.
Crush cookies until they resemble dirt. Cut cover of Cool Whip container to fit bottom of flower pot and put half of cookie crumbs in flower pot.
Add pudding mixture and spread rest of cookie crumbs over pudding.
Refrigerate overnight. Before serving, add a bunch of artificial flowers to pot.

title: pralines
directions: Bring to a bubbling boil.
Remove from fire and add 1 teaspoon soda.
Stir until it quits bubbling.
Return to fire and cook to firm ball stage.
Add lots of pecans, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 2 tablespoons butter (I use Parkay).
Beat until it loses its gloss and drop on wax paper.

title: apple-nut dessert
directions: Mix well egg and sugar.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture and stir well.
Stir in apples, nuts and vanilla.
Spread in greased pie dish or 8 x 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in
a heavy kettle.
Cover; bring to a boil and simmer for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: italian cheese bread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Spread on French bread (cut lengthwise). Bake at 375° until bubbly.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute pepper and onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin dream pie
directions: Combine milk and pudding mix.
Add pumpkin, Cool Whip and pie spice.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with additional Cool Whip and chopped pecans, if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: tea punch
directions: Brew tea.
Add sugar and stir to dissolve.
Add all other ingredients and chill.

title: apple pie
directions: Prepare pie crust according to standard pie crust directions.

title: ranch style lentils
directions: Cook lentils, about 30 minutes.
Brown meat in oil.
Add all other ingredients.
Place in 9 X 13 pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°-400°.
Top with cheese during last few minutes of baking. Serves 8.

title: super sloppy joes
directions: In a large skillet over medium-high heat add oil and beef to pan.
Brown and break meat up.
Add brown sugar and steak seasoning and combine.
Once browned, add in the onion and red pepper.
Turn heat to medium and cook for 5 minutes.
Add in vinegar, worcestershire, tomato sauce and paste.
Stir to combine and let cook for 5-10 more minutes.
Serve on crusty rolls.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and peanut butter in a heavy saucepan. Heat over medium
heat until mixture is bubbly.
Add Special K and stir.
Remove from heat.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and pat down.
Sprinkle chips on top and allow to melt.
Spread with a knife.
Cool and cut.

title: jeffrey's salad dressing
directions: In a tight fitting covered jar, combine all of the ingredients and shake well.
This recipe may be doubled or tripled.
This dressing is delicious on a pasta salad.

title: pumpkin bread(serves a crowd)
directions: Blend salad oil and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add pumpkin. Add dry
ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool bread in pan. Stays
moist for a long time.
Wrap in foil and store in refrigerator.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown onion in oleo.
Add hamburger; brown and drain off excess
fat.
Add
ketchup, mustard, sugar and vinegar.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: cheese cake diamonds
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar together.
Add flour and nuts; mix well.
Set aside 1 cup of mixture for toping.
Press remainder of mixture on bottom of 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Blend sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Add egg, milk, lemon juice and vanilla; beat well.
Spread over bottom crust.
Sprinkle 1 cup of saved mixture over the top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Chill.
Cut into diamonds (or squares).
Enjoy!

title: cranberry salad(serves 12)
directions: Grind cranberries and orange. Add sugar; mix and let stand a few minutes. Dissolve pineapple juice with water and jello. When half set, add to first mixture and nuts, marshmallows, celery, apple and pineapple. Pour in mold and set in cool place.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Put corn and green beans in a strainer and let drain while preparing other ingredients.
Mix together the celery, onion, soup, cheese and sour cream, then add vegetables.
Spray pan with Pam and pour mixture into casserole dish.
Top with Pepperidge Farm stuffing and drizzle with margarine.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Dump beans all into a crock-pot.
Brown your hamburger with onion and peppers.
Drain off fat.
Pour meat, onion and peppers on top of beans.
Put barbecue sauce on top of this mixture.
Do not stir at this time.
Cook on high until it comes to a boil. Turn to low and cook for 3 hours, then stir thoroughly.
Serve with slaw, mashed potatoes and corn bread.
Very good and a time saver.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Mix figs with sugar and gelatin in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly until thick, then cook 20 to 30 minutes.
Seal in hot jars and refrigerate.

title: microwave breakfast pita pockets
directions: Crumble sausage into a shallow 1-quart casserole.
Cover tightly with heavy-duty plastic wrap.
Fold back a small edge of wrap to allow steam to escape.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes or until sausage is browned, stirring once.
Drain well on paper towels.
Set aside.
Combine eggs, milk, oregano, salt and pepper in a shallow 1-quart casserole, mixing well.
Microwave on High 2 to 4 minutes, pushing cooked portion to center at 1 minute intervals.
Cut cheese and pita bread rounds in half.
Line each bread half with 1 piece of cheese.
Combine sausage and egg mixture.
Spoon about 1/4 cup sausage-egg mixture into pita pockets.
Wrap each pita pocket in a paper towel.
Place 4 pita pockets on a paper plate or glass pizza plate and microwave on Medium (50% power) 1 to 2 minutes or until warm.
Repeat process with remaining sandwiches.
Makes 4 servings.

title: covered rump roast
directions: Place fat side up on rack in a roasting pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread onion slices under and over roast.
Cover and cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 350°.
Remove from pan and make gravy.

title: fresh raspberry tea cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat honey with egg.
Mix salt, flour and baking powder.
Add egg mixture with milk all at once.
Stir up quickly until all ingredients are moistened.
Stir in melted butter and raspberries.

title: christmas rainbow poke cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour batter into 2 round pans, 8 or 9 x 1 1/2-inch (do not use pans with removable bottoms).
Bake as directed; cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool completely.
Place cake layers, top side up, back in the 2 clean pans.
Prick each layer with fork at 1/2-inch intervals. Pour 1 cup boiling water over raspberry jello in bowl; stir until jello is dissolved.
Spoon raspberry jello over 1 layer.
Repeat with lime jello.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Dip 1 layer in pan into warm water 10 seconds; invert on plate, gently shaking to loosen.
Remove pan; spread layer with 1 cup Cool Whip.
Remove remaining layer from pan the same way.
Frost with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate and garnish with flattened gumdrops; cut to resemble holly.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add frozen orange juice, pineapple and orange slices.
Place in an 8-inch casserole dish.
Allow to gel.
Prepare pudding using 1 cup of milk.
Fold in whipped topping and spread over congealed salad.

title: strawberry mousse
directions: Partially thaw frozen strawberries.
Reserve a few for garnish.
Blend in sour cream and sugar.
Place in 9-inch pie pan or 1-quart mold.
Partially freeze. Remove from freezer.
Beat until smooth.
Return to freezer until ready to serve.
Cut into squares.
Add whipped cream and a berry.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and roll in chopped nuts.

title: goat cheese rosemary
directions: Sprinkle 1/4 cup of the rosemary in bottom of a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish; arrange cheese slices over rosemary.
Pour the olive oil over cheese; sprinkle with remaining rosemary.
Cover and chill for 8 hours.

title: asian sloppy joes
directions: Saute turkey, add remaining ingredients. Simmer, covered for 10 minutes.

title: million dollar salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Add pineapple, nuts and cherries.
Add lemon juice.
(If you wish, add 1 can drained fruit cocktail.)
Let set in refrigerator for an hour or 2.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni to directions.
Drain.
Put in a bowl hot.
Add cheese and veggies, chopped to bite-size.
Add spices and mayo. Chill and serve.

title: seafood scampi
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Place shrimp, scallops and crab meat in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Combine next 8 ingredients. Pour over seafood.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.
Broil
4-inches from heat 5 minutes or until seafood is done. Serve over rice.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar, margarine, peanut butter and eggs together.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Press each one with floured fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: seafood sauce
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a medium mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Serve with cooked shellfish.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Make vanilla filling:
Set aside the egg whites.

Cook 1 cup sugar, cornstarch, vanilla, butter and milk until thick, pour half of the vanilla filling in a deep dish pie shell and set aside. Then take powdered sugar and peanut butter, mix until crumbly, pour 3/4 cup of crumbs on filling.
Pour remaining vanilla filling on top of crust.
Beat egg whites until peaks form.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar, beat until stiff.
Spread on pie.
Put remaining peanut butter crumbs on top of pie.
Cook at 325° until brown.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Pour water over Jell-O.
Mix.
Add cranberry sauce which has been softened with fork in can.
Add raspberries.
Pour into serving dish.

title: easy dessert
directions: Crumble angel food cake into an 8 x 8-inch pan or dish.
Cover with instant pudding mix, prepared as directed.
Put Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Refrigerate.
Crush Heath candy bars and sprinkle over top of dessert just before serving or up to 2 hours before. (If you freeze the candy, it is easier to crush.)
Chill and serve.

title: georgia pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar; cream well.
Beat together eggs and cream of tartar.
Alternately with flour, then beat for 10 minutes by the clock.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour, until done.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and mix well.
Beat in crumbs.
Add baking powder to milk and mix together.
Then add vanilla, coconut and nuts to mixture.
Pour into 3 layer pans and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana colada
directions: In a blender, combine the bananas, skim milk, pineapple and its juice, cream of coconut, sugar, rum extract and allspice. Blend mixture into a puree.
Then add the ice and blend again until smooth.

title: chow-chow
directions: Chop all the ingredients fine and boil for 20 minutes.

title: boiled custard
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl; mix with electric mixer until there are no lumps.
Cook on top of stove with medium heat until it simmers.
Stir constantly, then place in refrigerator.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: turkisk zucchini dolmas
directions: Combine all ingredients, except squash and tomatoes.
Cut ends from zucchini and scoop out centers.
Fill zucchini loosely with meat mixture.
Make meatballs from remainder.
Chop zucchini centers and add to large skillet with tomatoes.
Heat.
Add zucchini and meatballs.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes, or until tender.

title: easy slow cooker chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts into large chunks. Place the chicken breasts, cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup, cream of celery soup and the rice in a slow cooker. Cook on high for 3 hours or low for 4 hours.

title: millies beef jerky
directions: Put steak in large Ziploc bag and add mixture of Worcestershire sauce, salt, garlic powder, curry, soy sauce, onion powder, pepper and ginger.
Marinate 8 hours or more.
Put a single layer of meat on cookie sheet.
Set oven at lowest setting.
Cook for 10 hours with the oven door propped open slightly with folded wet dishcloth.

title: dog biscuits
directions: Add egg and liquid to flour; add remaining ingredients.
Roll dough to about 1/4-inch.
Shape.
Microwave in single layer for 7 to 8 minutes or until firm.

title: onion casserole
directions: Put onions in dish; spread soup over top.
Cover with cheese and then the potato chips.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry bread(2 loaves)
directions: Combine
flour,
sugar,
cinnamon,
soda
and salt in a large bowl.
Add salad oil and eggs; mix thoroughly.
Stir in strawberries and nuts.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x
x 3-inch loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
The
flavor
is better if loaves are wrapped tightly and allowed to sit overnight.

title: cookie pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with mixer.
Add nuts and chocolate chips or butterscotch.
Spread mixture in 2 ungreased 10-inch pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chili-hominy casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Pour in melted margarine.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake in a 2-quart casserole dish at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add beaten eggs.
Alternately add flour and bananas (previously mash bananas and mix in soda); add nuts.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 275° to 300° for about 1 to 1 1/4 hours; turn off oven and let soak until done.
Be sure to use enough bananas.
They are what make it moist.

title: lemon lime cocktail
directions: Pour over cracked ice.
Each serving contains 30 calories.

title: bob's meat loaf
directions: Mix together well.
Let stand overnight, then put in meat loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: monkey cake
directions: Take biscuits, cut.
Grease Bundt pan.
Shake biscuits in 3/4 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Drop in pan.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Fry bacon until crisp. Add liquid and pour over lettuce.

title: spaghetti bake
directions: Saute meat, onion and garlic in butter.
Add mushrooms, corn and soup with water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add vermicelli.
Cover.
Start at 350° for 30 minutes, then turn to 200° for about 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.
Recipe can be doubled for larger casserole.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Salt to taste and let stand for 30 minutes.
Drain.
Fry bacon in large skillet until crisp, then remove to drain.
Reserve bacon fat in skillet. Season flour with salt and pepper and dredge tomato slices in seasoned flour.
Heat bacon fat and fry tomato slices until brown on both sides.
Serve on hot platter with crisp
bacon.
Serve with green salad and biscuits.

title: lazy cobbler(dump cake)
directions: Pour the fruit into the baking dish.
Add the dry cake mix on top of the fruit.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add unbeaten eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Sift together the cocoa and flour and add alternately with the buttermilk.
Start with flour and end with the flour mixture. Stir the soda into the hot coffee and add last.
Mix only to blend well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or into cupcake tins.
Bake 30 minutes for cake or 20 minutes for cupcakes at 350°.

title: sweeter chex mix
directions: Cook margarine, brown sugar and syrup.
Bring to a boil.
Add baking soda.
Mix everything together in a brown paper bag.
Put in microwave for 2 1/2 minutes.
Shake, then cook 2 1/2 minutes more.
Add 1 pound M&M's.
Cool on waxed paper.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix crackers and melted butter; press 3/4 of crumbs in bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan or baking dish.
Blend pudding and milk.
Add ice cream.
Blend well.
Pour mixture evenly over crumbs.
Let set in refrigerator until chilled.
Spread with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.

title: chicken and almond casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in 1/4 cup margarine in large skillet. Add next 4 ingredients; mix well.
Add chicken and stuffing mix; mix well.
Place in 9 x 14-inch greased baking dish.
Saute almonds in 1/2 cup margarine.
Sprinkle over top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast; sprinkle over top of tepid water (not hot, but warm).
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add rest of water.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour.
Mix well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Rise, covered, in warm place.
Punch down.
Half for smaller pizza.
(Store in plastic bag in freezer if not using all.)
Spread dough on greased pan, flouring hands to work.
Spread on pizza sauce, cheese and cooked meat and spices as desired.
Bake at 400° until cheese is set and looks done, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: crunch-top baked apples
directions: Rinse apples and core.
Mix cereal, butter and sugar.
Press 1/6 of mixture in each apple.
Set apples slightly apart in shallow baking dish, 9 x 13-inch or 10 x 14-inch oval.
Add apple juice to pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° about 30 minutes.
Offer cream to pour over apples, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken with wild rice
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in pan.
Lay cleaned chicken breasts on top.
Sprinkle chicken with paprika.
Cover pan tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake 2 hours at 325°.

title: oyster stew
directions: Drain oysters, reserve liquid, set oysters aside.
Combine oyster liquid, flour, salt and water in saucepan.
Stir until smooth.
Add oysters and butter, simmer five minutes.
Stir scalded milk and cream into mixture.
Cover and remove from heat. Let stand 15 minutes.
Reheat over very low heat if desired. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pudding cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on package and bake in a large (9 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch) baking dish.
As soon as you take it from the oven, poke holes all over it.
I use the end of a wooden spoon.

title: fusilli with roasted tomatoes, pesto and mozzarella
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place tomatoes, cut side down, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until wrinkled (approximately 5 minutes).
Chop and set aside.
Meanwhile, prepare Pesto.
Toss cooked, hot fusilli with Pesto; add chopped tomatoes and Mozzarella.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix and store.
Use 2 scoops per cup of hot water (about 2 tablespoons per cup).

title: jogging juice
directions: Mix and drink 1/4 cup (2 ounces) each day.

title: hot cranberry punch(also called christmas punch)
directions: Combine all ingredients in large saucepan.
Let boil for one minute.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour into warm punch bowl.
Serve in warm cups.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes with skin; cool, peel and shred.
In saucepan over low heat melt cheese with margarine.
Stir until melted. Remove from heat and let stand at room temperature.
Combine cheese mixture, sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Fold into potatoes. Put into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chess cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix butter and 1 egg, then slowly add cake mix. Batter will almost be like bread dough.
Press batter into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Don't bake yet.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Heat water and beans to boiling in Dutch oven.
Boil 2 minutes; remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Add enough water to cover beans if necessary.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender (do not boil or beans will burst).
Heat oven to 350°.
Drain beans, reserving liquid.
Layer beans, onion and salt pork in ungreased 4-quart bean pot, casserole or Dutch oven.
Mix brown sugar, molasses, salt, dry mustard, pepper and bean liquid; pour over beans.
Add enough water to almost cover beans.
Cover and bake 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Uncover and bake about 30 minutes longer or until beans are desired consistency.
Makes 8 servings.

title: kosher dills
directions: Sterilize 5 quart jars and lids.
Wash fresh cucumbers and pack into hot jars.
To each quart add:
1 clove garlic, 2 heads fresh dill, small piece of hot red pepper.
Combine 1 cup of pickling salt, 3 cups water and 1 quart cider vinegar.
Bring to boil.
Fill jars to within 1/2 inch of top with boiling mixture.
Adjust lids. Process in boiling water bath for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate oat-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate morsels and nuts; mix well.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Add taco seasoning and water.
Mix refried beans with 1/3 cup taco sauce.
Put half the bean mixture in bottom of pie shell.
Add half the meat mixture, half the cheese and all the corn chips.
Then add bean mixture, meat and cheese last.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with optional toppings and taco sauce after removal from oven.

title: t cakes
directions: Mix in bowl until like biscuit dough.
Knead on floured board until stiff.
Roll dough out and cut out tea cakes and put on cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven until brown.

title: taco shells
directions: Mix and fry.
Top with favorite taco topping (lettuce, tomatoes, grated cheese, hamburger, onion, green peppers, etc.).

title: squash-carrot casserole
directions: Beat squash and carrots together and add all other ingredients.
Turn into buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Blend the flour, butter, sugar and water to form dough.
Press in a 12-inch round pizza pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°. Cool crust.

title: rock a bye punch
directions: Just before serving place sherbet in punch bowl. Add ginger ale and stir until sherbet is almost melted. Makes about 2 gallons.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Brown celery and onion
in skillet with 2 tablespoons of butter. Combine all ingredients in greased casserole dish and bake in oven for 40 minutes until brown.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels in 1/2 cup evaporated milk, stirring constantly. Set aside.

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat milk to scalding and pour over bread crumbs. Cool and add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Pour in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole (will be very watery). Cook at 350° for 1 hour (until knife comes out clean; will be puffy and will sink in center as it cools).

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugars, Crisco, peanut butter and vanilla together in large bowl.
Beat in eggs.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to peanut butter mixture.
Roll into 1-inch balls; press, with flour dipped fork, in crisscross pattern.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Melt 2 sticks of margarine.
Cool and add 2 cups sugar, 1/3 cup cocoa, flour, coconut, pecans, eggs and salt.
Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately spread with jar of Marshmallow Creme.
Wait 5 minutes and ice cake with remaining ingredients: 1 stick butter, powdered sugar, cocoa, canned milk and vanilla.

title: mingey potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins.
Cool, peel and coarsely shred.
In saucepan, cook butter and cheese.
Stir until almost melted. Remove from heat.
Blend seasonings, sour cream and onions.
Add potatoes and stir.
Turn in butter.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake in oven at 350° for 25 minutes or until heated. Cover casserole when baking.
Serves 8.

title: hot crossed tuna casserole
directions: Combine and mix all but rolls.
Put into 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Separate dough into 2 rectangles; press perforation to seal. Cut dough in strips; lattice across casserole.
Brush lightly with salad dressing.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with Cool Cucumber Sauce.

title: keema
directions: Saute onions in large kettle.
Fry hamburger in saucepan. When hamburger is half browned, add 1/4 cup water, 1/2 cup catsup, onion salt, garlic salt, turmeric, curry powder and salt.
After onions are browned, add 3 cups rice. Add whole cloves to hamburger mixture; add bay leaves to rice.
Add peas and juice to hamburger mixture.
Add 1 quart of more water to rice mixture; boil.
Add more water if it becomes too thick.
Simmer hamburger mixture with lid.
When rice is 3/4 done, put in heated oven at 450° for not more than 1 hour.
Serve the hamburger mixture over the rice mixture.
Be sure to remove the bay leaves.
Makes 20 servings.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: tango fried green plantains
directions: Peel plantains and slice diagonally into 1-inch slices.
Heat oil in a nonstick pan.
Fry plantains until a fork will go through them easily or until they turn golden brown (depends on how crispy you like them).
Drain on paper towel.
Then sprinkle with salt and vinegar for the tang-ohh!!

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix ingredients, using one can of tomato sauce.
Place in peppers, which have been seeded.
Pour other can of tomato sauce over them.
Cook one hour or until tender on 350°.
Cover loosely.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, boil sugar, butter, salt and milk for 10 minutes.
Start timing when mixture comes to rolling boil.
Stir frequently.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and nuts; mix well.
Pour into buttered 17 x 11 x 3/4-inch pan.
Chill thoroughly; cut into small squares.
Keep refrigerated in airtight container.

title: apple bars
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla and cinnamon in bowl. Mix dry ingredients together and add.
Add apples and nuts.
Pour in a greased 10 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate paska
directions: Melt the chocolate in top of double boiler and let cool while you continue the recipe.
Mix cream cheese, butter, sugar and vanilla with electric beater.
Add cooled chocolate and cream well.
Put in a cheesecloth lined clay flowerpot or form.
You can also use a square pan lined with a graham cracker crust. Refrigerate overnight.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, oil, water and pumpkin, then add mixed flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and soda.
Fold in chopped nuts if desired. Bake at 350° for one hour (in loaf pan) or when pick comes out clean.

title: farmers market
directions: Cook the pre soaked beans for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours in plenty of water with the salt, bay leaf and oregano.
Remove from heat when soft but not mushy as they will continue to cook in the stew. Drain beans and save the broth.
Prepare tomatoes.
Open the chili pods and remove the seeds and veins, then cut the chilies into narrow strips.
Cut the squash into large pieces.
Shave the kernels from the corn.
Heat oil in large skillet and saute onions over high heat for 1 to 2 minutes.
Lower heat, add garlic, chili powder, cumin and coriander and stir everything together.
Add a little bean broth so the chili doesn't scorch or burn.
Cook until onions begin to soften, about 4 minutes, then add tomatoes and stew for 5 minutes.
Stir in squash, corn, green beans, and chili strips, along with the cooked beans and enough broth to make a fairly wet stew.
Cook slowly until the vegetables are done, about 15 or 20 minutes.
Taste the stew and adjust the seasoning.
Stir in cheese and chopped cilantro and garnish with whole leaves of cilantro.
Serve with cornbread or tortillas.
A great one dish meal if you have a garden or have just visited the Farmer's Market.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Mix with asparagus liquid to add to rest of ingredients.
Beat egg whites and fold in last.
Dot with butter; place cracker crumbs on top (about 20 crackers).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars on medium speed for 5 minutes.
Add eggs and beat well.
Gradually add flour, soda and salt.
Beat well.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
You may add chocolate chips, nuts or peanuts.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put bread in baking dish. Add 1 cup milk. In another bowl, mix eggs and sugar, but not real good. Add margarine, vanilla and remaining milk. Pour in baking dish. Bake at 350° until custard is firm.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Mix together and place in crock-pot.
I cook all day or half day in crock-pot.

title: glorified cornbread
directions: Mix together well.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Combine pop and marshmallows over low heat until marshmallows are melted.
Pour over gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Add hot mixture slowly to cream cheese; beat until smooth.
Add lemon juice, pineapple and nuts. Chill until partially thickened.
Fold in whipped cream.
Blend together.
Refrigerate.

title: rosie's quick cobbler
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine in baking dish (1 1/2-quart dish). Combine all other ingredients.
Pour a line of batter lengthwise down the middle of the dish, the margarine will float to the sides.
Pour a line of blackberry pie filling down the middle of batter; batter will bake around filling.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: cheesy potato skins
directions: Scrub potatoes thoroughly and rub skins with oil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Let potatoes cool to touch.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Carefully scoop out pulp, leaving 1/4 to 1/8-inch shell.
(Pulp may be reserved for mashed potatoes or reserved for another recipe.)
Cut shells in half crosswise and deep fry in hot oil (375°) for 2 minutes or until lightly browned. Drain on paper towels.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook
vegetables
about ten minutes, drain and mix with other ingredients.
Cover with buttered cracker crumbs.
Cook in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Mix like most any cake.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: pecan cake
directions: Mix together and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 250° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Cool in pans.
Makes one angel food cake pan and one loaf or 3 loaf pans.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Heat strawberries with gelatin to dissolve.
Set aside to cool. Mix milk with pudding.
Line pan with wafers.
Over wafers, spread on vanilla pudding, then strawberry mixture, then sour cream and then Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until set.

title: mcfarlain's corn bread
directions: Cream sugar, margarine, eggs and honey.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Alternate dry ingredients and milk, batter will be lumpy, do not over mix.
Pour batter in greased baking pan (11x14). Bake at 325-350 for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: jane's poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar.
Add onion juice and stir.
Pour in mixing bowl and add oil slowly, beating constantly, until thick.
Add poppy seed and beat a few more minutes.

title: old fashioned egg custard(<2 g. carbs)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix first 4 ingredients well. Pour into buttered dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Serve warm or cold.

title: kraut and eggs
directions: Heat bacon grease in frying pan.
Add kraut and cook for about 15 minutes.
Pour eggs over kraut and stir well.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until eggs are done.

title: harvard beets
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; slowly stir in vinegar.
Add butter and minced onions.
Over medium heat, cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to low, add beets and cook until heated.

title: sante fe mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms; remove center portions.
Mix Cheddar cheese, sour cream, onions, parsley and chilies together.
Stuff mixture into center of each mushrooms.
Melt butter with garlic and brush onto mushroom caps.
Sprinkle each mushroom with Parmesan cheese and broil until bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Beat butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Mix in vanilla and slightly cooled chocolate.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 3 minutes after each addition.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill thoroughly.
Top with whipped cream and nuts before serving. Serves 8 to 10.

title: fooj(fudge)
directions: Mix all in pan, cook over low heat until oleo melts.
Increase heat slightly, cook to soft ball stage.
Use electric mixer and beat until starts to thicken, pour into buttered pan.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and put into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with remaining 1/4 cup melted butter and crushed stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Either chunk or shredded hash browns can be used.

title: brandied peaches
directions: Drain peaches and reserve 1 cup juice.
Mix sugar with the reserved peach juice and boil until reduced to half of the original quantity.
Cool.
Measure and stir in equal amount of brandy, approximately 1/2 cup, and almond extract.
Pour brandy syrup over peaches and serve.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: swiss corn bake
directions: Cook corn and drain well.
Combine corn, milk, egg, onion, salt and 3/4 cup cheese.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart greased baking dish.
Toss bread crumbs with margarine and 1/4 cup cheese. Sprinkle over corn mixture.
Bake in moderate oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with green pepper rings, if desired.

title: gay's vegetable soup with meat
directions: Cook together ground meat and onion.
Drain meat.
Add sliced carrots, potatoes, tomatoes, tomato sauce and broth.
Cook until vegetables are done, then add other vegetables of your choice. Slightly salt and add black pepper.

title: clear lemon filling
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Chill.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onion in butter; add vinegar, sugar, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, catsup, water, salt, pepper and honey. Simmer about 10 minutes.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Combine milk, margarine, sugar and cocoa in a pan over low heat.
Cook until ingredients come to a rolling boil; cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal, coconut and/or nuts.
Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: stuffed squash cooked in yogurt
directions: Cook bones with about 6 cups water to make broth.
Wash, stem and scoop out squash, leaving sides about 1/8-inch thick.
Rinse out squash and stuff with the filling.
Place squash in pot and strain broth over them, reserving 1 cup broth for yogurt sauce. Steam for about 15 minutes.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.
Cut in squares to serve. Very good!

title: nut puffs
directions: Mix above ingredients well. Roll into small balls.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes. Remove from oven and roll into powdered sugar while still warm.

title: bean pot
directions: Cover beans with 1 quart water; bring to boil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat and simmer.
Cook slowly until done. Check to be sure there is plenty of water.
Can be cooked in crock-pot.
When done, soup should be very thick.

title: mattie coley's sweet potato pie
directions: Beat egg.
Add brown sugar, flour and spices.
Blend in sweet potatoes or pumpkin.
Add milk.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: corn flakes macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites until light.
Add vanilla; dribble in sugar and beat until very thick.
Mix corn flakes, nuts and coconut; fold into egg mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on a well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake for about 15 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: greek style hummus
directions: Combine ingredients, except bread, cucumber and zucchini, in food processor or blender on high until smooth.
Spoon into serving bowl.
Serve with bread and veggies.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: baked beans
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, salt and flour.
Beat mixture until fluffy.
Pour pineapple into mixture and blend.
Place in a greased 2-quart casserole.
You may stop here and refrigerate.
When ready to bake, place cubed bread on top in geometric pattern.
Slice butter and place butter on top of bread.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Sift together and add to creamed mixture the flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Bake in an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan at 350°.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix melted oleo and pretzels, and press into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: lemon-poppy bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat 4 minutes.
Pour into 3 small loaf pans and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes (check with cake tester).

title: black and white cheesecake bites
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

title: stuffed hamburgers
directions: Combine.
Shape into 8 flat patties.
Spread 4 patties with about 1 teaspoon mustard.
Cover with remaining patties.
Pinch together with wet hands.

title: cold bread pudding
directions: Break cold biscuits in pieces and place in mixing bowl with sugar, milk and melted butter.
Add the flavoring of your choice. Be sure bread is real soft.
Place in baking dish or skillet. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve with sauce if desired.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix grated cheese and flour.
Add shallots, celery, garlic, parsley, red pepper sauce and dry seasonings.
Stir to mix.
Add cream and eggs.
Stir to mix.
Add crumbled bacon, mushrooms and spinach.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 45 to 55 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: snow capped strawberries
directions: Wash strawberries; leave tops on.
Melt chocolate.
Dip berries into chocolate (1/2 of berry only).
Stack in cone shape.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix ingredients well, roll into balls and let stand in refrigerator until firm (about 6 hours or put in freezer for 2 hours).

title: quick chicken a la king
directions: Bone and remove skin from chicken.
Cut into strips.
Preheat skillet to 350°.
Add margarine.
When margarine is hot, add chicken and onion.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Add soup, milk and pimiento.
Cover and simmer 3 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serve chicken over waffles or rice.

title: nine flavor cake
directions: Combine butter, sugar and oil until light and fluffy.
Add all flavorings.
Beat eggs until light and lemon colored.
Add to mixture.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Spoon mixture into greased and floured 10 inch tube pan.
Bake 325° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: zesty squash(microwave recipe)
directions: Place margarine and garlic into 2-quart casserole dish. Microwave on High (100%) until margarine is melted (1 to 1 1/2 minutes).
Mix in oregano, basil, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients, except tomato.
Toss to coat.
Cover and microwave on High (100%) until squash is tender, 8 to 10 minutes, stirring after the cooking time.
Stir in tomato.
Cover and let stand 2 minutes.

title: spaghetti bravissimo
directions: In a large saucepan, combine soup mix and spaghetti with water.
Cook 20 minutes or until spaghetti is tender.
Do not drain!
In a large skillet, brown meat.
Stir in tomato sauce and paste, parsley, oregano and basil.
Add to spaghetti and heat through.
Great for fixing after work!

title: heath candy
directions: Heat butter, sugar, water and vanilla in saucepan until golden brown.
Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Place Hershey bars on top of candy while still hot.
Spread chocolate bars when soft.

title: taco casserole
directions: Mix beef, onion, soup, taco seasoning, chili powder and garlic salt together.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, mixture, chips and cheese.
Repeat layers and bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: hot curried fruit* * * * *
directions: Our oldest son was engaged to an English girl for some time and she gave me this recipe.
The English do like their tomatoes for breakfast.
She also gave me a recipe for Yorkshire Pudding, but for the life of me, I have never been able to make them as light as she did.

title: popover pizza
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain.
Stir in sauce mix, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and oil until foamy.
Beat in flour and salt until batter is smooth.
Pour over filling and cover.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Grease muffin tins or an iron skillet. Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.

title: school teacher's pie
directions: Beat egg whites, add cream of tartar and beat until stiff; add sugar and vanilla.
Fold in crackers and nuts.
Pour into ungreased pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Use no milk.
Combine creamed corn, slightly beaten eggs and salt.
Add Rice Krispies and the butter.
Pour into well-greased casserole or baking dish and bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients listed well.
Place in casserole dish. Mix 1 small Pepperidge Farm dressing and 1/4 cup melted margarine. Sprinkle on top of cabbage mixture. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large bowl; set aside.
Combine sugar, peanut butter and oil in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until sugar melts.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter morsels, stirring until morsels melt.
Add to oat mixture, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Drop by rounded teaspoons on wax paper.
Chill about 30 minutes or until set.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine ingredients in ovenproof bowl.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over the top and bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix cornstarch together with juice in pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir over medium heat until thick.
Add more liquid, if necessary to thin or more cornstarch to thicken.
May be made ahead and frozen.

title: fruit punch
directions: Finish with enough water to make 1 gallon.

title: cheese-potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes (unpeeled) and cool.
Skin and dice.
Pour melted oleo over potatoes.
Mix in other ingredients.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Mix occasionally and add more milk if needed.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend cheese, marshmallow cream and sugar.
Keep refrigerated.
Good served with any kind of fruit such as apple slices, bananas, grapes, pineapple chunks, strawberries, melons, etc.

title: lemon tart
directions: Cream shortening in cake mix.
Add eggs and water; mix well. Add coconut and nuts.
Press in greased pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
While cake is hot make up lemon pie filling. Pour over cake.
Cool.
Cover with whipped topping or Cool Whip.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash and stem strawberries.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in pan; pour boiling water over this and cook.
Stir until clear and thick.
Remove from heat and add 2 tablespoons strawberry jello. Pour over strawberries in pie crust.

title: eric's peanut brittle
directions: In a heavy skillet, over low heat, put white sugar.
Stir slowly while melting.
When liquid, take off fire and add butter and soda.
Stir until bubbling stops.
Butter well an 8 or 9-inch pan.
Pour the peanuts.
Pour hot syrup over platter or pan.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugars in bowl until light and fluffy.
Add beaten eggs; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together except soda. Dissolve soda in milk.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with dry ingredients, beating well after each addition.
Stir in enough orange juice to make soft dough.
Roll to desired thickness on floured surface.
Cut as desired.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Cool on wire rack.
Store in airtight container.
Yield:
about 7 dozen 3-inch tea cakes.

title: shrimp toastetts
directions: In a medium bowl, combine the shrimp, green onions, water chestnuts, sherry, salt, sugar, black pepper and cornstarch.
Mix well.
Add the beaten egg and mix.
Allow the mixture to set for at least 30 minutes.

title: texas fruit cake
directions: Heat oven to 225°.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan.
Line bottom of pan with 2 layers of greased brown paper.
Cream margarine and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift 4 cups flour with baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with orange juice.
Mix pecans, cherries and coconut with 1/4 cup flour.
Fold into batter.
Spoon batter into prepared pan.
Bake 4 hours. Remove from oven.
Cool in pan at least 2 hours.
Remove from pan; cool thoroughly.
For easier slicing, wrap and store in refrigerator.

title: olive spread
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until it's soft. Mash with a fork and add mayonnaise.
Chop up pecans until you have 1/2 cup.
Chop up one cup of olives.
Put them in your bowl and add olive juice with a dash of pepper.
No salt!
Stir well. This will be mushy, but it's supposed to be that way.
Put this in a pint jar and refrigerate for at least 24 to 48 hours.
It will thicken.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Boil and mash potatoes; season to taste.
Place in casserole. Brown ground beef; season to taste.
Place over potatoes.
Top with the chopped bell pepper and onion over beef.
Spread cheese over this; bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: chocolate cake with salad dressing
directions: Mix sugar, vanilla and salad dressing together.
Add cocoa, salt and flour (which has been sifted together 3 times) alternately with hot water.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and meal.
Add eggs, milk, vinegar, lemon juice and flavoring.
Add melted butter.
Bake in an unbaked crust at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together. Put in the crust. Drain juice off pineapple. Pour on it. Put bananas and Cool Whip on last.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients; mix until everything is same color. Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° until brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 4 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: sweet 'n sour salad
directions: Mix
well and chill thoroughly.
This salad keeps well. The sweet
and sour flavor goes well with grilled pork chops, hamburgers, hot dogs and also pintos.
May add hot peppers.

title: ham and cheese spread
directions: Combine 5 ounce jar sharp process Old English cheese and 1/2 cup butter in a mixer.
Then combine cream cheese (softened) and deviled ham with catsup.
Mix.

title: meat vegetable dish
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender, in clear salted water.
Drain. Slice onion and cook slowly in butter.
Add hamburger and cook on medium heat for 5 minutes, then add cooked spaghetti, tomato soup and seasoning.
Cook 30 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Prepare roux:
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in small saucepan; stir in flour.
Cook over low heat 3 minutes.
Stir constantly. Cool.

title: sausage surprise
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese (mixed well) in a greased casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: pineapple torte
directions: Pour crushed pineapple into pie crust, then add walnuts.
Cook marshmallows over double boiler until melted.
Pour immediately into pie crust over pineapple and walnuts.
Top with whipping cream.
Cover with inverted plastic lid and put into freezer until hard.
Delicious!!!
Serves 6.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken in oil and butter; remove.
In same pan, put the brown rice, white rice and recommended amount of water.
Put onion soup in and stir all together.
Place chicken, skin side down, on top of rice and bake, uncovered, for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: egg enchiladas(for lent or anytime)
directions: In saucepan, steam onions in small amount of water.
In large, flat pan, pour half of enchilada sauce.
Fry tortillas briefly in small amount of oil.
Then turn tortillas in enchilada sauce and place 1 tablespoon onions, 2 olives, 1 tablespoon eggs and 2 tablespoons cheese in tortillas.
Roll and place filled tortillas in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Continue until all tortillas are filled.
May fill another 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pour remaining enchilada sauce over tortillas and cover with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter easter egg
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well. Gently stir in cereal. Shape into eggs. Chill. Dip in chocolate or colored coating.
Decorate.

title: vanilla peanut butter supremes
directions: Spread peanut butter between 2 saltines as to make a sandwich. Melt chocolate in microwave. Dip saltine sandwich in chocolate. Cool until set.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Combine sugar, baking soda, buttermilk and salt in a heavy 4-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat to 210° (about 5 minutes), stirring constantly.
Add butter, syrup and pecans. Continue stirring until candy reaches 234° (soft ball stage), about 5 minutes more, stirring constantly.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Grease a pizza pan.
Press crescent roll dough into pan. Sprinkle cooked sausage over dough, then eggs that are cooked. Sprinkle grated cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except egg whites. Pour in pot and cook until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Let cool and pour into baked pie shell. Beat egg whites until stiff and add 6 tablespoons sugar. Beat until it peaks. Put in oven to brown.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer all in the order listed.
Cover and refrigerate.
Stir when ready to serve.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Prepare package of Uncle Ben's rice according to directions. Set aside. Brown sausage.
Saute in a little pork grease (sometimes you must add a little butter) the green pepper, onion, celery and mushrooms until tender.
Mix with the sausage and add sour cream.
Heat through on top of stove or put in a greased casserole dish and bake, covered, until heated.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar and salt; continue beating.
Fold in milk, cream, flavoring and, if you like, 1 1/2 to 2 cups sweetened peaches or strawberries.
Omit flavoring if you use fruit.

title: mother's chinese chews
directions: Mix ingredients and pour in a greased and floured pan and bake 17 minutes at 350°.

title: greek beef stew
directions: Blanch onions in boiling water for 1 minute; drain and peel. In a kettle, melt the 1/2 stick butter over moderate heat, add the beef and toss to coat it with the butter, but do not let it brown. Add the wine, the stock, the tomato paste, the vinegar, the sugar, the cumin, the garlic, the allspice, the bay leaf and salt and pepper to taste; bring the mixture to a boil and simmer the stew, covered, for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Add the onions and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned sweet potato pie
directions: Combine potatoes and butter. Mix well. Blend in sugar, eggs, nutmeg and vanilla.
Stir in milk. Mix well.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; let stand in
hot
water while bringing to a boil the vinegar, water and salt.
Pack
hot cucumbers in jars with dill.	Fill jars with vinegar mixture.
Seal.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Sift together the flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder. Rub in the butter, then add the Sourdough Starter and mix.
Turn dough onto a lightly floured board; knead lightly until satiny. Roll dough 1/2-inch thick, then cut with a floured cutter.
Place biscuits on a well-greased pan; brush tops with soft lard.
Let rise for 1 hour in a warm place.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) until brown.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy; gradually add sugar.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until center is firm.
Cool and serve with ice cream or whipped topping, if desired.

title: polenta (soft)
directions: Fill pan 1/2 full of water.
Let come to a full boil.
In a bowl, add water to the cornmeal (small amount at a time).
Mix, then add to boiling water.
Cook 30 minutes, covered.

title: eli slocomb's smoky black bean soup
directions: Cook 12 minutes or more the bacon, onion and celery in large pan until bacon is done.
Stir in beans, broth, bay leaf and 1 1/4 cups water.
Lower heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Discard bay leaf.
Remove 2 cups of the solid food and puree the remainder of the dish, then return all ingredients to stove.
Season with pepper and Cajun seasoning.
Add more broth to this if necessary.
Serve with salad and rolls.
Serves 4.

title: corned beef stew
directions: Cut meat in cubes.
In a Dutch oven cook onion, celery and pepper in oil until tender.
Add water, potatoes, tomatoes, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and bouillon granules and bring to boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in corned beef and cook 2 minutes more.

title: oriental chicken soup
directions: Up to 6 hours before mealtime, in a 1-quart casserole, stir together water, chicken, carrot, soy sauce, bouillon granules, red pepper and ginger.
Microcook, covered, on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until boiling, stirring once.
Spoon soup into a small vacuum bottle; seal.

title: good punch
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Then add 1-quart ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: aunt dot's favorite lemon sponge pie
directions: Line a 10-inch pie plate with pastry.
Separate eggs and beat the whites until they hold up in peaks.
Add about 1/4 cup of the sugar.
Cream the butter.
Add salt and remaining sugar.
Add unbeaten egg yolks; beat well.
Add the flour, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Add milk, then fold in beaten whites.
Pour into unbaked pastry.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°; continue to bake for 25 minutes.
Place pie on rack to cool. Serves 6.

title: mom's coconut cream pie
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt. Gradually add enough milk to make a thick paste. Add egg yolks and beat until smooth. Add remaining milk and stir until smooth. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick. Add vanilla, butter and coconut. Mix and pour into baked pie shell. In another bowl: beat egg whites until foamy, add a dash of salt and continue beating. Add 1 tbsp. sugar for each egg white. Beat until stiff peaks form. Pour onto pie and spread to edge of pie. Sprinkle with coconut and bake at 275 degree oven until golden brown.

title: skillet spaghetti
directions: Combine first
7 ingredients, 3 cups water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Bring to boil.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes; stir often.
Add spaghetti; simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Stir often.
Serve with cheese.
Makes 7 servings.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix well the oil, sugar, pineapple, flavoring, salt and eggs. Add bananas and nuts.
Mix in flour gradually.
Stir until smooth (do not beat).
Grease 3 single pans and flour lightly.
Add mixture and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Use cream cheese icing.

title: steak roll
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix dressing on steak that has been lightly sprinkled with salt, pepper and garlic.
Roll like jelly roll and secure with toothpicks.
Place in pan and cover with cream of mushroom soup.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until steak is tender.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix together. Pour into muffin tins. Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes. Makes 6.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies; reserve 1/2 cup.
Mix remaining crumbs with margarine and press into 9 x 13-inch container.
Refrigerate 1 hour (or freeze) until set.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk and mix well.
Drop batter onto baking sheet.

title: peach and lemon punch
directions: Put peach slices in bowl; sprinkle with sugar and let sit 30 minutes.
Pour sherry over peaches and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Pour lemon juice and ginger ale over fruit.
Serve over ice in punch bowl.
Garnish with mint leaves and fresh flowers. Makes about 15 four ounce servings.

title: chewy fudge squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 3-inch pan.
Stir cake mix, eggs and butter with mixture until well blended (batter will be stiff).
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Spread batter in pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool, then cut into squares.

title: cheddar-broccoli quiche
directions: Toss the cheese with the flour.
Add the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour this into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mom's apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt the margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour until particles are like fine crumbs.
Add milk and stir with a fork until dough leaves the sides of the bowl.
Turn out on lightly floured board; knead just until smooth.
Roll dough out into a large rectangle about 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle apples or fruit evenly over the dough. Roll up dough like a jelly roll.
Dampen the edges of the dough with a little water and seal.
Slice dough into about 16 slices, 1/2 inch thick.
Place in pan with melted margarine.
Pour sugar syrup carefully around rolls.
(This looks like too much liquid, but the crust will absorb it.)
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Combine all ingredients and put into large casserole dish. Cover and bake 1 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally (every 15-20 minutes) in 350° oven.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt the margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine the corn, onion, sugar, eggs, salt, pepper, water and cornbread mix in a bowl; mix well.
Spoon into the prepared baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
May serve as a main dish by adding 1 pound browned ground beef before baking.
Yields 10 servings.

title: recipe for making a happy home
directions: Take friendship and add thoughtfulness.
Mix well together with a pinch of powdered tenderness, lightly beaten into a bowl of loyalty to which has been added faith, hope and charity.
Be sure to add gaiety that sings and the ability to laugh at little things.
Moisten with sudden tears of heartfelt sympathy.
Bake in a good natured pan.
Serve often.

title: chicken-rice purlo
directions: Saute onion in	bacon
drippings until tender.	Add cut up chicken and
seven	cups
water.
Add
salt and pepper.
(I like my purlo hot with pepper.) Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer until done, about 1 1/2 hours.
Debone chicken, measure out 4 cups broth.
Return
to	boil
and
add rice and chopped eggs.
Cook, covered,
until
grains
are tender and liquid is absorbed, about 25	to 30 minutes.	Other meats or seafood may be substituted for the
chicken.
(As	a
child I thought the whole world ate purlo for Sunday dinner.)

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: beef moussaka
directions: Brown meat with the onion and drain.
Stir in parsley, salt, pepper, nutmeg, tomato sauce and wine.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pare eggplant and cut into slices. Arrange half the eggplant in a baking dish.
Cover with the half the meat mixture.
Repeat layers.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until tender.
Beat together eggs, milk and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Pour over hot casserole and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake uncovered until custard is set, 10 to 15 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes, then cut into squares.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Blenderize all ingredients for 1 minute.
Pour or spoon onto heated griddle.
Turn once.
Serve with powdered sugar or your favorite fruit topping.
Makes 20 small (6-inch) pancakes.

title: touch of apple chicken salad
directions: In saucepan, simmer apple juice and lemon peel, covered, for about 45 minutes or until fork-tender.
Remove chicken and cool; reserve broth.
Add raisins to broth and let stand 20 minutes. Remove chicken meat from bones; discard bones and skin.
Chop chicken coarsely.
Place in large bowl.
Drain raisins and mix with chicken.
Add onion, bean sprouts, pecans, mayonnaise, olives and pepper relish.
Stir to mix well.
Chill.

title: albacore fettucine
directions: Bring large pot of water to a boil.
Cook broccoli until crisp-tender; remove with slotted spoon and place in serving bowl. Add fettucine to same pot of boiling water and cook until tender. Drain and add to broccoli.
Mix in tuna.
Combine remaining ingredients and cook in same pot, stirring, until sauce is smooth and heated through.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over pasta mixture and toss.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: fudge brownies
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter and chocolate.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar.
Blend in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla. Stir in flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Spread in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 16 squares.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Beat eggs well. Add sugar, butter, oil and vanilla and beat well. Stir in chopped apples, flour, nuts, salt, soda and cinnamon. Mix well. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes for tube pan. May also be baked in pint wide mouth jars or any size loaf pans. Adjust time for other containers but keep temperature the same. If using jars, wipe rim and place lids on as soon as you take them out of the oven.

title: oven-fried fish
directions: Mix mustard and water.
Line shallow pan with foil.
Spray with Pam.
Cut fish into 1-inch pieces and dip in mustard mixture.
Roll in corn meal.
Place in pan slightly apart.
Spray fish with Pam. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Then turn on broil for 5 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix vegetables together.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: chili con queso
directions: Layer all ingredients in order, ending with cheese.
Sprinkle with chili powder.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbling gently.
Cool slightly and serve with chips.

title: vanilla drops
directions: Heat oven to 375° (moderate).
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Swirl confectioners sugar frosting on top of each cookie.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: fresh strawberries and angel food cake
directions: Wash the strawberries and remove the stems.
Place in a large bowl.
Add the sugar on top.
Refrigerate mixture for 2 days until the strawberries form their own syrup.
Remove strawberries.

title: fresh kosher style dill pickles
directions: Wash the cucumbers. Make a brine of the vinegar, water and salt. Bring to a boil. Place a generous layer of dill, 1/2 to 1 clove garlic slice and 1/2 teaspoon of mustard seed in bottom of each clean quart jar. Pack the cucumbers into the jars. When the jars are half filled with cucumbers, add another layer of dill. Finish packing the jars. Fill the jars to within 1/2-inch of the top with the boiling brine. Put jar lids on and hand tighten. Process for 5 minutes in large canner of boiling water. Take out and let cool, sealing the jars. Best set for a few weeks before using to get the flavors.

title: dill bread
directions: In large bowl, mix 1 cup flour, sugar, onion, dill seed, soda and yeast.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix white sugar and cinnamon in large plastic bag. Cut biscuits in one quarter pieces, drop into bag and shake to coat. Place in a greased pan. Boil brown sugar, butter and pecans for 2 minutes, pour over biscuits, bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Turn out onto a plate to cool; syrup will continue to run down sides as bread cools.

title: chicken cordon blue
directions: You will need 6 toothpicks.

title: chicken and rice with yoshida sauce
directions: Brown chicken in a small amount of oil.
Add Yoshida sauce; cover with lid and simmer until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken to a plate.
Add 1 cup raw rice to Yoshida sauce, plus water.
Put chicken on top of this, cover with lid and simmer about 25 minutes, until rice is done.

title: chicken salad deluxe
directions: Combine salad dressing, mayonnaise, half and half, seasoning, salt and pepper in a small bowl.
Blend well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight to blend flavors.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend soups together; add milk until smooth.
Then add rice and pour into bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and spread evenly.
Place raw chicken over the rice mixture and sprinkle the onion soup mix over the chicken.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 2 hours.
