title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar and fruit cocktail; beat.
Add flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix well.
Pour in lightly greased 8 x 13-inch pan.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease a baking sheet.
Cream butter, vanilla and sugar until soft.
Add flour and nuts.
Roll into small balls.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
When done, roll balls in confectioners sugar while still hot.

title: janet's fettucine primavera
directions: In large skillet, saute chicken and onion in hot oil until chicken is no longer pink.
Add vegetables and saute 2 minutes longer.
Add spaghetti sauce and shrimp.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes or until shrimp turns pink and chicken is cooked through. Stir in spinach and let cook 3 to 5 minutes longer.
Serve over hot, cooked fettucine and top with Provolone.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
The shrimp may be cooked first and then put in at the end.

title: mile high pie
directions: Mix frozen strawberries, sugar, egg whites and 1 tablespoon lemon juice together.
Beat for 15 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle with crumbs.

title: chilled asparagus in dill mustard sauce
directions: Steam asparagus tender.
Run under cold water.
Mix ingredients.
Pour over cold asparagus.

title: sugar-free banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with skim milk.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip. Layer with vanilla wafers and banana slices.

title: cranberry walnut relish
directions: Wash cranberries and drain.
In shallow pan, stir cranberries with sugar.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Spread walnuts in separate pan.
Toast in oven until light golden brown, about 12 minutes.
Stir together baked cranberries, walnuts, marmalade and juice until well mixed.
Chill.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Grease casserole with butter or margarine.
Add defrosted broccoli.
Top with 1 cup rice.
Saute onion in butter.
Pour on top of rice.
Add milk and water mixture.
Top with sliced or shredded cheese.
Pour soup over all.
Top with bread crumbs and a little butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: split pea soup(crock-pot)
directions: Cook ground pork and drain.
Put into crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook for 10 to 12 hours.
Um um um!

title: best coleslaw
directions: Shake or toss.
Cover and let stand 2 hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spread the potatoes in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix next 5 ingredients and spread over the potatoes.
Cover with crushed corn flakes.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 300° about 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: boiled spice cake
directions: Boil together first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Cool, then add remaining ingredients.
Grease, then flour baking pan (about 12 x 12-inch).
Pour batter into pan and bake at 300°.
Cook until done, approximately 30 minutes.
Good with or without icing.

title: breaded tomato slices
directions: Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Cut tomatoes in 3/4-inch thick slices.
Dip in cracker crumbs, then in egg mixture and again in crumbs.
Fry in hot oil until browned.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and cook over very low heat until cheese is melted. Makes 4 servings.

title: orange-date cake
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs.
Add orange rind and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with milk. Mix 1/2 cup flour with dates and pecans.
Fold into cake mixture. Turn into greased tube pan (I use 2 loaf pans).
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Blend ingredients together with 1/2 cup cold water in heavy saucepan and add 2 cups boiling water.
Stir and cook until thick and bubbly.
Cool and pour into large baked pie shell.

title: microwave fried apples
directions: Place butter or margarine in an 8-inch round dish and microwave for 1 minute or until melted.
Mix together sugar and spices.
Stir them into the butter.
Add the apple slices and toss to coat evenly.
Microwave on 100% power for 5 minutes until apples are cooked but still firm.

title: hot corned beef bunwiches
directions: Chop
up corned beef finely and add the next 4 ingredients. Mix
thoroughly
and spread on bun halves for open-face sandwiches. Wrap loosely in foil.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble bread in dish; shred cheese.
Brown, drain and crumble sausage in dish.
Beat eggs and milk and pour over other ingredients.
Then add mushroom soup and the 1/2 cup milk; pour over top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients. Beat egg with milk and add to flour mixture along with melted butter. Stir well. Spread batter in 9-inch pie plate and bake in 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly browned around edges. Serves 6.

title: white texas sheet cake
directions: Frost cake while still warm.

title: pineapple-lemon chicken
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine juice with garlic, cornstarch, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and rosemary.
Arrange chicken in shallow casserole dish, skin side up.
Sprinkle with salt.
Broil until brown.
Stir sauce.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Arrange pineapple and lemon around chicken.
Spoon sauce over all.
Bake for 5 minutes longer.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lattice top chicken bake
directions: Combine soup, milk, salt, chicken, vegetables, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Spread in greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Bake uncovered at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown meat with chopped onions; set aside.
Combine soup, chilies, sour cream and salt.
Stir well.
Add browned meat and onion mixture.
Fill each tortilla with 1 1/2 tablespoons sauce and a spoon of cheese.
Roll up and place in 13 x 9-inch baking pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Spoon extra sauce over top and sprinkle with any extra cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
May be prepared a day ahead and kept refrigerated.

title: carmen's ratatouille
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil in large pot.
Saute until light brown.
Add zucchini and green pepper; cook over medium heat 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except macaroni.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes. Add to soup; simmer 5 minutes more.
Serve hot.
Rye breads go very well with this.

title: party potatoes
directions: Stir butter into hot potatoes. Whip cream cheese with sour cream until it is smooth. Stir this into mashed potatoes along with salt and pepper. Spoon into buttered casserole. Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Put 7-Up and berries in bowl.
Add sherbet.

title: peach salad
directions: Drain and dice peaches.
Combine all ingredients and chill for 1/2 hour.

title: sausage bread
directions: In frying pan, cook sausage and onion until sausage is browned.
Beat together eggs and pour into pan with sausage.
Cook eggs loosely.
Turn heat off and cool mixture.
Pinch together all of the crescent rolls to form a rectangle.
Place on a baking sheet.
Put egg and sausage into middle of dough.
Sprinkle cheese over meat.
Pull up sides of dough and pinch together to close over meat.
Close up ends and bake at 350° until bread is browned, approximately 20 minutes.

title: spanish casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and salt. Add enchilada sauce and water mixed with soup and green chilies. Simmer for 30 minutes. In a large 13 x 9-inch casserole or pan, grease and line bottom with 6 tortillas. Cover with half of the meat mixture. Sprinkle half of the grated cheese on top. Continue second layer, topping with remaining cheese. Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until mixture is bubbly.

title: warm potato salad
directions: Boil the potatoes in their jackets.
Peel and slice fine in large salad bowl.
Saute the onions in shortening, being careful not to let them burn.
Add a little hot water and boil until tender.
Then add salt, sugar and vinegar and heat well.
Pour dressing over the potatoes.
Add chopped, hard-boiled eggs, if desired, to add flavor and nutritional value.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Remove from heat and add all remaining ingredients and stir.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: spaghetti with oil and garlic
directions: Bring a large pot of salted water to boil and cook the spaghetti until al dente.
Drain.

title: chicken, pasta and vegetables
directions: Cut chicken and brown in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add soup, water and vegetable combination.
Heat to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat until tender, about 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cheese nut balls(nonmeat entree)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into patties or balls.
Cover with tomato soup or mushroom soup.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: picnic chicken
directions: Combine egg and milk in shallow bowl.
Mix lightly.
Combine spaghetti sauce mix, flour and cheese; mix well.
Put chicken pieces in egg mixture and then in spaghetti sauce mixture.
Fry in hot oil in a large skillet for about 10 minutes, turning to brown evenly. Cover and cook for 20 to 30 minutes longer or until tender.
Chill and serve cold.

title: cauliflower or broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp pate
directions: Drain and mash shrimp with a potato masher.
Add the onion. Melt the butter and pour over the shrimp and mix well.
Add lemon juice, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
This should be a rather thick paste.
Pack firmly into a 3-cup mold.
Chill several hours until firm.
Turn it out onto serving plate.
Serve with crackers.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Crumble ground beef in bowl.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Add chopped onion.
Toss all with fingers.
Add rice only from Rice-A-Roni.
Toss again.
Form into quarter-size balls. Brown these in skillet in margarine all at the same time, turning once (about 5 minutes on each side).
Drain off grease.
Sprinkle seasoning mix from Rice-A-Roni over meat balls.
Add 3 cups hot water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, cut down to low and cook for 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon swirl raisin bread
directions: Place warm water, yeast and sugar in a bowl and let bubble. Place in a large mixing bowl and mix well the flour, sugar and salt.
While mixer is running, pour in yeast mixture and beat on medium speed for 3 or more minutes.
Add eggs, butter and raisins. Mix for 1 more minute.
Change to dough hook.
Add 3 cups more flour in 1/2 cup increments until dough clings to hook, but is not dry.
(This should take about 5 minutes.)
Place dough in greased bowl and grease top.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Punch down and let rise again about 30 minutes.
Turn out on floured surface and divide into 3 equal parts.
Flatten dough and sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar; roll up.
Grease top of loaf, cover and let rise until doubled.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring catsup, butter and Worcestershire sauce to a boil.
Add sugar, black pepper and lemon.
Cook until lemon pulps.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach; cool and drain.
Combine spinach and all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Form walnut-size balls and chill 2 hours.
Place spinach balls on greased cookie sheet and bake.
Good hot or cold.
Makes about 20.
Cooking Time: 18 minutes.
Temperature:
Servings:
Pan Size:
8 x 12-inch.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice
cookie
dough and arrange on pizza pan.	Cook as directed
on package.
(Cookie dough should merge together and form
a
crust.) Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together.
Spread on cooled crusts.
Use fruit of your choice (except pineapple).

title: orange molded salad
directions: Drain orange slices and pineapple, reserving juices. Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Cool slightly and add cream cheese.
Beat until well blended.
Let cool and add Cool Whip and 1/2 cup combined juices.
Beat until light.
Fold in orange slices and crushed pineapple.
Let set in refrigerator, stirring occasionally until like egg white.	Pour into mold and refrigerate overnight.

title: egg potato pie
directions: Brown sausage in a skillet.
Fry potatoes in same skillet. Mix eggs and cheese in a bowl.
Pour eggs and cheese over potatoes and sausage.
Do not mix.
Cover; cook on medium/low heat until eggs are done.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: quick crunchy chicken
directions: Cook chicken and chop.
Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Can add a topping of 1 cup crushed potato chips.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick of margarine and 2 cups of graham cracker crumbs. Press in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat 2 eggs, 2 sticks margarine and 2 cups of powdered sugar for 15 minutes with mixer.
Spread over crust.
Cover with sliced bananas, crushed pineapple and then Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: budceyes(candy)
directions: Combine softened butter, peanut butter and powdered sugar. Mix thoroughly.
Roll into 1/2-inch balls and chill.
In double boiler, melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls, using toothpicks, into chocolate mixture.
Place on waxed paper to allow to harden.

title: shrimp victoria
directions: Peel and clean shrimp.
Saute shrimp and onion in oleo for 10 minutes or until shrimp are pink and tender.
Add mushrooms and cook for 5 minutes more.
Sprinkle in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in sour cream and cook gently for 10 minutes, not allowing mixture to boil.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sugared walnuts
directions: Cook sugar, honey and water to soft ball stage (very soft and droopy).
Remove from heat and add vanilla and walnuts.
Stir until thick and creamy.
Turn out on wax paper and separate quickly with a fork.

title: heavenly peach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put fruit on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle all of jello over fruit.
Sprinkle all of cake mix over fruit. Dollop thin pieces of butter over top of cake mix.
Pour all of water on top of cake mix and butter.
Bake for 1 hour or until done.
(I always add a bit more fruit than the recipe calls for.) The following fruits are also good:
red tart cherries with cherry jello and blackberries with blackberry jello.
Strawberries and blueberries get too mushy when cooked, but you can try them if you wish.
Use corresponding jello with fruit.

title: hot and spicy cinnamon sauce for apple dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients together in saucepan over medium heat. Bring to a boil, stirring.
Serve warm over apple dumplings.
Makes 2/3 cup, for 6 to 8 dumplings.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Slice and marinate hot dogs in bourbon.
Stir occasionally. Let set 24 hours.
Drain off bourbon and throw away?
Put hot dogs in casserole and pour catsup and brown sugar over.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix together margarine, flour and pecans.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350° until golden brown. Let cool.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: To melted oleo add sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla and soda.
Mix in flour and salt, then add chips and nuts.
Bake in 375° to 400° oven.
Do not overbake.

title: fried rice luncheon
directions: Stir-fry in oil the egg, celery and diced meat.
Add bean sprouts.
Serve over prepared rice with soy sauce to taste. Serves 4.

title: little clam bake
directions: Soften cheese.	Drain clams and add to cheese.	Add Worcestershire sauce and mix well.	Store in refrigerator (covered).	Just before serving, spread 1 teaspoon mixture on crackers.
Sprinkle with paprika and place on large cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for about 5 minutes.

title: electric skillet chicken
directions: Rub salt, garlic salt and pepper onto fryer.
Place cut up chicken into electric skillet.
Mix together the first 3 ingredients and pour over chicken; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer until meat leaves bone and sauce is very thick.
Turn occasionally.

title: egg drop soup
directions: In a large saucepan, dissolve bouillon in hot water. Mix cornstarch with a small amount of water and stir into bouillon. Add soy sauce, vinegar and green onion. Bring to a boil, then simmer, stirring occasionally. Gradually pour the beaten eggs into the saucepan while stirring. Serve at once.

title: goulash(weight watchers)
directions: In a large nonstick skillet combine all ingredients and mix well.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, until macaroni is done and tomatoes thickened.

title: chicken and pastry
directions: Cook chicken until done, take out to cool.
Put in cream of chicken soup and bring to boil.
Put pastry in 4 to 6 at a time. Let it cook, then put more until all is in.
Then put chicken back in pot.
Take chicken off the bone.
Salt and pepper to your taste.

title: sour dill pickles
directions: Wash small cucumbers and put in fruit jars with dill and garlic to taste.
Boil water, vinegar and salt until a good, rolling boil.
(Can boil jars with lids in water before sealing jars.)
Pour pickle brine over cucumbers and seal.

title: wassail(good hot punch for holidays.)
directions: Combine sugar and water.
Boil 10 minutes. Add spices.
Cover and let stand 1 hour in a warm place. Strain. Add juices and cider.
Serve warm.
Keeps warm well in crock-pot.

title: quick "pigs in the blanket"
directions: Chop cabbage into medium-size pieces and spread in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish (prefer glass; tomato and metal gets bitter taste).
Brown meat and onion, breaking up meat as it cooks.
Stir in rice, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture over cabbage.

title: sweet potato puff
directions: Cook potatoes until tender (15 to 20 minutes in microwave, 1 hour in preheated 450° oven or boiled 25 minutes).
Cool.
Peel. In large bowl, mash.
Add marmalade, sugar, orange juice and almond extract.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
In 2nd bowl, beat egg whites to stiff peaks.
Fold into potato mixture.
Coat a 6 cup casserole with nonstick spray.
Add mixture.
Sprinkle with almonds, if desired.
Bake at 350° until puffy and set (about 40 minutes).
Serves 6.

title: sue's coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 20 minutes more.
Serves 8.

title: cajun style chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken in water until cooked thoroughly, set chicken aside to cool before separating.
Meanwhile bring 2 quarts water to a boil in a large pot. Add noodles and cook until tender. While noodles cook; saute mushrooms in about 1/4 stick of
butter, do not drain butter sauce off of mushrooms. When
noodles are tender, drain all but about 1/4 of the water off.
Add all ingredients and stir until cheese is melted. Makes about 8 servings.

title: calico bean bake
directions: Brown the hamburger and onion together.
Drain and add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover with foil while baking.

title: lamb kabobs and cucumber with yogurt sauce
directions: Combine lamb with remaining ingredients, except rice.
Preheat broiler to high.
When ready to broil, divide lamb among 4 skewers.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat source, turning to cook evenly, about 10 minutes.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet crisp pickles
directions: Cover whole cucumbers
in salt water.
Let stand for 10 days. Take out cucumbers
and cut.
Put in clear water for 24 hours. Take out and put in alum water.
Heat to warm on stove for 2 hours,
just
covered in alum water.
Stir occasionally. Take from hot water and chill in ice water.

title: fudge or choco-pound cake
directions: Cream
oleo or butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Keep
this separate.
Mix well remaining ingredients into a
paste
and pour with the first ingredients.
Mix well and add flour.
Add walnuts and mix well.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, then bake 15 minutes at 300°.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Boil chicken for 20 minutes.
Remove skin and bones.
Arrange in a 3-quart oblong baking dish.
Mix sour cream and soups.
Pour over the chicken.
Mix poppy seed and cracker crumbs; sprinkle over the top.
Drizzle the margarine over all.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain bacon, reserving 3 tablespoons drippings in pan.
Set bacon aside.
Add chopped potato, onion, carrot and celery to bacon drippings.
Cook over low heat about 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in the milk, salt and pepper.
Bring mixture to boil.
Stir together sour cream, flour and paprika. Gradually stir about 1 cup of the hot mixture into sour cream mixture.
Return to remaining hot mixture in saucepan.
Cook and stir just until mixture bubbles.
Top with bacon pieces.
Serve immediately.

title: fastnacht kuecheles
directions: In a large bowl, mix about 1 1/2 cups flour, dry yeast, salt and sugar.
Heat milk and shortening in saucepan until lukewarm (shortening need not melt).
Add dry ingredients in mixer bowl and beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add egg and 1/2 cup more flour. Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough; knead lightly.
Cover bowl; let rise in warm place until double in bulk (about
1 hour).
Place dough on floured surface; knead.
Roll out 1/4 and 1/2-inch thick.
Cut in 2-inch squares.
Heat oil to 375° and fry squares.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and sour cream. Add all other ingredients. Chill and serve with chips.

title: super duper potatoes
directions: Heat butter, half and half, salt and cheese.
Stir until melted.
Mix in potatoes and bake in a 2-quart baking dish at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add sour cream and continue cooking for 15 minutes.
Garnish with bacon.

title: egg pies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Beat at slow speed, about 5 minutes.
Melt 2 1/2 sticks pure butter.
Heat oven at 350°, about 10 minutes before putting pies into oven.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or 1 hour.

title: pocketbook rolls
directions: Add butter, salt and sugar to boiling water.
Cool. Then add dissolved yeast cake.
Add sifted flour and set aside in a warm place to rise.
When double in bulk, add well beaten egg.
Knead lightly.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick on well floured board.
Cut with biscuit cutter, 3-inches around.
Crease with dull knife.
Brush with melted butter and fold over, pinching the dough on sides to make a pocket book. Brush tops with butter.
Let rise and bake on a cookie sheet in 390° oven about 20 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the margarine with sugar substitute.
Combine soda and applesauce; add to the margarine mixture.
Add all the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a nonstick 7 x 11-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
When cake is cool, cut into 15 equal slices.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix the Cool Whip, Eagle Brand and lemon juice.
Drain and chop oranges, pineapple and coconut.
Pour into pie shells.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: raw carrot salad
directions: Wash, scrape and grate the carrots on the downward stroke (coarse grater) or chip very fine.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichoke hearts into small chunks.
Mix all ingredients together (remember to squeeze chilies).
Sprinkle more shredded Parmesan cheese on top of dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: squash and apple bake
directions: Cut in half; clean and peel squash.
Slice in 1/2-inch slices.
Place in 11 x 7-inch baking pan.
Top with apple slices. Mix remaining ingredients together and sprinkle over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes in 350° oven until squash is tender.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Place all ingredients in a saucepan.
Cover; cook 25 minutes over medium heat.
Uncover; cook 20 minutes over medium heat.

title: apfelkuchen(apple cake)
directions: Combine flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, butter, salt and vanilla. Press into bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan, saving some crumbs for top. Boil apple slices in 1/4 cup water.
When partly done, add 1 cup granulated sugar and 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Pour over crust. Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti into fourths and boil according to directions. Drain and run under cold water until cool. Mix all together and chill.

title: seasoned crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients in Tupperware bowl.
Shake occasionally.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Do not cook until dry.
Add grated cheese until melted.
Add butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Continue stirring.
Cook at 350° until brown.
Take out of stove while mixture is still thin.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: The Dry Mix:
Sift together flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda and salt into large bowl.
Add fruit, carrots and nuts; stir well to combine.

title: herb roast chicken
directions: Mix together the rosemary, sage, thyme, cumin and salt in a bowl. Sprinkle over the chicken breasts and rub in, coating both sides. Broil or grill chicken until done.

title: ground beef and vegetable stew
directions: In Dutch oven, brown beef, breaking up pieces with fork or spoon.
Add onions, garlic, water, basil, salt, pepper, potatoes and carrots.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes and carrots are almost tender.
Add peppers and tomato sauce.
(I sometimes add chunks of zucchini at this time.)
Finish cooking until all vegetables are tender.
Serve with crusty bread or rolls.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pupusas
directions: Cheese, pork, tomatoes and bell peppers, grind them and mix together.
Then mix the margarine and the season of chicken and make the pupusa.
Cook it in a comal and wait for it to be ready and enjoy.

title: beef supreme
directions: Cut chuck roast into cubes.
Place beef cubes in casserole dish.
Mix soup and sherry.
Pour mixture over beef.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; salt and pepper to taste and refrigerate until well chilled.
Serve with chips or veggies.

title: mike's hummus
directions: Drain beans.
Process all ingredients in a blender or food processor until smooth.
Serve as a dip.
Can also be used as a condiment on sandwiches.

title: pizza cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (12-inch) pizza pans.
Combine 1/2 dry cake mix with water.
Add eggs, brown sugar and butter; mix well.
Add remaining cake mix and nuts.
Press mixture into pizza pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and sugar; add juice, egg yolks and milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in last. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at
for
minutes or until knife comes out clean and the top is crusty looking.

title: apple delights
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Prepare pastry for 9-inch two crust pie as directed on package, except; roll half of dough into 13 x 9-inch rectangle and place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Stir together pie filling and raisins; spread evenly over pastry to within 3/4-inch of edge.
Roll out remaining dough for top crust.
Place over filling.
Pinch edges together securely.
Cut slits in top to allow steam to escape.
Bake about 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: zucchini cobbler
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients in saucepan on top of stove over medium heat until it starts to thicken.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Crumble cake mix over zucchini mixture.
Top with chopped walnuts.
Cut margarine over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: wanda's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes, or until knife inserted in middle of pie comes out clean.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put cottage cheese in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs and stir; add broccoli.
Sprinkle cornstarch on top and mix well.
Add oleo and stir in half of the cheese.
Season with salt, pepper and onion.
Put in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake for 1 hour.

title: creamy pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving the juice in a small saucepan.
Set pineapple aside.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 1/3 cups; bring to a boil.
Place gelatin in a bowl; add boiling liquid and stir to dissolve.
Cool until slightly thickened.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350 for 20-30 minutes.

title: basic fritter batter
directions: Sift flour
and
salt together into a medium bowl.
Add the oil, egg and
water or enough to make a thick batter.
Dip vegetable of
your	choice	into
batter
and
deep
fry until golden.
If batter does not adhere to the vegetables, add 1 to 2 tablespoons
water	to batter.
Use vegetables such as mushrooms, cauliflower, eggplant, zucchini.
Yields 2 cups.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add cold water.
Add berries and set aside to cool.
Do not refrigerate.
Cream 3 tablespoons sugar with margarine; add pretzels.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°; cool.
Blend cream cheese with powdered sugar.
Add whipped topping.
Spread cream cheese mixture over cooled crust and let firm up in refrigerator.
When cream cheese mixture firms, top with strawberry mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: sirloin steak with molasses rub
directions: To prepare the rub, combine all ingredients, except steaks, in the bowl of a food processor and process until the mixture is well blended. This rub can be prepared in advance and stored in an airtight container until ready to use. Using your hands, completely cover the steaks with the rub. Place them on a plate; cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 4 hours. Remove steaks from the refrigerator and allow to return to room temperature while preparing the grill. Grill steaks for 6 to 8 minutes per side for medium-rare.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients except sugar.
Form into 1/2-inch balls. Bake in a 400° oven until light brown, about 14 minutes.
Roll in sugar while hot.
Cool and roll again.

title: 7-up lemon jello salad
directions: Mix jello, boiling water and 7-Up.
Let jell slightly.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and sliced bananas.
Let jell solid.
Cook sugar, flour, egg and pineapple juice.
Take off heat and let cool.
Add 2 tablespoons butter.
Fold in one cup of nondairy topping and spread over jello.
Refrigerate.

title: pink bavarian cream jello
directions: Drain strawberries, reserving syrup.
Pour boiling water over gelatin, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Add enough cold water to reserved syrup to measure 1 cup.
Stir into dissolved gelatin.
Chill until almost set.

title: old-fashion tea cakes
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt and set aside.
Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla to margarine and sugar mixture.
Then add flour mixture slowly and mix until smooth.
Roll out on floured surface and cut into biscuit shapes. Bake at 375° until brown.
Cool and remove.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, milk and cocoa in a pot on stove. Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Take off stove and stir in 3 cups of oatmeal.
Spoon onto foil and allow to cool.

title: mushroom roll-ups
directions: Make mixture of cream cheese, mushrooms and garlic; salt to taste.
Leave rolls in squares and sprinkle poppy seed on one side.
Turn squares over and put a roll of mixture down center of square.
Fold edges to meet.
Cut into 6 squares; bake at 350° until golden brown.
Makes 48 rolls.
Can be made ahead and frozen uncooked.
Best when served warm.
Use warming tray or chafing dish.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir in nuts.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until batter is moistened.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: celery seed dressing (for 100)
directions: Mix together in blender; keep in refrigerator. Shake before using.

title: mama's enchiladas
directions: Butter a 9 x 12 x 2-inch casserole.
Preheat oven to 350°. Fry meat in a skillet until browned, stirring with fork to keep it pebbly.
Drain; add chili powder, salt, pepper and chilies. Combine undiluted soups and enchilada sauce in saucepan.
Heat over medium heat, stirring until well blended.
Add 1 1/2 cups soup mixture to beef.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix
well; pat out in pie plate on bottom and up sides. Prick with fork.	Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: black chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; mix about 2 minutes at medium speed.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Excellent iced or topped with Cool Whip.

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Cook mixture in a medium-size pot until it forms a soft ball; add nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: homemade grits
directions: Combine pork, potato water, onion, garlic and seasonings in a large saucepan.
Bring to boiling point, then reduce heat and allow to simmer for 25 minutes or until surplus liquid is reduced. Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in mashed potato. Chill mixture.

title: brownstone front cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and add to sour cream which has been stirred with eggs.
Add vanilla and bake in moderate oven.

title: baked chopped suey
directions: Brown beef, onions and celery.
Brown uncooked rice.
Combine ingredients in casserole and mix well with soups and soy sauce. Cook 45 minutes at 350°.
After 30 minutes, top with Chinese noodles.
Return and finish cooking for 15 minutes.

title: chicken noodle supreme(main-dish soup)
directions: In large saucepan, combine soups; gradually stir in water. Add remaining ingredients.
Heat; stir occasionally.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: spiced cranberry tea
directions: For Spice Bag:
Place cinnamon and cloves in the center of a 6-inch square of 100% cheesecloth.
Bring corners of cheesecloth together and tie with a clean string.
Set aside.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix together and pour into crust made of vanilla wafers crushed very fine and combined with melted butter.
Beat egg whites and sugar for meringue.

title: butter cookies
directions: With
electric mixer cream butter; gradually add sugar. Beat until
light
and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla. With spoon blend
in
flour.
Fill cookie press and press out onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
May top with frosting, if desired, after cooling.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Chop cheese into pieces.
Crush crackers. Melt butter.
Add together all ingredients.
Cover with milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir casserole once while baking.

title: green rice bake
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
Saute onions in butter until soft but not brown.
Stir in rice, soup and broccoli. Turn into a buttered shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grammy's rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash rice several times in cold water. Put hot water into outside part of double boiler.
Put rice in inside part with salt and boiling water.
Boil 1/2 hour with lid on.
While rice boils, put 3 cups milk in separate pot and heat. Grease casserole dish with butter.
Into dish put boiled rice and milk, then add sugar and stir.
Bake for 1/2 hour until light crust forms.
Remove from oven and stir crust in.
Add vanilla.
Put back in oven until light crust forms again.
Remove and cool.

title: wieners in sweet sauce
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and bring to boil.
Cut wieners into bite size.
Heat in sauce.
Serve in chafing dish.
Makes 2 cups sauce.
Sauce keeps more than 1 month in refrigerator.

title: chili con carne
directions: *Comes boxed in stores.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake in a 350° oven until filling is set.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix and pudding mix.
Add sour cream, oil, water and eggs.
Beat well, about 2 minutes.
Add chocolate chips.
Grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes.
Very moist; no frosting needed.

title: apple oat crisp
directions: Work the last 6 items with a pastry blender or finger tips. Spread apples in bottom of a baking dish, sprinkle with topping. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
